Text:  'Say, "Ay, ay, sir."
Audio: SAY AYE AYE SIR

#:~:text=.%22-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='%20-,'ay%2C%20ay%2C%20sir.
Text:  'Ay, ay, sir.
Audio: AYE AYE SIR

#:~:text=sir.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='there%20is%20o,.
Text:  'There is one thing,' Peter continued, 'that every boy who serves under me has to promise, and so must you.
Audio: THERE IS ONE THING PETER CONTINUED THAT EVERY BOY WHO SERVES UNDER ME HAS TO PROMISE AND SO MUST YOU

#:~:text=ou.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=john%20p,%20
Text:  John paled.
Audio: JOHN PALED

#:~:text='it%20is%20th,.
Text:  'It is this, if we meet Hook in open fight, you must leave him to me.
Audio: IT IS THIS IF WE MEET HOOK IN OPEN FIGHT YOU MUST LEAVE HIM TO ME

#:~:text=me.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='i%20p,.%20
Text:  'I promise,' John said loyally.
Audio: I PROMISE JOHN SAID LOYALLY

#:~:text=for%20the%20moment%20they%20w,.%20
Text:  For the moment they were feeling less eerie, because Tink was flying with them, and in her light they could distinguish each other. 
Audio: FOR THE MOMENT THEY WERE FEELING LESS EERY BECAUSE TINK WAS FLYING WITH THEM AND IN HER LIGHT THEY COULD DISTINGUISH EACH OTHER

#:~:text=unfortunately%20she%20c,.%20
Text:  Unfortunately she could not fly so slowly as they, and so she had to go round and round them in a circle in which they moved as in a halo. 
Audio: UNFORTUNATELY SHE CANNOT FLY SO SLOWLY AS THEY AND SO SHE HAD TO GO ROUND AND ROUND THEM IN A CIRCLE IN WHICH THEY MOVED AS IN A HALO

#:~:text=wendy%20q,.%20
Text:  Wendy quite liked it, until Peter pointed out the drawback.
Audio: WENDY QUITE LIKED IT UNTIL PETER POINTED OUT THE DRAWBACKS

#:~:text='she%20te,.
Text:  'She tells me,' he said, 'that the pirates sighted us before the darkness came, and got Long Tom out.
Audio: SHE TELLS ME HE SAID THAT THE PIRATES SIGHTED US BEFORE THE DARKNESS CAME AND GOT LONG TOM OUT

#:~:text=ut.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='the%20b,%3F
Text:  'The big gun?
Audio: THE BIG GUN

#:~:text=un%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='yes.%20
Text:  'Yes. 
Audio: YES

#:~:text=and%20of%20course%20they,.
Text:  And of course they must see her light, and if they guess we are near it they are sure to let fly.
Audio: AND OF COURSE THEY MUST SEE HER LIGHT AND IF THEY GUESS WE ARE NEAR IT THEY ARE SURE TO LET FLY

#:~:text=fly.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='wendy!
Text:  'Wendy!
Audio: WENDY

#:~:text=dy!-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='john!
Text:  'John!
Audio: JOHN

#:~:text=hn!-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='michael!
Text:  'Michael!
Audio: MICHAEL

#:~:text=el!-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='tel,.%20
Text:  'Tell her to go away at once, Peter,' the three cried simultaneously, but he refused.
Audio: TELL HER TO GO AWAY AT ONCE PETER THE THREE CRIED SIMULTANEOUSLY BUT HE REFUSED

#:~:text='she%20th,.%20
Text:  'She thinks we have lost the way,' he replied stiffly, 'and she is rather frightened. 
Audio: SHE THINKS WE HAVE LOST THE WAY HE REPLIED STIFLY AND SHE IS RATHER FRIGHTENED

#:~:text=you%20don't%20think%20i%20would%20s,!
Text:  You don't think I would send her away all by herself when she is frightened!
Audio: YOU DON'T THINK I WOULD SEND HER AWAY ALL BY HERSELF WHEN SHE'S FRIGHTENED

#:~:text=ened!-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=for%20a%20moment%20t,.%20
Text:  For a moment the circle of light was broken, and something gave Peter a loving little pinch.
Audio: FOR A MOMENT THE CIRCLE OF LIGHT WAS BROKEN AND SOMETHING GAVE PETER A LOVING LITTLE PINCH

#:~:text='then%20tell%20her%2C,.
Text:  'Then tell her,' Wendy begged, 'to put out her light.
Audio: THEN TELL HER WENDY BEGGED TO PUT OUT HER LIGHT

#:~:text=ht.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='she%20can't%20p,.%20
Text:  'She can't put it out. 
Audio: SHE CAN'T PUT IT OUT

#:~:text=that%20is%20a,.%20
Text:  That is about the only thing fairies can't do. 
Audio: THAT IS ABOUT THE ONLY THING FAIRIES CAN'T DO IT JUST

#:~:text=it%20j,.
Text:  It just goes out of itself when she falls asleep, same as the stars.
Audio: IT JUST GOES OUT OF ITSELF WHEN SHE FALLS ASLEEP SAME AS THE STARS

#:~:text=rs.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='then%20tell%20her%20,.%20
Text:  'Then tell her to sleep at once,' John almost ordered.
Audio: THEN TELL HER TO SLEEP AT ONCE JOHN ALMOST ORDERED

#:~:text='she%20can't%20s,.%20
Text:  'She can't sleep except when she's sleepy. 
Audio: SHE CAN'T SLEEP EXCEPT WHEN SHE'S SLEEPY

#:~:text=it%20is%20the%20o,.
Text:  It is the only other thing fairies can't do.
Audio: IT IS THE ONLY OTHER THING FAIRIES CAN'T DO

#:~:text=%20do.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='seem,.
Text:  'Seems to me,' growled John, 'these are the only two things worth doing.
Audio: SEEMS TO ME GROWLED JOHN THESE ARE THE ONLY TWO THINGS WORTH DOING

#:~:text=ng.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=here%20he%20got,.%20
Text:  Here he got a pinch, but not a loving one.
Audio: HERE HE GOT A PINCH BUT NOT A LOVING ONE

#:~:text='if%20only%20o,.
Text:  'If only one of us had a pocket,' Peter said, 'we could carry her in it.
Audio: IF ONLY ONE OF US HAD A POCKET PETER SAID WE COULD CARRY HER IN IT

#:~:text='%20how,.%20
Text:  ' However, they had set off in such a hurry that there was not a pocket between the four of them.
Audio: HOWEVER THEY HAD SET OFF IN SUCH A HURRY THAT THERE WAS NOT A POCKET BETWEEN THE FOUR OF THEM

#:~:text=he%20had%20a%20ha,.%20
Text:  He had a happy idea. 
Audio: HE HAD A HAPPY IDEA

#:~:text=john's%20hat!
Text:  John's hat!
Audio: JOHN'S HAT

#:~:text=tink%20ag,.%20
Text:  Tink agreed to travel by hat if it was carried in the hand. 
Audio: TINK AGREED TO TRAVEL BY HAT IF IT WAS CARRIED IN THE HAND

#:~:text=john%20ca,.%20
Text:  John carried it, though she had hoped to be carried by Peter. 
Audio: JOHN CARRIED IT THOUGH SHE HAD HOPED TO BE CARRIED BY PETER

#:~:text=presently%20w,.%20
Text:  Presently Wendy took the hat, because John said it struck against his knee as he flew; and this, as we shall see, led to mischief, for Tinker Bell hated to be under an obligation to Wendy.
Audio: PRESENTLY WENDY TOOK THE HAT BECAUSE JOHN SAID IT STRUCK AGAINST HIS KNEE AS HE FLEW AND THIS AS WE SHALL SEE LED TO MISCHIEF FOR TINKERBELL HATED TO BE UNDER AN OBLIGATION TO WENDY

#:~:text=in%20the%20black%20t,.%20
Text:  In the black topper the light was completely hidden, and they flew on in silence. 
Audio: IN THE BLACK TOPPER THE LIGHT WAS COMPLETELY HIDDEN AND THEY FLEW ON IN SILENCE

#:~:text=it%20was%20the%20s,.%20
Text:  It was the stillest silence they had ever known, broken once by a distant lapping, which Peter explained was the wild beasts drinking at the ford, and again by a rasping sound that might have been the branches of trees rubbing together, but he said it was the redskins sharpening their knives.
Audio: IT WAS THE STILLEST SILENCE THEY HAD EVER KNOWN BROKEN ONCE BY A DISTANT LAPPING WICH PETER EXPLAINED WAS THE WILD BEAST'S DRINKING AT THE FORD AND AGAIN BY A RASPING SOUND THAT MIGHT HAVE BEEN THE BRANCHES OF TREES RUBBING TOGETHER BUT HE SAID IT WAS THE RED SKINS SHARPENING THEIR KNIVES

#:~:text=even%20thes,.%20
Text:  Even these noises ceased. 
Audio: EVEN THESE NOISES CEASED

#:~:text=to%20mic,.%20
Text:  To Michael the loneliness was dreadful. 
Audio: TO MICHAEL THE LONELINESS WAS DREADFUL

#:~:text='if%20only%20s,!
Text:  'If only something would make a sound!
Audio: IF ONLY SOMETHING WOULD MAKE A SOUND

#:~:text=d!-,'%20he%20cried.%20
Text:  ' he cried.
Audio: HE CRIED

#:~:text=as%20if%20in%20answer%20to%20h,.%20
Text:  As if in answer to his request, the air was rent by the most tremendous crash he had ever heard. 
Audio: AS OF IN ANSWER TO HIS REQUEST THE AIR WAS RENT BY THE MOST TREMENDOUS CRASH HE HAD EVER HEARD

#:~:text=the%20pirates%20h,.%20
Text:  The pirates had fired Long Tom at them.
Audio: THE PIRATES HAD FIRED LONG TOM AT THEM

#:~:text=the%20roar%20of%20i,%3F
Text:  The roar of it echoed through the mountains, and the echoes seemed to cry savagely, 'Where are they, where are they, where are they?
Audio: THE ROAR OF IT ECHOED THROUGH THE MOUNTAINS AND THE ECHO SEEMED TO CRY SAVAGELY WHERE ARE THEY WHERE ARE THEY WHERE ARE THEY

#:~:text=hey%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=thus%20s,.%20
Text:  Thus sharply did the terrified three learn the difference between an island of make-believe and the same island come true.
Audio: THUS SHARPLY THAT THE TERRIFIED THREE LEARNED THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN AN ISLAND OF MAKE-BELIEVE AND THE SAME ISLAND TO COME TRUE

#:~:text=when%20at%20last%20t,.%20
Text:  When at last the heavens were steady again, John and Michael found themselves alone in the darkness. 
Audio: WHEN AT LAST THE HEAVENS WERE STEADY AGAIN JOHN AND MICHAEL FOUND THEMSELVES ALONE IN THE DARKNESS

#:~:text=john%20was%20t,.%20
Text:  John was treading the air mechanically, and Michael without knowing how to float was floating.
Audio: JOHN WAS TREADING THE AIR MECHANICALLY AND MICHAEL WITHOUT KNOWING HOW TO FLOAT WAS FLOATING

#:~:text='are%20you%20sh,%3F
Text:  'Are you shot?
Audio: ARE YOU SHOT

#:~:text='%20john%20whispered%20t,%20
Text:  ' John whispered tremulously.
Audio: JOHN WHISPERED TREMULOUSLY

#:~:text='i%20haven,.%20
Text:  'I haven't tried yet,' Michael whispered back.
Audio: I haven't tried myself out yet, Michael whispered back.

#:~:text=we%20kno,.%20
Text:  We know now that no one had been hit. 
Audio: We know now that no one had been hit.

#:~:text=peter%2C%20h,.%20
Text:  Peter, however, had been carried by the wind of the shot far out to sea, while Wendy was blown upwards with no companion but Tinker Bell.
Audio: Peter, however, had been carried by the wind of the shot far out to sea, while Wendy was blown upwards with no companion but Tinkerbell.

#:~:text=it%20would%20have%20been%20w,.%20
Text:  It would have been well for Wendy if at that moment she had dropped the hat.
Audio: It would have been well for Wendy if at that moment she had dropped the hat.

#:~:text=i%20don't%20know%20whether%20t,.%20
Text:  I don't know whether the idea came suddenly to Tink, or whether she had planned it on the way, but she at once popped out of the hat and began to lure Wendy to her destruction.
Audio: I don't know whether the idea came suddenly to Tink, or whether she had planned it on the way, but she at once popped out of the hat and began to lure Wendy to her destruction.

#:~:text=tink%20was%20n,.%20
Text:  Tink was not all bad: or, rather, she was all bad just now, but, on the other hand, sometimes she was all good. 
Audio: Tink was not all bad, or, rather, she was all bad just now, but, on the other hand, sometimes she was all good.

#:~:text=fairies%20h,.%20
Text:  Fairies have to be one thing or the other, because being so small they unfortunately have room for one feeling only at a time. 
Audio: Fairies have to be one thing or the other, because being so small, they unfortunately have room for one feeling only at a time.

#:~:text=they%20are%2C,.%20
Text:  They are, however, allowed to change, only it must be a complete change. 
Audio: They are, however, allowed to change, only it must be a complete change.

#:~:text=at%20pres,.%20
Text:  At present she was full of jealousy of Wendy. 
Audio: At present, she was full of jealousy of Wendy.

#:~:text=what%20she%20s,.
Text:  What she said in her lovely tinkle Wendy could not of course understand, and I believe some of it was bad words, but it sounded kind, and she flew back and forward, plainly meaning 'Follow me, and all will be well.
Audio: What she said in her lovely Tinkle, Wendy could not, of course, understand, but I believe some of it was bad words. But it sounded kind, and she flew back and forward, plainly meaning, follow me, and all will be well.

#:~:text=ell.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=what%20e,%3F%20
Text:  What else could poor Wendy do? 
Audio: What else could poor Wendy do?

#:~:text=she%20cal,.%20
Text:  She called to Peter and John and Michael, and got only mocking echoes in reply. 
Audio: She called to Peter and John and Michael, and got only mocking echoes in reply.

#:~:text=she%20did%20not%20y,.%20
Text:  She did not yet know that Tink hated her with the fierce hatred of a very woman. 
Audio: She did not yet know that Tink hated her with the fierce hatred of a very woman.

#:~:text=and%20so%2C%20,.%20
Text:  And so, bewildered, and now staggering in her flight, she followed Tink to her doom.
Audio: And so, bewildered, and now staggering in her flight, she followed Tink to her doom. End of chapter 4 Recording by William Ching

#:~:text=.%20-,chapter%20v%20
Text:  CHAPTER V
Audio: CHAPTER V.

#:~:text=chapter%20v%20-,the%20island%20come%20true%20
Text:  THE ISLAND COME TRUE
Audio: THE ISLAND COME TRUE

#:~:text=feeling%20that%20p,.%20
Text:  Feeling that Peter was on his way back, the Neverland had again woke into life. 
Audio: Feeling that Peter was on his way back, the Neverland had again woken to life.

#:~:text=we%20o,.%20
Text:  We ought to use the pluperfect and say wakened, but woke is better and was always used by Peter.
Audio: We ought to use the pluperfect and say wakened, but woke is better, and was always used by Peter.

#:~:text=in%20his%20a,.%20
Text:  In his absence things are usually quiet on the island. 
Audio: In his absence things are usually quiet on the island.

#:~:text=the%20fairies%20,.%20
Text:  The fairies take an hour longer in the morning, the beasts attend to their young, the redskins feed heavily for six days and nights, and when pirates and lost boys meet they merely bite their thumbs at each other. 
Audio: The fairies take an hour longer in the morning, the beasts attend to their young, the redskins feed heavily for six days and nights, and when pirates and lost boys meet they merely bite their thumbs at each other.

#:~:text=but%20wi,.%20
Text:  But with the coming of Peter, who hates lethargy, they are all under way again: if you put your ear to the ground now, you would hear the whole island seething with life.
Audio: But with the coming of Peter, who hates lethargy, they are under way again. If you put your ear to the ground now you would hear the whole island seething with life.

#:~:text=on%20thi,.%20
Text:  On this evening the chief forces of the island were disposed as follows. 
Audio: On this evening the chief forces of the island were disposed as follows.

#:~:text=the%20lost%20boys%20w,.%20
Text:  The lost boys were out looking for Peter, the pirates were out looking for the lost boys, the redskins were out looking for the pirates, and the beasts were out looking for the redskins. 
Audio: The lost boys were out looking for Peter, the pirates were out looking for the lost boys, the redskins were out looking for the pirates, and the beasts were out looking for the redskins.

#:~:text=they%20were%20go,.%20
Text:  They were going round and round the island, but they did not meet because all were going at the same rate.
Audio: They were going round and round the island, but they did not meet, because all were going at the same rate.

#:~:text=all%20wan,.%20
Text:  All wanted blood except the boys, who liked it as a rule, but to-night were out to greet their captain. 
Audio: All wanted blood except the boys, who liked it as a rule, but to-night were out to greet their captain.

#:~:text=the%20boys%20o,.%20
Text:  The boys on the island vary, of course, in numbers, according as they get killed and so on; and when they seem to be growing up, which is against the rules, Peter thins them out; but at this time there were six of them, counting the twins as two. 
Audio: The boys on the island vary, of course, in numbers, according as they get killed and so on. And when they seem to be growing up, which is against the rules, Peter thins them out. But at this time there were six of them, counting the twins as two.

#:~:text=let%20us%20pr,.%20
Text:  Let us pretend to lie here among the sugar-cane and watch them as they steal by in single file, each with his hand on his dagger.
Audio: Let us pretend to lie here among the sugar-cane and watch them as they steal by in single file, each with his hand on his dagger.

#:~:text=they%20are%20f,.%20
Text:  They are forbidden by Peter to look in the least like him, and they wear the skins of bears slain by themselves, in which they are so round and furry that when they fall they roll. 
Audio: They are forbidden by Peter to look in the least like him, and they wear the skins of the bears, slain by themselves, in which they are so round and furry, that when they fall, they roll.

#:~:text=they%20have%20t,.%20
Text:  They have therefore become very sure-footed.
Audio: They have therefore become very sure-footed.

#:~:text=the%20first%20to%20p,.%20
Text:  The first to pass is Tootles, not the least brave but the most unfortunate of all that gallant band. 
Audio: The first to pass is tootles, not the least brave, but the most unfortunate of all that gallant band.

#:~:text=he%20had%20been%20i,.%20
Text:  He had been in fewer adventures than any of them, because the big things constantly happened just when he had stepped round the corner; all would be quiet, he would take the opportunity of going off to gather a few sticks for firewood, and then when he returned the others would be sweeping up the blood. 
Audio: He had been in fewer adventures than any of them, because the big things constantly happened just when he had stepped round the corner. All would be quiet, he would take the opportunity of going off to gather a few sticks for firewood, and then when he returned the others would be sweeping up the blood.

#:~:text=this%20il,.%20
Text:  This ill-luck had given a gentle melancholy to his countenance, but instead of souring his nature had sweetened it, so that he was quite the humblest of the boys. 
Audio: This ill-luck had given a gentle melancholy to his countenance, but instead of souring his nature, had sweetened it, so that he was quite the humblest of the boys.

#:~:text=poor%20k,.%20
Text:  Poor kind Tootles, there is danger in the air for you to-night. 
Audio: Poor, kind tootles, there is danger in the air for you to-night.

#:~:text=take%20care%20l,.%20
Text:  Take care lest an adventure is now offered you, which, if accepted, will plunge you in deepest woe. 
Audio: Take care lest an adventure is now offered you, which, if accepted, will plunge you in deepest woe.

#:~:text=tootles%2C%20the%20,.%20
Text:  Tootles, the fairy Tink who is bent on mischief this night is looking for a tool, and she thinks you the most easily tricked of the boys. 
Audio: Tootles, the fairy Tink, who is bent on mischief this night, is looking for a tool, and she thinks you are the most easily tricked of the boys.

#:~:text='war,.%20
Text:  'Ware Tinker Bell.
Audio: Beware Tinkerbell.

#:~:text=would%20th,.%20
Text:  Would that he could hear us, but we are not really on the island, and he passes by, biting his knuckles.
Audio: Would that he could hear us, but we are not really on the island, and he passes by, biting his knuckles.

#:~:text=next%20c,.%20
Text:  Next comes Nibs, the gay and debonair, followed by Slightly, who cuts whistles out of the trees and dances ecstatically to his own tunes. 
Audio: Next comes Nibs, the gay and debonair, followed by Slightly, who cuts whistles out of the trees, and dances ecstatically to his own tunes.

#:~:text=slightly%20is,.%20
Text:  Slightly is the most conceited of the boys. 
Audio: Slightly is the most conceited of the boys.

#:~:text=he%20thinks%20h,.%20
Text:  He thinks he remembers the days before he was lost, with their manners and customs, and this has given his nose an offensive tilt. 
Audio: He thinks he remembers the days before he was lost, with their manners and customs, and this has given his nose an offensive tilt.

#:~:text=curly%20i,.%20
Text:  Curly is fourth; he is a pickle, and so often has he had to deliver up his person when Peter said sternly, 'Stand forth the one who did this thing,' that now at the command he stands forth automatically whether he has done it or not. 
Audio: Curly is forth, he is a pickle, and so often has he had to deliver up his person when Peter said sternly, Stand forth, the one who did this thing! that now at the command he stands forth automatically, whether he has done it or not.

#:~:text=last%20c,.%20
Text:  Last come the Twins, who cannot be described because we should be sure to be describing the wrong one. 
Audio: Last come the twins, who cannot be described, because we should be sure to be describing the wrong one.

#:~:text=peter%20ne,.%20
Text:  Peter never quite knew what twins were, and his band were not allowed to know anything he did not know, so these two were always vague about themselves, and did their best to give satisfaction by keeping close together in an apologetic sort of way.
Audio: Peter never quite knew what twins were, and his band were not allowed to know anything he did not know, so these two were always vague about themselves, and did their best to give satisfaction by keeping close together in an apologetic sort of way.

#:~:text=the%20boys%20v,.%20
Text:  The boys vanish in the gloom, and after a pause, but not a long pause, for things go briskly on the island, come the pirates on their track. 
Audio: The boys vanish in the gloom, and after a pause, but not a long pause, for things go briskly on the island, come the pirates on their track.

#:~:text=we%20hear%20them,%3A%20
Text:  We hear them before they are seen, and it is always the same dreadful song:
Audio: We hear them before they are seen, and it is always the same dreadful song.

#:~:text='avast%20,to%2C%20
Text:  'Avast belay, yo ho, heave to,
Audio: A vast belay, yo ho, heave to

#:~:text=a-p,%2C%20
Text:  A-pirating we go,
Audio: a pirating we go,

#:~:text=and%20if%20w,t%20
Text:  And if we're parted by a shot
Audio: and if we are parted by a shot,

#:~:text=we're%20s,!
Text:  We're sure to meet below!
Audio: we are sure to meet below.

#:~:text=ow!-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=a%20mor,.%20
Text:  A more villainous-looking lot never hung in a row on Execution dock. 
Audio: A more villainous-looking lot never hung in a row on execution dock.

#:~:text=here%2C%20a%20,.%20
Text:  Here, a little in advance, ever and again with his head to the ground listening, his great arms bare, pieces of eight in his ears as ornaments, is the handsome Italian Cecco, who cut his name in letters of blood on the back of the governor of the prison at Gao. 
Audio: Here, a little in advance, ever and again with his head to the ground listening, his great arms bare, pieces of eight in his ears as ornaments, is the handsome Italian secco, who cut his name in letters of blood on the back of the governor of the prison at Geyo.

#:~:text=that%20gi,.%20
Text:  That gigantic black behind him has had many names since he dropped the one with which dusky mothers still terrify their children on the banks of the Guadjo-mo. 
Audio: That gigantic black behind him has had many names since he dropped the one with which dusky mothers still terrify their children on the banks of the Guadjomo.

#:~:text=here%20is%20bi,.%20
Text:  Here is Bill Jukes, every inch of him tattooed, the same Bill Jukes who got six dozen on the Walrus from Flint before he would drop the bag of moidores; and Cookson, said to be Black Murphy's brother (but this was never proved); and Gentleman Starkey, once an usher in a public school and still dainty in his ways of killing; and Skylights (Morgan's Skylights); and the Irish bo'sun Smee, an oddly genial man who stabbed, so to speak, without offence, and was the only Nonconformist in Hook's crew; and Noodler, whose hands were fixed on backwards; and Robt. 
Audio: Here is Bill Jukes, every inch of him tattooed, the same Bill Jukes, who got six dozen on the walrus from Flint before he would drop the bag of Mordorys, and Cookson, said to be Black Murphy's brother, but this was never proved, and Gentleman Starkey, once an usher in a public school, and still dainty in his ways of killing, and Skylights, Morgan's Skylights, and the Irish bosun Smee, an oddly genial man who stabbed, so to speak, without a fence, and was the only non-conformist in Hook's crew, and Noodler, whose hands were fixed on backwards, and Robert

#:~:text=mull,.%20
Text:  Mullins and Alf Mason and many another ruffian long known and feared on the Spanish Main.
Audio: Mullins, and Alf Mason, and many another ruffian long known and feared on the Spanish main.

#:~:text=in%20the%20mid,.%20
Text:  In the midst of them, the blackest and largest jewel in that dark setting, reclined James Hook, or as he wrote himself, Jas. 
Audio: In the midst of them, the blackest and largest in that dark setting, reclined James Hook, or as he wrote himself, J.A.S.

#:~:text=hook%2C%20of,.%20
Text:  Hook, of whom it is said he was the only man that the Sea-Cook feared. 
Audio: Hook, of whom it is said he was the only man that the sea-cook feared.

#:~:text=he%20lay,.%20
Text:  He lay at his ease in a rough chariot drawn and propelled by his men, and instead of a right hand he had the iron hook with which ever and anon he encouraged them to increase their pace. 
Audio: He lay at his ease in a rough chariot drawn and propelled by his men, and instead of a right hand he had the iron hook with which ever and anon he encouraged them to increase their pace.

#:~:text=as%20dogs%20thi,.%20
Text:  As dogs this terrible man treated and addressed them, and as dogs they obeyed him. 
Audio: As dogs this terrible man treated and addressed them, and as dogs they obeyed him.

#:~:text=in%20per,.%20
Text:  In person he was cadaverous and blackavized, and his hair was dressed in long curls, which at a little distance looked like black candles, and gave a singularly threatening expression to his handsome countenance. 
Audio: In person he was cadaverous and black-avised, and his hair was dressed in long curls, which at a little distance looked like black candles, and gave a singularly threatening expression to his handsome countenance.

#:~:text=his%20eyes%20were%20o,.%20
Text:  His eyes were of the blue of the forget-me-not, and of a profound melancholy, save when he was plunging his hook into you, at which time two red spots appeared in them and lit them up horribly. 
Audio: His eyes were of the blue of the forget-me-not, and of a profound melancholy, save when he was plunging his hook into you, at which time two red spots appeared in them, and lit them up horribly.

#:~:text=in%20ma,.%20
Text:  In manner, something of the grand seigneur still clung to him, so that he even ripped you up with an air, and I have been told that he was a raconteur of repute. 
Audio: In manner something of the grand seigneur still clung to him, so that he even ripped you up with an air, and I have been told that he was a raconteur of repute.

#:~:text=he%20was%20ne,.%20
Text:  He was never more sinister than when he was most polite, which is probably the truest test of breeding; and the elegance of his diction, even when he was swearing, no less than the distinction of his demeanour, showed him one of a different caste from his crew. 
Audio: He was never more sinister than when he was most polite, which is probably the truest test of breeding, and the elegance of his diction, even when he was swearing, no less than the distinction of his demeanour, showed him one of a different cast from his crew.

#:~:text=a%20man%20,.%20
Text:  A man of indomitable courage, it was said of him that the only thing he shied at was the sight of his own blood, which was thick and of an unusual colour. 
Audio: A man of indomitable courage, it was said that the only thing he shied at was the sight of his own blood, which was thick and of an unusual colour.

#:~:text=in%20dres,%2C%20
Text:  In dress he somewhat aped the attire associated with the name of Charles II., 
Audio: In dress he somewhat aped the attire associated with the name of Charles the

#:~:text=having%20h,.%20
Text:  having heard it said in some earlier period of his career that he bore a strange resemblance to the ill-fated Stuarts; and in his mouth he had a holder of his own contrivance which enabled him to smoke two cigars at once. 
Audio: Second, having heard it said in some earlier period of his career that he bore a strange resemblance to the ill-fated Stuarts, and in his mouth he had a holder of his own contrivance which enabled him to smoke two cigars at once,

#:~:text=but%20und,.%20
Text:  But undoubtedly the grimmest part of him was his iron claw.
Audio: but undoubtedly the grimmest part of him was his iron claw.

#:~:text=let%20us%20n,.%20
Text:  Let us now kill a pirate, to show Hook's method. 
Audio: Let us now kill a pirate, to show Hook's method.

#:~:text=skylights%20w,.%20
Text:  Skylights will do. 
Audio: Skylights will do.

#:~:text=as%20they%20p,.%20
Text:  As they pass, Skylights lurches clumsily against him, ruffling his lace collar; the hook shoots forth, there is a tearing sound and one screech, then the body is kicked aside, and the pirates pass on. 
Audio: As they pass, Skylights lurches clumsily against him, ruffling his lace collar. The Hook shoots forth, there is a tearing sound, and one screech. Then the body is kicked aside, and the pirates pass on.

#:~:text=he%20has%20n,.%20
Text:  He has not even taken the cigars from his mouth.
Audio: He has not even taken the cigars from his mouth.

#:~:text=such%20i,.%20
Text:  Such is the terrible man against whom Peter Pan is pitted. 
Audio: Such is the terrible man against whom Peter Pan is pitted.

#:~:text=which%20wi,%3F%20
Text:  Which will win?
Audio: Which will win?

#:~:text=on%20the%20trail%20of%20the%20p,.%20
Text:  On the trail of the pirates, stealing noiselessly down the war-path, which is not visible to inexperienced eyes, come the redskins, every one of them with his eyes peeled. 
Audio: On the trail of the pirates, stealing noiselessly down the war-path, which is not visible to inexperienced eyes, come the red-skins, every one of them with his eyes peeled.

#:~:text=they%20car,.%20
Text:  They carry tomahawks and knives, and their naked bodies gleam with paint and oil. 
Audio: They carry tomahawks and knives, and their naked bodies gleam with paint and oil.

#:~:text=strun,.%20
Text:  Strung around them are scalps, of boys as well as of pirates, for these are the Piccaninny tribe, and not to be confused with the softer-hearted Delawares or the Hurons. 
Audio: Strung around them are scalps, of boys as well as pirates, for these are the Pickaninny tribe, and not to be confused with the softer-hearted Delawares or the Hurons.

#:~:text=in%20the%20v,.%20
Text:  In the van, on all fours, is Great Big Little Panther, a brave of so many scalps that in his present position they somewhat impede his progress. 
Audio: In the van on all fours is great big little panther, a brave of so many scalps, that in his present position they somewhat impede his progress.

#:~:text=bringing%20u,.%20
Text:  Bringing up the rear, the place of greatest danger, comes Tiger Lily, proudly erect, a princess in her own right. 
Audio: Bringing up the rear, the place of greatest danger, comes Tiger Lily, proudly erect, a princess in her own right.

#:~:text=she%20is%20t,.%20
Text:  She is the most beautiful of dusky Dianas and the belle of the Piccaninnies, coquettish, cold and amorous by turns; there is not a brave who would not have the wayward thing to wife, but she staves off the altar with a hatchet. 
Audio: She is the most beautiful of dusky Dianas, and the belle of the Pickaninnys, coquettish, cold, and amorous by turns. There is not a brave who would not have the wayward thing to wife, but she stays off the altar with a hatchet.

#:~:text=obse,.%20
Text:  Observe how they pass over fallen twigs without making the slightest noise. 
Audio: Observe how they pass over fallen twigs without making the slightest noise.

#:~:text=the%20only%20sound%20t,.%20
Text:  The only sound to be heard is their somewhat heavy breathing. 
Audio: The only sound to be heard is their somewhat heavy breathing.

#:~:text=the%20fact,.%20
Text:  The fact is that they are all a little fat just now after the heavy gorging, but in time they will work this off. 
Audio: The fact is that they are all a little fat just now, after the heavy gorging, but in time they will work this off.

#:~:text=for%20the%20moment%2C%20h,.%20
Text:  For the moment, however, it constitutes their chief danger.
Audio: For the moment, however, it constitutes their chief danger.

#:~:text=the%20redskins%20d,.%20
Text:  The redskins disappear as they have come like shadows, and soon their place is taken by the beasts, a great and motley procession: lions, tigers, bears, and the innumerable smaller savage things that flee from them, for every kind of beast, and, more particularly; all the man-eaters, live cheek by jowl on the favoured island. 
Audio: The Redskins disappear as they have come, like shadows, and soon their place is taken by the beasts, a great and motley procession, lions, tigers, bears, and the innumerable smaller savage things that flee from them. For every kind of beast, and more particularly, all the man-eaters, live cheek by jowl on the favoured island.

#:~:text=their%20to,.%20
Text:  Their tongues are hanging out, they are hungry to-night.
Audio: Their tongues are hanging out. They are hungry to-night.

#:~:text=when%20they%20hav,.%20
Text:  When they have passed, comes the last figure of all, a gigantic crocodile. 
Audio: When they have passed, comes the last figure of all, a gigantic crocodile.

#:~:text=we%20shall%20see%20f,.%20
Text:  We shall see for whom she is looking presently.
Audio: We shall see for whom she is looking presently.

#:~:text=the%20crocodile%20,.%20
Text:  The crocodile passes, but soon the boys appear again, for the procession must continue indefinitely until one of the parties stops or changes its pace. 
Audio: The crocodile passes, but soon the boys appear again, for the procession must continue indefinitely until one of the parties stops or changes its pace.

#:~:text=then%20q,.%20
Text:  Then quickly they will be on top of each other.
Audio: Then quickly they will be on top of each other.

#:~:text=all%20ar,.%20
Text:  All are keeping a sharp look-out in front, but none suspects that the danger may be creeping up from behind. 
Audio: All are keeping a sharp look-out in front, but none suspects that the danger may be creeping up from behind.

#:~:text=this%20shows,.%20
Text:  This shows how real the island was.
Audio: This shows how real the island was.

#:~:text=the%20first%20to%20f,.%20
Text:  The first to fall out of the moving circle was the boys. 
Audio: The first to fall out of the moving circle was the boys.

#:~:text=they%20flu,.%20
Text:  They flung themselves down on the sward, close to their underground home.
Audio: They flung themselves down on the sward, close to their underground home.

#:~:text='i%20do%20w,.%20
Text:  'I do wish Peter would come back,' every one of them said nervously, though in height and still more in breadth they were all larger than their captain.
Audio: "'I do wish Peter would come back,' every one of them said nervously, though in height and still more in breadth, they were all larger than their captain.

#:~:text='i%20am%20t,.
Text:  'I am the only one who is not afraid of the pirates,' Slightly said, in the tone that prevented his being a general favourite; but perhaps some distant sound disturbed him, for he added hastily, 'but I wish he would come back, and tell us whether he has heard anything more about Cinderella.
Audio: "'I am the only one who is not afraid of the pirates,' Slightly said, in the tone that prevented his being a general favourite. But perhaps some distant sound disturbed him, for he added hastily, "'but I wish he would come back and tell us whether he has heard anything more about Cinderella.'

#:~:text=a.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=they%20talked%20o,.%20
Text:  They talked of Cinderella, and Tootles was confident that his mother must have been very like her.
Audio: They talked of Cinderella, and Tootles was confident that his mother must have been very like her.

#:~:text=it%20was%20only%20i,.%20
Text:  It was only in Peter's absence that they could speak of mothers, the subject being forbidden by him as silly.
Audio: It was only in Peter's absence that they could speak of mothers, the subject being forbidden by him as silly.

#:~:text='all,%22%20
Text:  'All I remember about my mother,' Nibs told them, 'is that she often said to father, "Oh, how I wish I had a cheque-book of my own." 
Audio: "'All I remember about my mother,' Nibs told them, is that she often said to my father, "'Oh, how I wish I had a check-book of my own!

#:~:text=i%20don't%20know%20wha,.
Text:  I don't know what a cheque-book is, but I should just love to give my mother one.
Audio: I don't know what a check-book is, but I should just love to give my mother one.'

#:~:text=one.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=while%20they%20t,.%20
Text:  While they talked they heard a distant sound. 
Audio: While they talked they heard a distant sound.

#:~:text=you%20or%20i%2C,%3A%20
Text:  You or I, not being wild things of the woods, would have heard nothing, but they heard it, and it was the grim song:
Audio: "'You or I, not being wild things of the woods, would have heard nothing. But they heard it, and it was the grim song.

#:~:text='yo%20,e%2C%20
Text:  'Yo ho, yo ho, the pirate life,
Audio: "'Yo-ho, yo-ho, the pirate life,

#:~:text=the%20fla,%2C%20
Text:  The flag o' skull and bones,
Audio: the flag of skull and bones,

#:~:text=a%20merry%20h,e%2C%20
Text:  A merry hour, a hempen rope,
Audio: a merry hour, a hemp and rope

#:~:text=and%20hey,.
Text:  And hey for Davy Jones.
Audio: and hay for Davy Jones!'

#:~:text=nes.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=at%20once%20the,%3F%20
Text:  At once the lost boys—but where are they? 
Audio: "'At once the lost boys—' "'But where are they?

#:~:text=they%20are%20no%20,.%20
Text:  They are no longer there. 
Audio: They are no longer there.

#:~:text=rabb,.%20
Text:  Rabbits could not have disappeared more quickly.
Audio: Rabbits could not have disappeared more quickly.

#:~:text=i%20will%20t,.%20
Text:  I will tell you where they are. 
Audio: "'I will tell you where they are.

#:~:text=with%20the%20exc,.%20
Text:  With the exception of Nibs, who has darted away to reconnoitre, they are already in their home under the ground, a very delightful residence of which we shall see a good deal presently. 
Audio: With the exception of Nibs, who has darted away to reconnoiter, they are already in their home under the ground, a very delightful residence of which we shall see a good deal presently.

#:~:text=but%20how%20h,%3F%20
Text:  But how have they reached it? 
Audio: But how have they reached it?

#:~:text=for%20there%20is%20n,.%20
Text:  for there is no entrance to be seen, not so much as a pile of brushwood, which if removed would disclose the mouth of a cave. 
Audio: For there is no entrance to be seen, not so much as a large stone, which, if rolled away, would disclose the mouth of a cave.

#:~:text=look%20c,.%20
Text:  Look closely, however, and you may note that there are here seven large trees, each having in its hollow trunk a hole as large as a boy. 
Audio: Look closely, however, and you may note that there are here seven large trees, each with a hole in its hollow trunk as large as a boy.

#:~:text=these%20are%20the%20s,.%20
Text:  These are the seven entrances to the home under the ground, for which Hook has been searching in vain these many moons. 
Audio: These are the seven entrances to the home under the ground, for which Hook has been searching in vain these many moons.

#:~:text=will%20he%20,%3F%20
Text:  Will he find it to-night?
Audio: Will he find it to-night?'

#:~:text=as%20the%20p,.%20
Text:  As the pirates advanced, the quick eye of Starkey sighted Nibs disappearing through the wood, and at once his pistol flashed out. 
Audio: As the pirates advanced, the quick eye of Starkey sighted Nibs disappearing through the wood, and at once his pistol flashed out.

#:~:text=but%20an,.%20
Text:  But an iron claw gripped his shoulder.
Audio: But an iron claw gripped his shoulder.

#:~:text='cap,.%20
Text:  'Captain, let go,' he cried, writhing.
Audio: "'Captain, let go!' he cried, writhing.

#:~:text=now%20fo,.%20
Text:  Now for the first time we hear the voice of Hook. 
Audio: Now, for the first time, we hear the voice of Hook.

#:~:text=it%20was%20a%20b,.%20
Text:  It was a black voice. 
Audio: It was a black voice.

#:~:text='pu,.%20
Text:  'Put back that pistol first,' it said threateningly.
Audio: "'Put back that pistol first,' it said threateningly.

#:~:text='it%20was%20one,.%20
Text:  'It was one of those boys you hate. 
Audio: "'It was one of those boys you hate.

#:~:text=i%20could%20h,.
Text:  I could have shot him dead.
Audio: I could have shot him dead.'

#:~:text=ad.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='ay%2C%20an,.%20
Text:  'Ay, and the sound would have brought Tiger Lily's redskins upon us. 
Audio: "'Aye, and the sound would have brought Tiger Lily's redskins upon us.

#:~:text=do%20you%20want%20t,%3F
Text:  Do you want to lose your scalp?
Audio: Do you want to lose your scalp?'

#:~:text=lp%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='shall%20i%20a,%3F
Text:  'Shall I after him, captain,' asked pathetic Smee, 'and tickle him with Johnny Corkscrew?
Audio: "'Shall I after him, Captain?' asked Pathetic Smee. "'And tickle him with Johnny Corkscrew?'

#:~:text='%20smee%20h,.%20
Text:  ' Smee had pleasant names for everything, and his cutlass was Johnny Corkscrew, because he wriggled it in the wound. 
Audio: Smee had pleasant names for everything, and his cutlass was Johnny Corkscrew, because he wiggled it in the wound.

#:~:text=one%20could%20m,.%20
Text:  One could mention many lovable traits in Smee. 
Audio: One could mention many lovable traits in Smee.

#:~:text=for%20instance%2C%20a,.%20
Text:  For instance, after killing, it was his spectacles he wiped instead of his weapon.
Audio: For instance, after killing, it was his spectacles he wiped, instead of his weapon.

#:~:text='johnn,.%20
Text:  'Johnny's a silent fellow,' he reminded Hook.
Audio: "'Johnny's a silent fellow,' he reminded Hook.

#:~:text='not%20n,.%20
Text:  'Not now, Smee,' Hook said darkly. 
Audio: "'Not now, Smee,' Hook said darkly.

#:~:text='he%20is%20o,.%20
Text:  'He is only one, and I want to mischief all the seven. 
