Text:  'It is, it is,' they all cried; 'we saw it at once.
Audio: It is, it is, they all cried We saw it at once

#:~:text=ce.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='ver,.%20
Text:  'Very well,' she said, 'I will do my best. 
Audio: Very well, she said I will do my best

#:~:text=come%20ins,.%20
Text:  Come inside at once, you naughty children; I am sure your feet are damp. 
Audio: Come inside at once You naughty children I am sure your feet are damp

#:~:text=and%20bef,.
Text:  And before I put you to bed I have just time to finish the story of Cinderella.
Audio: And before I put you to bed I have just time to finish the story of Cinderella

#:~:text=la.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=in%20they%20w,.%20
Text:  In they went; I don't know how there was room for them, but you can squeeze very tight in the Neverland. 
Audio: In they went I don't know how there was room for them But you can squeeze very tight in Neverland

#:~:text=and%20that%20w,.%20
Text:  And that was the first of the many joyous evenings they had with Wendy. 
Audio: And that was the first of the many joyous evenings they had with Wendy

#:~:text=by%20and%20by%20s,.%20
Text:  By and by she tucked them up in the great bed in the home under the trees, but she herself slept that night in the little house, and Peter kept watch outside with drawn sword, for the pirates could be heard carousing far away and the wolves were on the prowl. 
Audio: By and by she tucked them up in the great bed in the home under the trees But she herself slept that night in the little house And Peter kept watch outside with drawn sword For the pirates could be heard carousing far away And the wolves were on the prowl

#:~:text=the%20little%20house%20lo,.%20
Text:  The little house looked so cosy and safe in the darkness, with a bright light showing through its blinds, and the chimney smoking beautifully, and Peter standing on guard. 
Audio: The little house looked so cozy and safe in the darkness With a bright light showing through its blinds And the chimneys smoking beautifully And Peter standing on guard

#:~:text=after%20a%20t,.%20
Text:  After a time he fell asleep, and some unsteady fairies had to climb over him on their way home from an orgy. 
Audio: After a time he fell asleep And some unsteady fairies had to climb over him on their way home from an orgy

#:~:text=any%20of%20the%20o,.%20
Text:  Any of the other boys obstructing the fairy path at night they would have mischiefed, but they just tweaked Peter's nose and passed on.
Audio: Any of the other boys obstructing the ferry path at night They would have mischieved But they just tweaked Peter's nose And passed on

#:~:text=chapter%20vii%20
Text:  CHAPTER VII
Audio: This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain. For more information, and to find out how you can volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org. Read and recorded by Catherine Eastman www.stanford.edu slash Tilda Seastman On March 24, 2006. Peter Pan by J. M. Barrie Chapter 7

#:~:text=i%20-,the%20home%20under%20the%20ground%20
Text:  THE HOME UNDER THE GROUND
Audio: The Home Under the Ground

#:~:text=one%20of%20the%20f,.%20
Text:  One of the first things Peter did next day was to measure Wendy and John and Michael for hollow trees. 
Audio: One of the first things Peter did next day was to measure Wendy and John and Michael for hollow trees.

#:~:text=hook%2C%20y,.%20
Text:  Hook, you remember, had sneered at the boys for thinking they needed a tree apiece, but this was ignorance, for unless your tree fitted you it was difficult to go up and down, and no two of the boys were quite the same size. 
Audio: Hook, you remember, had sneered at the boys for thinking they needed a tree apiece. But this was ignorance, for unless your tree fitted you, it was difficult to go up and down, and no two of the boys were quite the same size.

#:~:text=once%20you%20fitt,.%20
Text:  Once you fitted, you drew in your breath at the top, and down you went at exactly the right speed, while to ascend you drew in and let out alternately, and so wriggled up. 
Audio: Once you fitted, you drew in your breath at the top, and down you went at exactly the right speed, while to ascend you drew in and let out alternately, and so wriggled up.

#:~:text=of%20course%2C%20w,.%20
Text:  Of course, when you have mastered the action you are able to do these things without thinking of them, and then nothing can be more graceful.
Audio: Of course, when you have mastered the action, you are able to do these things without thinking of them, and nothing can be more graceful.

#:~:text=but%20you%20simply%20m,.%20
Text:  But you simply must fit, and Peter measures you for your tree as carefully as for a suit of clothes: the only difference being that the clothes are made to fit you, while you have to be made to fit the tree. 
Audio: But you simply must fit. And Peter measures you for your tree as carefully as for a suit of clothes, the only difference being that the clothes are made to fit you, while you have to be made to fit the tree.

#:~:text=usually%20i,.%20
Text:  Usually it is done quite easily, as by your wearing too many garments or too few; but if you are bumpy in awkward places or the only available tree is an odd shape, Peter does some things to you, and after that you fit. 
Audio: Usually it is done quite easily, as by your wearing too many garments or too few. But if you are bumpy in awkward places, or the only available tree is an odd shape, Peter does some things to you. And after that you fit.

#:~:text=once%20you%20fit%2C,.%20
Text:  Once you fit, great care must be taken to go on fitting, and this, as Wendy was to discover to her delight, keeps a whole family in perfect condition.
Audio: Once you fit, great care must be taken to go on fitting. And this, as Wendy was to discover to her delight, keeps a whole family in perfect condition.

#:~:text=wendy%20and%20m,.%20
Text:  Wendy and Michael fitted their trees at the first try, but John had to be altered a little.
Audio: Wendy and Michael fitted their trees at the first try, but John had to be altered a little.

#:~:text=after%20a%20f,.%20
Text:  After a few days' practice they could go up and down as gaily as buckets in a well. 
Audio: After a few days' practice, they could go up and down as gaily as buckets in a well.

#:~:text=and%20how%20a,.%20
Text:  And how ardently they grew to love their home under the ground; especially Wendy. 
Audio: And how ardently they grew to love their home under the ground, especially Wendy.

#:~:text=it%20consisted%20o,.%20
Text:  It consisted of one large room, as all houses should do, with a floor in which you could dig if you wanted to go fishing, and in this floor grew stout mushrooms of a charming colour, which were used as stools. 
Audio: It consisted of one large room, as all houses should do, with a floor in which you could dig if you wanted to go fishing. And in this floor grew stout mushrooms of a charming color, which were used as stools.

#:~:text=a%20nev,.%20
Text:  A Never tree tried hard to grow in the centre of the room, but every morning they sawed the trunk through, level with the floor. 
Audio: A never-tree tried hard to grow in the center of the room. But every morning they sawed the trunk through, level with the floor.

#:~:text=by%20te,.%20
Text:  By tea-time it was always about two feet high, and then they put a door on top of it, the whole thus becoming a table; as soon as they cleared away, they sawed off the trunk again, and thus there was more room to play. 
Audio: By tea-time it was always about two feet high, and then they put a door on top of it, the hole thus becoming a table. As soon as they cleared away, they sawed off the trunk again, and thus there was more room to play.

#:~:text=there%20was%20an%20,.%20
Text:  There was an enormous fireplace which was in almost any part of the room where you cared to light it, and across this Wendy stretched strings, made of fibre, from which she suspended her washing. 
Audio: There was an enormous fireplace, which was in almost any part of the room where you cared to light it, and across this Wendy stretched strings made of fiber, from which she suspended her washing.

#:~:text=the%20bed%20w,.%20
Text:  The bed was tilted against the wall by day, and let down at 6.30, when it filled nearly half the room; and all the boys except Michael slept in it, lying like sardines in a tin. 
Audio: The bed was tilted against the wall by day, and let down at six-thirty, when it filled nearly half the room. And all the boys slept in it except Michael, lying like sardines in a tin.

#:~:text=there%20was%20a%20str,.%20
Text:  There was a strict rule against turning round until one gave the signal, when all turned at once. 
Audio: There was a strict rule against turning round until one gave the signal, when all turned at once.

#:~:text=michael%20sh,.%20
Text:  Michael should have used it also; but Wendy would have a baby, and he was the littlest, and you know what women are, and the short and the long of it is that he was hung up in a basket.
Audio: Michael should have used it also, but Wendy would have a baby. And he was the littlest. And you know what women are. And the short and long of it is that he was hung up in a basket.

#:~:text=it%20was%20ro,.%20
Text:  It was rough and simple, and not unlike what baby bears would have made of an underground house in the same circumstances. 
Audio: It was rough and simple, and not unlike what baby bears would have made of an underground house in the same circumstances.

#:~:text=but%20there%20was%20one%20r,.%20
Text:  But there was one recess in the wall, no larger than a bird-cage, which was the private apartment of Tinker Bell. 
Audio: But there was one recess in the wall no larger than a bird-cage, which was the private apartment of Tinkerbell.

#:~:text=it%20cou,.%20
Text:  It could be shut off from the rest of the home by a tiny curtain, which Tink, who was most fastidious, always kept drawn when dressing or undressing. 
Audio: It could be shut off from the rest of the house by a tiny curtain, which Tink, who was most fastidious, always kept drawn when dressing or undressing.

#:~:text=no%20wom,.%20
Text:  No woman, however large, could have had a more exquisite boudoir and bedchamber combined. 
Audio: No woman, however large, could have had a more exquisite boudoir and bed-chamber combined.

#:~:text=the%20couc,.%20
Text:  The couch, as she always called it, was a genuine Queen Mab, with club legs; and she varied the bedspreads according to what fruit-blossom was in season. 
Audio: The couch, as she always called it, was a genuine queen mab with club legs, and she varied the bed-spreads according to what fruit-blossom was in season.

#:~:text=her%20mi,.%20
Text:  Her mirror was a Puss-in-boots, of which there are now only three, unchipped, known to the fairy dealers; the wash-stand was Pie-crust and reversible, the chest of drawers an authentic Charming the Sixth, and the carpet and rugs of the best (the early) period of Margery and Robin. 
Audio: Her mirror was a puss-in-boots, of which there are now only three unchipped known to fairy dealers. The wash-stand was pie-crust and reversible, the chest of drawers an authentic charming the sixth, and the carpet and rugs the best, the early, period, of Marjorie and Robin.

#:~:text=there%20was%20a%20c,.%20
Text:  There was a chandelier from Tiddly winks for the look of the thing, but of course she lit the residence herself. 
Audio: There was a chandelier from Tiddlywinks for the look of the thing, but of course she lit the residence herself.

#:~:text=tink%20was%20v,.%20
Text:  Tink was very contemptuous of the rest of the house, as indeed was perhaps inevitable; and her chamber, though beautiful, looked rather conceited, having the appearance of a nose permanently turned up.
Audio: Tink was very contemptuous of the rest of the house, as indeed was perhaps inevitable, and her chamber, though beautiful, looked rather conceited, having the appearance of a nose permanently turned up.

#:~:text=i%20suppose%20i,.%20
Text:  I suppose it was all especially entrancing to Wendy, because those rampagious boys of hers gave her so much to do. 
Audio: I suppose it was all especially entrancing to Wendy, because those rampagious boys of hers gave her so much to do.

#:~:text=really%20ther,.%20
Text:  Really there were whole weeks when, except perhaps with a stocking in the evening, she was never above ground. 
Audio: Really, there were whole weeks when, except perhaps with a stocking in the evening, she was never above ground.

#:~:text=the%20coo,.%20
Text:  The cooking, I can tell you, kept her nose to the pot. 
Audio: The cooking, I can tell you, kept her nose to the pot,

#:~:text=their%20chie,.%20
Text:  Their chief food was roasted breadfruit, yams, cocoa-nuts, baked pig, mammee-apples, tappa rolls and bananas, washed down with calabashes of poe-poe; but you never exactly knew whether there would be a real meal or just a make-believe, it all depended upon Peter's whim. 
Audio: and even if there was nothing in it, even if there was no pot, she had to keep watching that it came a boil just the same. You never exactly knew whether there would be a real meal or just a make-believe. It all depended upon Peter's whim. He

#:~:text=he%20could%20e,.%20
Text:  He could eat, really eat, if it was part of a game, but he could not stodge just to feel stodgy, which is what most children like better than anything else; the next best thing being to talk about it. 
Audio: could eat, really eat, if it was part of a game. But he could not stodge just to feel stodgy, which is what most children like better than anything else, the next best thing being to talk about it.

#:~:text=make-believe%20w,.%20
Text:  Make-believe was so real to him that during a meal of it you could see him getting rounder. 
Audio: Make-believe was so real to him that during a meal of it you could see him getting rounder.

#:~:text=of%20course%20it%20was%20t,.%20
Text:  Of course it was trying, but you simply had to follow his lead, and if you could prove to him that you were getting loose for your tree he let you stodge.
Audio: Of course it was trying, but you simply had to follow his lead, and if you could prove to him that you were getting loose for your tree, he let you stodge.

#:~:text=wendy's%20fav,.%20
Text:  Wendy's favourite time for sewing and darning was after they had all gone to bed. 
Audio: Wendy's favorite time for sewing and darning was after they had all gone to bed.

#:~:text=then%2C%20as%20sh,.%20
Text:  Then, as she expressed it, she had a breathing time for herself; and she occupied it in making new things for them, and putting double pieces on the knees, for they were all most frightfully hard on their knees.
Audio: Then, as she expressed it, she had a breathing time for herself, and she occupied it in making new things for them and putting double pieces on the knees, for they were almost frightfully hard on their knees.

#:~:text=when%20she%20sa,.
Text:  When she sat down to a basketful of their stockings, every heel with a hole in it, she would fling up her arms and exclaim, 'Oh dear, I am sure I sometimes think spinsters are to be envied.
Audio: 

#:~:text=ied.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: she sat down to a basketful of their stockings, every heel with a hole in it, she would fling up her arms and exclaim, oh dear, I am sure I sometimes think spinsters are to be envied.

#:~:text=her%20face%20b,.%20
Text:  Her face beamed when she exclaimed this.
Audio: Her face beamed when she exclaimed this.

#:~:text=you%20remember%20,.%20
Text:  You remember about her pet wolf. 
Audio: You remember about her pet wolf?

#:~:text=well%2C%20i,.%20
Text:  Well, it very soon discovered that she had come to the island and it found her out, and they just ran into each other's arms. 
Audio: Well, it very soon discovered that she had come to the island, and it found her out, and they just ran into each other's arms.

#:~:text=after%20that%20i,.%20
Text:  After that it followed her about everywhere.
Audio: After that, it followed her about everywhere.

#:~:text=as%20time%20w,%3F%20
Text:  As time wore on did she think much about the beloved parents she had left behind her? 
Audio: As time wore on, did she think much about the beloved parents she had left behind her?

#:~:text=this%20is%20a%20,.%20
Text:  This is a difficult question, because it is quite impossible to say how time does wear on in the Neverland, where it is calculated by moons and suns, and there are ever so many more of them than on the mainland. 
Audio: This is a difficult question, because it is quite impossible to say how time does wear on in the Neverland, where it is calculated by moons and suns, and there are ever so many more of them than on the mainland.

#:~:text=but%20i%20a,.%20
Text:  But I am afraid that Wendy did not really worry about her father and mother; she was absolutely confident that they would always keep the window open for her to fly back by, and this gave her complete ease of mind. 
Audio: But I am afraid that Wendy did not really worry about her father and mother. She was absolutely confident that they would always keep the window open for her to fly back by, and this gave her complete ease of mind.

#:~:text=what%20did,.%20
Text:  What did disturb her at times was that John remembered his parents vaguely only, as people he had once known, while Michael was quite willing to believe that she was really his mother. 
Audio: What did disturb her at times was that John remembered his parents vaguely only as people he had once known, while Michael was quite willing to believe that she was really his mother.

#:~:text=these%20things%20s,.%20
Text:  These things scared her a little, and nobly anxious to do her duty, she tried to fix the old life in their minds by setting them examination papers on it, as like as possible to the ones she used to do at school. 
Audio: These things scared her a little, and, nobly anxious to do her duty, she tried to fix the old life in their minds by setting them examination papers on it as like as possible to the ones she used to do at school.

#:~:text=the%20other%20boys%20t,.%20
Text:  The other boys thought this awfully interesting, and insisted on joining, and they made slates for themselves, and sat round the table, writing and thinking hard about the questions she had written on another slate and passed round. 
Audio: The other boys thought this awfully interesting, and insisted on joining, and they made slates for themselves, and sat round the table, writing and thinking hard about the questions she had written on another slate, and passed round.

#:~:text=they%20were%20the%20m,%3F%20
Text:  They were the most ordinary questions—'What was the colour of Mother's eyes? 
Audio: They were the most ordinary questions. What was the colour of mother's eyes?

#:~:text=which%20was%20ta,%3F%20
Text:  Which was taller, Father or Mother? 
Audio: Which was taller, father or mother?

#:~:text=was%20mot,%3F%20
Text:  Was Mother blonde or brunette? 
Audio: Was mother blonde or brunette?

#:~:text=answer%20a,.
Text:  Answer all three questions if possible.
Audio: Answer all three questions if possible.

#:~:text='%20',.%20
Text:  ' '(A) Write an essay of not less than 40 words on How I spent my last Holidays, or The Caracters of Father and Mother compared. 
Audio: A. Write an essay of not less than 40 words on how I spent my last holidays, or, the characters of father and mother compared,

#:~:text=only%20one%20of,.
Text:  Only one of these to be attempted.
Audio: only one of these to be attempted.

#:~:text='%20o,.
Text:  ' Or '(1) Describe Mother's laugh; (2) Describe Father's laugh; (3) Describe Mother's Party Dress; (4) Describe the Kennel and its Inmate.
Audio: 1. Describe mother's laugh. 2. Describe father's laugh. 3. Describe mother's party dress. 4. Describe the kennel and its inmate.

#:~:text=te.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=they%20were%20j,.%20
Text:  They were just everyday questions like these, and when you could not answer them you were told to make a cross; and it was really dreadful what a number of crosses even John made. 
Audio: They were just everyday questions like these, and when you could not answer them you were told to make a cross. And it was really dreadful what a number of crosses even John made.

#:~:text=of%20course%20the%20,.%20
Text:  Of course the only boy who replied to every question was Slightly, and no one could have been more hopeful of coming out first, but his answers were perfectly ridiculous, and he really came out last: a melancholy thing.
Audio: Of course the only boy who replied to every question was slightly, and no one could have been more hopeful of coming out first. But his answers were perfectly ridiculous, and he really came out last. A melancholy thing.

#:~:text=peter%20did%20no,.%20
Text:  Peter did not compete. 
Audio: Peter did not compete.

#:~:text=for%20one%20thing%20,.%20
Text:  For one thing he despised all mothers except Wendy, and for another he was the only boy on the island who could neither write nor spell; not the smallest word. 
Audio: For one thing, he despised all mothers except Wendy, and for another, he was the only boy on the island who could neither write nor spell, not the smallest word.

#:~:text=he%20was%20abo,.%20
Text:  He was above all that sort of thing.
Audio: He was above all that sort of thing.

#:~:text=by%20the%20wa,.%20
Text:  By the way, the questions were all written in the past tense. 
Audio: By the way, the questions were all written in the past tense.

#:~:text=what%20was%20the%20colour%20of%20mother's%20eyes%2C,.%20
Text:  What was the colour of Mother's eyes, and so on. 
Audio: What was the color of mother's eyes? And so on.

#:~:text=wendy%2C%20you%20s,.%20
Text:  Wendy, you see, had been forgetting too.
Audio: Wendy, you see, had been forgetting too.

#:~:text=adventures%2C%20o,.%20
Text:  Adventures, of course, as we shall see, were of daily occurrence; but about this time Peter invented, with Wendy's help, a new game that fascinated him enormously, until he suddenly had no more interest in it, which, as you have been told, was what always happened with his games. 
Audio: Adventures, of course, as we shall see, were of daily occurrence. But about this time, Peter invented, with Wendy's help, a new game that fascinated him enormously, until he suddenly had no more interest in it, which, as you have been told, was what always happened with his games.

#:~:text=it%20consisted%20i,.%20
Text:  It consisted in pretending not to have adventures, in doing the sort of thing John and Michael had been doing all their lives: sitting on stools flinging balls in the air, pushing each other, going out for walks and coming back without having killed so much as a grizzly. 
Audio: It consisted in pretending not to to have adventures. In doing the sort of thing John and Michael had been doing all their lives. Sitting on stools, flinging balls in the air, pushing each other, going out for walks, and coming back without having killed so much as a grizzly.

#:~:text=to%20see%20p,.%20
Text:  To see Peter doing nothing on a stool was a great sight; he could not help looking solemn at such times, to sit still seemed to him such a comic thing to do. 
Audio: To see Peter doing nothing on a stool was a great sight. He could not help looking solemn at such times. To sit still seemed to him such a comic thing to do.

#:~:text=he%20boas,.%20
Text:  He boasted that he had gone a walk for the good of his health. 
Audio: He boasted that he had gone walking for the good of his health.

#:~:text=for%20sev,.%20
Text:  For several suns these were the most novel of all adventures to him; and John and Michael had to pretend to be delighted also; otherwise he would have treated them severely.
Audio: For several sons, these were the most novel of all adventures to him. And John and Michael had to pretend to be delighted also, otherwise he would have treated them severely.

#:~:text=he%20often%20w,.%20
Text:  He often went out alone, and when he came back you were never absolutely certain whether he had had an adventure or not. 
Audio: He often went out alone. And when he came back, you were never absolutely certain whether he had had an adventure or not.

#:~:text=he%20might%20h,.%20
Text:  He might have forgotten it so completely that he said nothing about it; and then when you went out you found the body; and, on the other hand, he might say a great deal about it, and yet you could not find the body. 
Audio: He might have forgotten it so completely that he said nothing about it. And then when you went out, you found the body. And on the other hand, he might say a great deal about it. And yet you could not find the body.

#:~:text=sometimes%20he,.%20
Text:  Sometimes he came home with his head bandaged, and then Wendy cooed over him and bathed it in lukewarm water, while he told a dazzling tale. 
Audio: Sometimes he came home with his head bandaged, and then Wendy cooed over him and bathed it in lukewarm water while he told a dazzling tale.

#:~:text=but%20she%20was%20n,.%20
Text:  But she was never quite sure, you know. 
Audio: But she was never quite sure, you know.

#:~:text=there%20were%2C,.%20
Text:  There were, however, many adventures which she knew to be true because she was in them herself, and there were still more that were at least partly true, for the other boys were in them and said they were wholly true. 
Audio: There were, however, many adventures which she knew to be true, because she was in them herself. And there were still more that were at least partly true, for the other boys were in them and said they were wholly true.

#:~:text=to%20describe%20t,.%20
Text:  To describe them all would require a book as large as an English-Latin, Latin-English Dictionary, and the most we can do is to give one as a specimen of an average hour on the island. 
Audio: To describe them all would require a book as large as an English Latin-Latin-English dictionary. And the most we can do is to give one as a specimen of an average hour on the island.

#:~:text=the%20dif,.%20
Text:  The difficulty is which one to choose. 
Audio: The difficulty is which one to choose.

#:~:text=should%20w,%3F%20
Text:  Should we take the brush with the redskins at Slightly Gulch? 
Audio: Should we take the brush with the redskins at slightly gulch?

#:~:text=it%20was%20a%20sa,.%20
Text:  It was a sanguinary affair, and especially interesting as showing one of Peter's peculiarities, which was that in the middle of a fight he would suddenly change sides. 
Audio: It was a sanguinary affair, and especially interesting, as showing one of Peter's peculiarities, which was that in the middle of a fight he would suddenly change sides.

#:~:text=at%20the%20gulch%2C,%3F
Text:  At the Gulch, when victory was still in the balance, sometimes leaning this way and sometimes that, he called out, 'I'm redskin to-day; what are you, Tootles?
Audio: At the gulch, when victory was still in the balance, sometimes leaning this way and sometimes that, he called out, I'm Redskin today. What are you, Tootles?

#:~:text='%20and%20t,%3F
Text:  ' And Tootles answered, 'Redskin; what are you, Nibs?
Audio: And Tootles answered, Redskin, what are you, Nibs?

#:~:text='%20and%20n,%3F
Text:  ' and Nibs said,'Redskin; what are you, Twin?
Audio: And Nibs said, Redskin, what are you, Twin?

#:~:text='%20and%20so%20on%3B,.%20
Text:  ' and so on; and they were all redskin; and of course this would have ended the fight had not the real redskins, fascinated by Peter's methods, agreed to be lost boys for that once, and so at it they all went again, more fiercely than ever.
Audio: And so on. And they were all redskins. And of course, this would have ended the fight had not the real redskins, fascinated by Peter's methods, agreed to be lost boys for that once. And so at it they all went again more fiercely than ever.

#:~:text=the%20extra,.%20
Text:  The extraordinary upshot of this adventure was—but we have not decided yet that this is the adventure we are to narrate. 
Audio: The extraordinary upshot of this adventure was, but we have not decided yet that this is the adventure we are to narrate.

#:~:text=perhaps%20a,.%20
Text:  Perhaps a better one would be the night attack by the redskins on the house under the ground, when several of them stuck in the hollow trees and had to be pulled out like corks. 
Audio: Perhaps a better one would be the night attack by the redskins on the house under the ground, when several of them stuck in the hollow trees and had to be pulled out like corks.

#:~:text=or%20we%20m,.%20
Text:  Or we might tell how Peter saved Tiger Lily's life in the Mermaids' Lagoon, and so made her his ally.
Audio: Or we might tell how Peter saved Tiger Lily's life in the Mermaid's Lagoon, and so made her his ally.

#:~:text=or%20we%20c,.%20
Text:  Or we could tell of that cake the pirates cooked so that the boys might eat it and perish; and how they placed it in one cunning spot after another; but always Wendy snatched it from the hands of her children, so that in time it lost its succulence, and became as hard as a stone, and was used as a missile, and Hook fell over it in the dark.
Audio: Or we could tell of that cake the pirates cooked so that the boys might eat it and perish, and how they placed it in one cunning spot after another. But always Wendy snatched it from the hands of her children, so that in time it lost its succulents, and became as hard as a stone, and was used as a missile, and Hook fell over it in the dark.

#:~:text=or%20sup,.%20
Text:  Or suppose we tell of the birds that were Peter's friends, particularly of the Never bird that built in a tree overhanging the lagoon, and how the nest fell into the water, and still the bird sat on her eggs, and Peter gave orders that she was not to be disturbed. 
Audio: Or suppose we tell of the birds that were Peter's friends, particularly of the never-bird that built in a tree overhanging the lagoon, and how the nest fell into the water. And still the bird sat on her eggs, and Peter gave orders that she was not to be disturbed.

#:~:text=that%20is%20a%20p,.%20
Text:  That is a pretty story, and the end shows how grateful a bird can be; but if we tell it we must also tell the whole adventure of the lagoon, which would of course be telling two adventures rather than just one. 
Audio: That is a pretty story, and the end shows how grateful a bird can be. But if we tell it, we must also tell the whole adventure of the lagoon, which would of course be telling two adventures rather than just one.

#:~:text=a%20sho,.%20
Text:  A shorter adventure, and quite as exciting, was Tinker Bell's attempt, with the help of some street fairies, to have the sleeping Wendy conveyed on a great floating leaf to the mainland. 
Audio: A shorter adventure, and quite as exciting, was Tinker Bell's attempt, with the help of some street fairies, to have the sleeping Wendy conveyed on a great floating leaf of the island.

#:~:text=fortu,.%20
Text:  Fortunately the leaf gave way and Wendy woke, thinking it was bath-time, and swam back. 
Audio: Fortunately, the leaf gave way, and Wendy woke, thinking it was bath-time, and swam back.

#:~:text=or%20ag,.%20
Text:  Or again, we might choose Peter's defiance of the lions, when he drew a circle round him on the ground with an arrow and defied them to cross it; and though he waited for hours, with the other boys and Wendy looking on breathlessly from trees, not one of them dared to accept his challenge.
Audio: Or, again, we might choose Peter's defiance of the lions, when he drew a circle round him on the ground with an arrow, and dared them to cross it. And though he waited for hours, with the other boys and Wendy looking on breathlessly from trees, not one of them dared to accept his challenge.

#:~:text=which%20of%20thes,%3F%20
Text:  Which of these adventures shall we choose? 
Audio: Which of these adventures shall we choose?

#:~:text=the%20best%20w,.%20
Text:  The best way will be to toss for it.
Audio: The best way will be to toss for it.

#:~:text=i%20have%20tos,.%20
Text:  I have tossed, and the lagoon has won. 
Audio: I have tossed, and the lagoon has won.

#:~:text=this%20alm,.%20
Text:  This almost makes one wish that the gulch or the cake or Tink's leaf had won. 
Audio: This almost makes one wish that the gulch, or the cake, or Tink's leaf had won.

#:~:text=of%20course%20i%20c,.%20
Text:  Of course I could do it again, and make it best out of three; however, perhaps fairest to stick to the lagoon.
Audio: Of course I could do it again, and make it the best out of three. However, perhaps fairest, to stick to the lagoon.

#:~:text=chapter%20viii
Text:  CHAPTER VIII
Audio: This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain. For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org. Recording by Lizzy Oldfather. Peter Pan by J. M. Barry. Chapter 8.

#:~:text=the%20mermaids'%20lagoon%20
Text:  THE MERMAIDS' LAGOON
Audio: The Mermaid's Lagoon.

#:~:text=if%20you%20sh,.%20
Text:  If you shut your eyes and are a lucky one, you may see at times a shapeless pool of lovely pale colours suspended in the darkness; then if you squeeze your eyes tighter, the pool begins to take shape, and the colours become so vivid that with another squeeze they must go on fire. 
Audio: If you shut your eyes and are a lucky one, you may see at times a shapeless pool of lovely pale colors suspended in the darkness. Then if you squeeze your eyes tighter, the pool begins to take shape, and the colors become so vivid that with another squeeze they must go on fire.

#:~:text=but%20ju,.%20
Text:  But just before they go on fire you see the lagoon. 
Audio: But just before they go on fire, you see the lagoon.

#:~:text=this%20is%20the%20n,.%20
Text:  This is the nearest you ever get to it on the mainland, just one heavenly moment; if there could be two moments you might see the surf and hear the mermaids singing.
Audio: This is the nearest you ever get to it on the mainland, just one heavenly moment. If there could be two moments, you might see the surf and hear the mermaids singing.

#:~:text=the%20children%20o,.%20
Text:  The children often spent long summer days on this lagoon, swimming or floating most of the time, playing the mermaid games in the water, and so forth. 
Audio: The children often spent long summer days on this lagoon, swimming or floating most of the time, playing the mermaid games in the water and so forth.

#:~:text=you%20mu,.%20
Text:  You must not think from this that the mermaids were on friendly terms with them; on the contrary, it was among Wendy's lasting regrets that all the time she was on the island she never had a civil word from one of them. 
Audio: You must not think from this that the mermaids were on friendly terms with them. On the contrary, it was among Wendy's lasting regrets that all the time she was on the island she never had a civil word from one of them.

#:~:text=when%20she%20st,.%20
Text:  When she stole softly to the edge of the lagoon she might see them by the score, especially on Marooners' Rock, where they loved to bask, combing out their hair in a lazy way that quite irritated her; or she might even swim, on tiptoe as it were, to within a yard of them, but then they saw her and dived, probably splashing her with their tails, not by accident, but intentionally.
Audio: When she stole softly to the edge of the lagoon, she might see them by the score, especially on Marooner's rock, where they loved to bask, combing out their hair in a lazy way that quite irritated her. Or she might even swim, on tiptoe as it were, to within a yard of them. But then they saw her and dived, probably splashing her with their tails, not by accident, but intentionally.

#:~:text=they%20treate,.%20
Text:  They treated all the boys in the same way, except of course Peter, who chatted with them on Marooners' Rock by the hour, and sat on their tails when they got cheeky. 
Audio: They treated all the boys in the same way, except, of course, Peter, who chatted with them on Marooner's rock by the hour and sat on their tails when they got cheeky.

#:~:text=he%20gave%20w,.%20
Text:  He gave Wendy one of their combs.
Audio: He gave Wendy one of their combs.

#:~:text=the%20most%20ha,.%20
Text:  The most haunting time at which to see them is at the turn of the moon, when they utter strange wailing cries; but the lagoon is dangerous for mortals then, and until the evening of which we have now to tell, Wendy had never seen the lagoon by moonlight, less from fear, for of course Peter would have accompanied her, than because she had strict rules about every one being in bed by seven. 
Audio: The most haunting time at which to see them is at the turn of the moon, when they utter strange wailing cries. But the lagoon is dangerous for mortals then, and until the evening, of which we now have to tell, Wendy had never seen the lagoon by moonlight. Less from fear, for, of course, Peter would have accompanied her, than because she had strict rules about everyone being in bed by seven.

#:~:text=she%20was%20of,.%20
Text:  She was often at the lagoon, however, on sunny days after rain, when the mermaids come up in extraordinary numbers to play with their bubbles. 
Audio: She was often at the lagoon, however, on sunny days after rain, when the mermaids come up in extraordinary numbers to play with their bubbles.

#:~:text=the%20bubbles,.%20
Text:  The bubbles of many colours made in rainbow water they treat as balls, hitting them gaily from one to another with their tails, and trying to keep them in the rainbow till they burst. 
Audio: The bubbles of many colors made in the rainbow water they treat as balls, hitting them gaily from one to another with their tails, and trying to keep them in the rainbow until they burst.

#:~:text=the%20goa,.%20
Text:  The goals are at each end of the rainbow, and the keepers only are allowed to use their hands. 
Audio: The goals are at each end of the rainbow, and the keepers only are allowed to use their hands.

#:~:text=sometimes%20hu,.%20
Text:  Sometimes hundreds of mermaids will be playing in the lagoon at a time, and it is quite a pretty sight.
Audio: Sometimes a dozen of these games will be going on in the lagoon at a time, and it is quite a pretty sight.

#:~:text=but%20the%20mom,.%20
Text:  But the moment the children tried to join in they had to play by themselves, for the mermaids immediately disappeared. 
Audio: But the moment the children tried to join in, they had to play by themselves, for the mermaids immediately disappeared.

#:~:text=nevertheless%20w,.%20
Text:  Nevertheless we have proof that they secretly watched the interlopers, and were not above taking an idea from them; for John introduced a new way of hitting the bubble, with the head instead of the hand, and the mermaid goal-keepers adopted it. 
Audio: Nevertheless, we have proof that they secretly watched the interlopers, and were not above taking an idea from them, for John introduced a new way of hitting the bubble, with the head instead of the hand, and the mermaids adopted it.

#:~:text=this%20is%20the%20o,.%20
Text:  This is the one mark that John has left on the Neverland.
Audio: This is the one mark that John has left on the Neverland.

#:~:text=it%20must%20a,.%20
Text:  It must also have been rather pretty to see the children resting on a rock for half an hour after their midday meal. 
Audio: It must also have been rather pretty to see the children resting on a rock for half an hour after their midday meal.

#:~:text=wendy%20i,.%20
Text:  Wendy insisted on their doing this, and it had to be a real rest even though the meal was make-believe. 
Audio: Wendy insisted on their doing this, and it had to be a real rest, even though the meal was make-believe.

#:~:text=so%20they%20l,.%20
Text:  So they lay there in the sun, and their bodies glistened in it, while she sat beside them and looked important.
Audio: So they lay there in the sun, and their bodies glistened in it, while she sat beside them and looked important.

#:~:text=it%20was%20one,.%20
Text:  It was one such day, and they were all on Marooners' Rock. 
Audio: It was one such day, and they were all on Marooner's rock.

#:~:text=the%20rock%20was%20n,.%20
Text:  The rock was not much larger than their great bed, but of course they all knew how not to take up much room, and they were dozing, or at least lying with their eyes shut, and pinching occasionally when they thought Wendy was not looking. 
Audio: The rock was not much larger than their great bed, but of course they all knew how not to take up much room, and they were dozing, or at least lying with their eyes shut, and pinching occasionally, when they thought Wendy was not looking.

#:~:text=she%20was%20very%20b,.%20
Text:  She was very busy, stitching.
Audio: She was very busy stitching.

#:~:text=while%20she%20st,.%20
Text:  While she stitched a change came to the lagoon. 
Audio: While she stitched, a change came to the lagoon.

#:~:text=little%20sh,.%20
Text:  Little shivers ran over it, and the sun went away and shadows stole across the water, turning it cold. 
Audio: Little shivers ran over it, and the sun went away, and shadows stole across the water, turning it cold.

#:~:text=wendy%20cou,.%20
Text:  Wendy could no longer see to thread her needle, and when she looked up, the lagoon that had always hitherto been such a laughing place seemed formidable and unfriendly.
Audio: Wendy could no longer see to thread her needle, and when she looked up, the lagoon that had always hitherto been such a laughing place seemed formidable and unfriendly.

#:~:text=it%20was%20not%2C,.%20
Text:  It was not, she knew, that night had come, but something as dark as night had come. 
Audio: It was not, she knew, that night had come, but something as dark as night had come.

#:~:text=no%2C%20wo,.%20
Text:  No, worse than that. 
Audio: No, worse than that.

#:~:text=it%20had%20not%20c,.%20
Text:  It had not come, but it had sent that shiver through the sea to say that it was coming. 
Audio: It had not come, but it had sent that shiver through the sea to say that it was coming.

#:~:text=what%20was%20it%3F
Text:  What was it?
Audio: What was it?

#:~:text=there%20cr,.%20
Text:  There crowded upon her all the stories she had been told of Marooners' Rock, so called because evil captains put sailors on it and leave them there to drown. 
Audio: There crowded upon her all the stories she had been told of Marooner's rock. So-called because evil captains put sailors on it and leave them there to drown.

#:~:text=they%20dr,.%20
Text:  They drown when the tide rises, for then it is submerged.
Audio: They drown when the tide rises, for then it is submerged.

#:~:text=of%20course%20she%20s,.%20
Text:  Of course she should have roused the children at once; not merely because of the unknown that was stalking toward them, but because it was no longer good for them to sleep on a rock grown chilly. 
Audio: Of course she should have roused the children at once, not merely because of the unknown that was stalking towards them, but because it was no longer good for them to sleep on a rock-grown chili. But she was a young mother, and she did not know this. She thought you simply

#:~:text=but%20she%20was%20a,.%20
Text:  But she was a young mother and she did not know this; she thought you simply must stick to your rule about half an hour after the midday meal. 
Audio: must stick to your rule about half an hour after the midday meal.

#:~:text=so%2C%20tho,.%20
Text:  So, though fear was upon her, and she longed to hear male voices, she would not waken them. 
Audio: So, though fear was upon her and she longed to hear male voices, she would not waken them.

#:~:text=even%20w,.%20
Text:  Even when she heard the sound of muffled oars, though her heart was in her mouth, she did not waken them. 
Audio: Even when she heard the sound of muffled oars, though her heart was in her mouth, she did not waken them.

#:~:text=she%20stoo,.%20
Text:  She stood over them to let them have their sleep out. 
Audio: She stood over to let them have their sleep out.

#:~:text=was%20it%20not%20br,%3F%20
Text:  Was it not brave of Wendy?
Audio: Was it not brave of Wendy?

#:~:text=it%20was%20wel,.%20
Text:  It was well for those boys then that there was one among them who could sniff danger even in his sleep. 
Audio: It was well for those boys, then, that there was one among them who could sniff danger even in his sleep.

#:~:text=peter%20sp,.%20
Text:  Peter sprang erect, as wide awake at once as a dog, and with one warning cry he roused the others.
Audio: Peter sprang erect, as wide awake at once as a dog, and with one warning cry he roused the others.

#:~:text=he%20stood%20m,.%20
Text:  He stood motionless, one hand to his ear.
Audio: He stood motionless, one hand to his ear.

#:~:text='pi,!
Text:  'Pirates!
Audio: Pirates!

#:~:text=!-,'%20he%20cried.%20
Text:  ' he cried. 
Audio: he cried.

#:~:text=the%20others%20c,.%20
Text:  The others came closer to him. 
Audio: The others came closer to him. A

#:~:text=a%20strange%20sm,.%20
Text:  A strange smile was playing about his face, and Wendy saw it and shuddered. 
Audio: A strange smile was playing about his face, and Wendy saw it and shuddered.

#:~:text=while%20tha,.%20
Text:  While that smile was on his face no one dared address him; all they could do was to stand ready to obey. 
Audio: While that smile was on his face, no one dared address him. All they could do was stand ready to obey.

#:~:text=the%20order%20,.%20
Text:  The order came sharp and incisive.
Audio: The order came sharp and incisive.

#:~:text='div
Text:  'Dive!
Audio: 

#:~:text=ve!-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=there%20was%20a%20g,.%20
Text:  There was a gleam of legs, and instantly the lagoon seemed deserted. 
Audio: There was a gleam of legs, and instantly the lagoon seemed deserted.

#:~:text=marooners'%20rock%20s,.%20
Text:  Marooners' Rock stood alone in the forbidding waters, as if it were itself marooned.
Audio: Marooner's Rock stood alone in the forbidding waters, as if it were itself marooned.

#:~:text=the%20boat%20d,.%20
Text:  The boat drew nearer. 
Audio: The boat drew nearer.

#:~:text=it%20was%20the%20p,.%20
Text:  It was the pirate dinghy, with three figures in her, Smee and Starkey, and the third a captive, no other than Tiger Lily. 
Audio: It was the pirate dinghy, with three figures in her, Smee and Starkey, and the third a captive, no other than Tiger Lily.

#:~:text=her%20hands,.%20
Text:  Her hands and ankles were tied, and she knew what was to be her fate. 
Audio: Her hands and ankles were tied, and she knew what was to be her fate.

#:~:text=she%20was%20to%20,%3F%20
Text:  She was to be left on the rock to perish, an end to one of her race more terrible than death by fire or torture, for is it not written in the book of the tribe that there is no path through water to the happy hunting-ground? 
Audio: She was to be left on the rock to perish, an end to one of her race more terrible than death by fire or torture, for is it not written in the book of the tribe that there is no path through water to the happy hunting ground?

#:~:text=yet%20her,.%20
Text:  Yet her face was impassive; she was the daughter of a chief, she must die as a chief's daughter, it is enough.
Audio: Yet her face was impassive. She was the daughter of a chief. She must die as a chief's daughter. It is enough.

#:~:text=they%20had%20c,.%20
Text:  They had caught her boarding the pirate ship with a knife in her mouth. 
Audio: They had caught her boarding the pirate ship with a knife in her mouth.

#:~:text=no%20wat,.%20
Text:  No watch was kept on the ship, it being Hook's boast that the wind of his name guarded the ship for a mile around. 
Audio: No watch was kept on the ship, it being Hook's boast that the wind of his name guarded the ship for a mile around.

#:~:text=now%20her,.%20
Text:  Now her fate would help to guard it also. 
Audio: Now her fate would help to guard it also.

#:~:text=one%20more%20w,.%20
Text:  One more wail would go the round in that wind by night.
Audio: One more whale would go round in that wind by night.

#:~:text=in%20the%20gl,.%20
Text:  In the gloom that they brought with them the two pirates did not see the rock till they crashed into it.
Audio: In the gloom that they brought with them, the two pirates did not see the rock till they crashed into it.

#:~:text='lu,.%20
Text:  'Luff, you lubber,' cried an Irish voice that was Smee's; 'here's the rock. 
Audio: Lough, you lubber, cried an Irish voice that was Smee's. Here's the rock.

#:~:text=now%2C%20then,.
Text:  Now, then, what we have to do is to hoist the redskin on to it and leave her there to drown.
Audio: 

#:~:text=wn.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: then, what we have to do is hoist the red skin onto it and leave her here to drown.

#:~:text=it%20was%20the%20w,.%20
Text:  It was the work of one brutal moment to land the beautiful girl on the rock; she was too proud to offer a vain resistance.
Audio: It was the work of one brutal moment to land the beautiful girl on the rock. She was too proud to offer a vain resistance.

#:~:text=quite%20n,.%20
Text:  Quite near the rock, but out of sight, two heads were bobbing up and down, Peter's and Wendy's. 
Audio: Quite near the rock, but out of sight. Two heads were bobbing up and down, Peter's and Wendy's.

#:~:text=wendy%20was%20c,.%20
Text:  Wendy was crying, for it was the first tragedy she had seen. 
Audio: Wendy was crying, for it was the first tragedy she had seen.

#:~:text=peter%20had%20se,.%20
Text:  Peter had seen many tragedies, but he had forgotten them all. 
Audio: Peter had seen many tragedies, but he had forgotten them all.

#:~:text=he%20was%20l,.%20
Text:  He was less sorry than Wendy for Tiger Lily: it was two against one that angered him, and he meant to save her. 
Audio: He was less sorry than Wendy for Tiger Lily. It was two against one that angered him, and he meant to save her. An

#:~:text=an%20ea,.%20
Text:  An easy way would have been to wait until the pirates had gone, but he was never one to choose the easy way.
Audio: An easy way would have been to wait until the pirates had gone, but he was never one to choose the easy way.

#:~:text=there%20was%20al,.%20
Text:  There was almost nothing he could not do, and he now imitated the voice of Hook.
Audio: There was almost nothing he could not do. He now imitated the voice of Hook.

#:~:text='aho,.%20
Text:  'Ahoy there, you lubbers,' he called. 
Audio: Ahoy there, you lovers, he called.

#:~:text=it%20was%20a%20m,.%20
Text:  It was a marvellous imitation.
Audio: It was a marvelous imitation.

#:~:text='the%20ca,.%20
Text:  'The captain,' said the pirates, staring at each other in surprise.
Audio: The captain, said the pirates, staring at each other in surprise.

#:~:text='he%20m,.%20
Text:  'He must be swimming out to us,' Starkey said, when they had looked for him in vain.
Audio: He must be swimming out to us, Starkey said when they had looked for him in vain.

#:~:text='we%20are%20p,.%20
Text:  'We are putting the redskin on the rock,' Smee called out.
Audio: We are putting the red skin on the rock, Smee called out.

#:~:text='set,.%20
Text:  'Set her free,' came the astonishing answer.
Audio: Set her free, came the astonishing answer.

#:~:text='fr,!
Text:  'Free!
Audio: Free?

#:~:text=ee!-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='yes%2C%20c,.
Text:  'Yes, cut her bonds and let her go.
Audio: Yes, cut her bonds and let her go.

#:~:text=%20go.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='but%2C%20c,%20
Text:  'But, captain——'
Audio: But captain!

#:~:text='at%20once%2C%20,.
Text:  'At once, d'ye hear,' cried Peter, 'or I'll plunge my hook in you.
Audio: At once, do you hear? cried Peter, or I'll plunge my hook into you.

#:~:text=ou.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='this,.%20
Text:  'This is queer,' Smee gasped.
Audio: This is queer, Smee gasped.

#:~:text='better%20d,.%20
Text:  'Better do what the captain orders,' said Starkey nervously.
Audio: Better do what the captain orders, said Starkey nervously.

#:~:text='ay%2C%20ay%2C'%20s,.%20
Text:  'Ay, ay,' Smee said, and he cut Tiger Lily's cords. 
Audio: Aye, aye, Smee said, and he cut Tiger Lily's cords.

#:~:text=at%20once%20l,.%20
Text:  At once like an eel she slid between Starkey's legs into the water.
Audio: At once, like an eel, she slid between Starkey's legs into the water.

#:~:text=of%20course%20we,.%20
Text:  Of course Wendy was very elated over Peter's cleverness; but she knew that he would be elated also and very likely crow and thus betray himself, so at once her hand went out to cover his mouth. 
Audio: Of course, Wendy was very elated over Peter's cleverness, but she knew that he would be elated also, and very likely crow and thus betray himself, so at once her hand went out to cover his mouth.

#:~:text=but%20it%20was%20s,!
Text:  But it was stayed even in the act, for 'Boat ahoy!
Audio: But it was stayed even in the act, for, Boat ahoy,

#:~:text='%20ra,.%20
Text:  ' rang over the lagoon in Hook's voice, and this time it was not Peter who had spoken.
Audio: rang over the lagoon in Hook's voice, and this time it was not Peter who had spoken.

#:~:text=peter%20ma,.%20
Text:  Peter may have been about to crow, but his face puckered in a whistle of surprise instead.
