#:~:text=ibs%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: you glad, Nibs?

#:~:text='ra,.
Text:  'Rather.
Audio: Rather—

#:~:text=her.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='are%20you%20glad%2C%20t,%3F
Text:  'Are you glad, Twins?
Audio: 

#:~:text=ins%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: you glad, twins?

#:~:text='we%20are%20j,.
Text:  'We are just glad.
Audio: 

#:~:text=ad.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: are glad.

#:~:text='oh%20dear%2C',.%20
Text:  'Oh dear,' sighed Wendy.
Audio: Oh, dear, sighed Wendy.

#:~:text='lit,.%20
Text:  'Little less noise there,' Peter called out, determined that she should have fair play, however beastly a story it might be in his opinion.
Audio: Little less noise there, Peter called out, determined that she should have fair play, however beastly a story it might be, in his opinion.

#:~:text='the%20ge,g.
Text:  'The gentleman's name,' Wendy continued, 'was Mr. Darling, and her name was Mrs. Darling.
Audio: 

#:~:text=ng.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: gentleman's name, Wendy continued, was Mr. Darling, and her name was Mrs. Darling.

#:~:text='i%20k,.%20
Text:  'I knew them,' John said, to annoy the others.
Audio: I knew them, John said, to annoy the others.

#:~:text='i%20thi,.%20
Text:  'I think I knew them,' said Michael rather doubtfully.
Audio: I think I knew them, said Michael, rather doubtfully.

#:~:text='they%20we,%3F
Text:  'They were married, you know,' explained Wendy, 'and what do you think they had?
Audio: They were married, you know, explained Wendy. And what do you think they had?

#:~:text=ad%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
