#:~:text=in%20the%20meantime%20t,.%20
Text:  In the meantime the boys were gazing very forlornly at Wendy, now equipped with John and Michael for the journey. 
Audio: In the meantime, the boys were gazing very forlornly at Wendy, now equipped with John and Michael for the journey.

#:~:text=by%20this%20time%20they%20were%20d,.%20
Text:  By this time they were dejected, not merely because they were about to lose her, but also because they felt that she was going off to something nice to which they had not been invited. 
Audio: By this time, they were dejected, not merely because they were about to lose her, but also because they felt that she was going off to something nice, to which they had not been invited.

#:~:text=novelty%20w,.%20
Text:  Novelty was beckoning to them as usual.
Audio: Novelty was beckoning to them as usual.

#:~:text=credit,.%20
Text:  Crediting them with a nobler feeling Wendy melted.
Audio: Crediting them with a nobler feeling, Wendy melted.

#:~:text='dear%20o,.
Text:  'Dear ones,' she said, 'if you will all come with me I feel almost sure I can get my father and mother to adopt you.
Audio: Dear ones, she said, if you will all come with me, I feel almost sure I can get my father and mother to adopt you.

#:~:text=ou.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=the%20inv,.%20
Text:  The invitation was meant specially for Peter; but each of the boys was thinking exclusively of himself, and at once they jumped with joy.
Audio: The invitation was meant specially for Peter, but each of the boys was thinking exclusively of himself, and at once they jumped with joy.

#:~:text='but%20wo,%3F
Text:  'But won't they think us rather a handful?
Audio: But won't they think us rather a handful?

#:~:text='%20nibs%20a,.%20
Text:  ' Nibs asked in the middle of his jump.
Audio: Nibs asked, in the middle of his jump.

#:~:text='oh%20no%2C,.
Text:  'Oh no,' said Wendy, rapidly thinking it out, 'it will only mean having a few beds in the drawing-room; they can be hidden behind screens on first Thursdays.
Audio: Oh no, said Wendy, rapidly thinking it out. It will only mean having a few beds in the drawing-room. They can be hidden behind the screens on first Thursdays.

#:~:text=ays.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='peter%2C%20c,%3F
Text:  'Peter, can we go?
Audio: Peter, can we go?

#:~:text='%20they%20all%20cried%20,%20
Text:  ' they all cried imploringly. 
Audio: they all cried imploringly.

#:~:text=they%20too,.%20
Text:  They took it for granted that if they went he would go also, but really they scarcely cared. 
Audio: They took it for granted that if they went, he would go also. But really they scarcely cared.

#:~:text=thus%20c,.%20
Text:  Thus children are ever ready, when novelty knocks, to desert their dearest ones.
Audio: Thus children are ever ready, when novelty knocks, to desert their dearest ones.

#:~:text='all%20r,.%20
Text:  'All right,' Peter replied with a bitter smile; and immediately they rushed to get their things.
Audio: All right, Peter replied with a bitter smile, and immediately they rushed to get their things.

#:~:text='and%20now%2C,.
Text:  'And now, Peter,' Wendy said, thinking she had put everything right, 'I am going to give you your medicine before you go.
Audio: And now, Peter, Wendy said, thinking she had put everything right, I am going to give you your medicine before you go.

#:~:text='%20she%20l,.%20
Text:  ' She loved to give them medicine, and undoubtedly gave them too much. 
Audio: She loved to give them medicine, and undoubtedly gave them too much.

#:~:text=of%20course%20it%20was%20o,.%20
Text:  Of course it was only water, but it was out of a calabash, and she always shook the calabash and counted the drops, which gave it a certain medicinal quality. 
Audio: Of course it was only water, but it was out of a bottle, and she always shook the bottle and counted the drops, which gave it a certain medicinal quality.

#:~:text=on%20this%20occasion%2C,.%20
Text:  On this occasion, however, she did not give Peter his draught, for just as she had prepared it, she saw a look on his face that made her heart sink.
Audio: On this occasion, however, she did not give Peter his draught. For, just as she had prepared it, she saw a look on his face that made her heart sink.

#:~:text='ge,.%20
Text:  'Get your things, Peter,' she cried, shaking.
Audio: Get your things, Peter, she cried, shaking.

#:~:text='no%2C'%20h,.
Text:  'No,' he answered, pretending indifference, 'I am not going with you, Wendy.
Audio: No, he answered, pretending indifference. I am not going with you, Wendy.

#:~:text=ndy.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='yes%2C%20p,.
Text:  'Yes, Peter.
Audio: Yes, Peter.

#:~:text=ter.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='%20-,'no.
Text:  'No.
Audio: Peter, no.

#:~:text='no.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=to%20show%20t,.%20
Text:  To show that her departure would leave him unmoved, he skipped up and down the room, playing gaily on his heartless pipes. 
Audio: To show that her departure would leave him unmoved, he skipped up and down the room, playing gaily, on his heartless pipes.

#:~:text=she%20had%20to%20r,.%20
Text:  She had to run about after him, though it was rather undignified.
Audio: She had to run about after him, though it was rather undignified.

#:~:text='to%20f,.%20
Text:  'To find your mother,' she coaxed.
Audio: To find your mother, she coaxed.

#:~:text=now%2C%20i,.%20
Text:  Now, if Peter had ever quite had a mother, he no longer missed her. 
Audio: Now, if Peter had ever quite had a mother, he no longer missed her.

#:~:text=he%20could%20do%20v,.%20
Text:  He could do very well without one. 
Audio: He could do very well without one.

#:~:text=he%20had%20th,.%20
Text:  He had thought them out, and remembered only their bad points.
Audio: He had thought them out, and remembered only their bad points.

#:~:text='no%2C%20n,.
Text:  'No, no,' he told Wendy decisively; 'perhaps she would say I was old, and I just want always to be a little boy and to have fun.
Audio: No, no, he told Wendy, decisively. Perhaps she would say I was old, and I just want always to be a little boy, and to have fun.

#:~:text=un.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='but%2C%20p,%20
Text:  'But, Peter——'
Audio: But Peter?

#:~:text=%E2%80%94'%20-,'no.
Text:  'No.
Audio: No.

#:~:text='no.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=and%20so%20t,.%20
Text:  And so the others had to be told.
Audio: And so the others had to be told.

#:~:text='peter%20i,.
Text:  'Peter isn't coming.
Audio: Peter isn't coming.

#:~:text=ming.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=peter%20n,!%20
Text:  Peter not coming! 
Audio: Peter not coming.

#:~:text=they%20gaz,.%20
Text:  They gazed blankly at him, their sticks over their backs, and on each stick a bundle. 
Audio: They gazed blankly at him. There's sticks over their backs, and on each stick a bundle.

#:~:text=their%20fir,.%20
Text:  Their first thought was that if Peter was not going he had probably changed his mind about letting them go.
Audio: Their first thought was that if Peter was not going, he had probably changed his mind about letting them go.

#:~:text=but%20he%20was%20f,.%20
Text:  But he was far too proud for that. 
Audio: But he was far too proud for that.

#:~:text='if%20you%20f,.
Text:  'If you find your mothers,' he said darkly, 'I hope you will like them.
Audio: If you find your mothers, he said darkly, I hope you will like them.

#:~:text=hem.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=the%20aw,.%20
Text:  The awful cynicism of this made an uncomfortable impression, and most of them began to look rather doubtful. 
Audio: The awful cynicism of this made an uncomfortable impression, and most of them began to look rather doubtful.

#:~:text=after%20all%2C%20the,%3F%20
Text:  After all, their faces said, were they not noodles to want to go?
Audio: After all, their faces said, were they not noodles to want to go?

#:~:text='now%20then%2C',.%20
Text:  'Now then,' cried Peter, 'no fuss, no blubbering; good-bye, Wendy'; and he held out his hand cheerily, quite as if they must really go now, for he had something important to do.
Audio: Now then, cried Peter. No fuss. No blubbering. Goodbye, Wendy. And he held out his hand cheeringly, quite as if they must really go now, for he had something important to do.

#:~:text=she%20had%20to%20t,.%20
Text:  She had to take his hand, as there was no indication that he would prefer a thimble.
Audio: She had to take his hand. And there was no indication that he would prefer a thimble.

#:~:text='you%20will%20r,%3F
Text:  'You will remember about changing your flannels, Peter?
Audio: You will remember about changing your flannels, Peter,

#:~:text='%20she%20said%2C%20l,.%20
Text:  ' she said, lingering over him. 
Audio: she said, lingering over him.

#:~:text=she%20was%20al,.%20
Text:  She was always so particular about their flannels.
Audio: She was always so particular about their flannels.

#:~:text=.%20-,'yes.
Text:  'Yes.
Audio: Yes.

#:~:text=yes.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='and%20you%20w,%3F
Text:  'And you will take your medicine?
Audio: And you will take your medicine.

#:~:text=ine%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='%20-,'yes.
Text:  'Yes.
Audio: Yes.

#:~:text=yes.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=that%20see,.%20
Text:  That seemed to be everything; and an awkward pause followed. 
Audio: That seemed to be everything, and an awkward pause followed.

#:~:text=peter%2C%20ho,.%20
Text:  Peter, however, was not the kind that breaks down before people. 
Audio: Peter, however, was not the kind that breaks down before other people.

#:~:text='are%20you%20ready%2C%20t,%3F
Text:  'Are you ready, Tinker Bell?
Audio: Are you ready, Tinkerbell?

#:~:text='%20he%20called%20o,%20
Text:  ' he called out.
Audio: He called out.

#:~:text=.%20-,'ay%2C%20ay.
Text:  'Ay, ay.
Audio: Aye,

#:~:text=%2C%20ay.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='then%20le,.
Text:  'Then lead the way.
Audio: Then lead the way.

#:~:text=way.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=tink%20da,.%20
Text:  Tink darted up the nearest tree; but no one followed her, for it was at this moment that the pirates made their dreadful attack upon the redskins. 
Audio: Tink darted up the nearest tree, but no one followed her, for it was at this moment that the pirates made their dreadful attack upon the Redskins.

#:~:text=above%2C%20whe,.%20
Text:  Above, where all had been so still, the air was rent with shrieks and the clash of steel. 
Audio: Above, where all had been so still, the air was rent with shrieks and the clash of steel.

#:~:text=below%2C%20ther,.%20
Text:  Below, there was dead silence. 
Audio: Below there was dead silence.

#:~:text=mouths%20op,.%20
Text:  Mouths opened and remained open. 
Audio: Mouths opened and remained open.

#:~:text=wendy%20fe,.%20
Text:  Wendy fell on her knees, but her arms were extended toward Peter. 
Audio: Wendy fell on her knees, but her arms were extended toward Peter.

#:~:text=all%20ar,.%20
Text:  All arms were extended to him, as if suddenly blown in his direction; they were beseeching him mutely not to desert them. 
Audio: All arms were extended to him, as if suddenly blown in his direction. They were beseeching him mutely not to desert them.

#:~:text=as%20for%20p,.%20
Text:  As for Peter, he seized his sword, the same he thought he had slain Barbecue with; and the lust of battle was in his eye.
Audio: As for Peter, he seized his sword, the same he thought he had slain barbecue with, and the lust of battle was in his eye.

#:~:text=chapter%20xii%20
Text:  CHAPTER XII
Audio: End of chapter 11

#:~:text=the%20children%20ar,f%20
Text:  THE CHILDREN ARE CARRIED OFF
Audio: This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain. For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org. Recording by Genevieve Toks, April 8, 2007, New Haven, Connecticut. Peter Pan by J. M. Berry. Chapter 12. The Children Are Carried Off.

#:~:text=the%20pirate%20at,.%20
Text:  The pirate attack had been a complete surprise: a sure proof that the unscrupulous Hook had conducted it improperly, for to surprise redskins fairly is beyond the wit of the white man.
Audio: The pirate attack had been a complete surprise, a sure proof that the unscrupulous hook had conducted it improperly, for to surprise redskins fairly is beyond the wit of the white man.

#:~:text=by%20al,.%20
Text:  By all the unwritten laws of savage warfare it is always the redskin who attacks, and with the wiliness of his race he does it just before the dawn, at which time he knows the courage of the whites to be at its lowest ebb. 
Audio: By all the unwritten laws of savage warfare, it is always the redskin who attacks, and with the wiliness of his race, he does it just before the dawn, at which time he knows the courage of the whites to be at its lowest ebb.

#:~:text=the%20white%20me,.%20
Text:  The white men have in the meantime made a rude stockade on the summit of yonder undulating ground, at the foot of which a stream runs; for it is destruction to be too far from water. 
Audio: The white men have in the meantime made a rude stockade on the summit of yonder undulating ground, at the foot of which a stream runs, for it is destruction to be too far from water.

#:~:text=there%20th,.%20
Text:  There they await the onslaught, the inexperienced ones clutching their revolvers and treading on twigs, but the old hands sleeping tranquilly until just before the dawn. 
Audio: There they await the onslaught, the inexperienced ones clutching their revolvers and treading on twigs, with the old hands sleeping tranquilly until the dawn.

#:~:text=through%20the%20l,.%20
Text:  Through the long black night the savage scouts wriggle, snake-like, among the grass without stirring a blade. 
Audio: Through the long black night, the savage scouts wriggle, snake-like, among the grass, without stirring a blade.

#:~:text=the%20brushw,.%20
Text:  The brushwood closes behind them as silently as sand into which a mole has dived. 
Audio: The brushwood closes behind them, as silently as sand into which a mole has dived.

#:~:text=not%20a%20sound%20i,.%20
Text:  Not a sound is to be heard, save when they give vent to a wonderful imitation of the lonely call of the coyote. 
Audio: Not a sound is to be heard, save when they give vent to a wonderful imitation of the lonely call of the coyote. The

#:~:text=the%20cry%20i,.%20
Text:  The cry is answered by other braves; and some of them do it even better than the coyotes, who are not very good at it. 
Audio: The cry is answered by other braves, and some of them do it even better than the coyotes, who are not very good at it.

#:~:text=so%20the%20c,.%20
Text:  So the chill hours wear on, and the long suspense is horribly trying to the paleface who has to live through it for the first time; but to the trained hand those ghastly calls and still ghastlier silences are but an intimation of how the night is marching.
Audio: So the chill hours wear on, and a long suspense is horribly trying, to the pale face who has to live through it for the first time. But to the trained hand, those ghastly calls, and still ghastlier silences, are but an intimation of how the night is marching.

#:~:text=that%20this%20was%20th,.%20
Text:  That this was the usual procedure was so well known to Hook that in disregarding it he cannot be excused on the plea of ignorance.
Audio: That this was the usual procedure, was so well known to Hook, that in disregarding it, he cannot be excused on the plea of ignorance.

#:~:text=the%20piccaninni,.%20
Text:  The Piccaninnies, on their part, trusted implicitly to his honour, and their whole action of the night stands out in marked contrast to his. 
Audio: The Piccaninnies, on their part, trusted implicitly to his honor, and their whole election of the night stands out in marked contrast to his.

#:~:text=they%20le,.%20
Text:  They left nothing undone that was consistent with the reputation of their tribe. 
Audio: They left nothing undone that was consistent with the reputation of their tribe.

#:~:text=with%20that%20a,.%20
Text:  With that alertness of the senses which is at once the marvel and despair of civilised peoples, they knew that the pirates were on the island from the moment one of them trod on a dry stick; and in an incredibly short space of time the coyote cries began. 
Audio: With that alertness of the senses, which is at once the marvel and despair of civilized peoples, they knew that the pirates were on the island from the moment one of them trod on a dry stick. And in an incredibly short space of time, the coyote cries began.

#:~:text=every%20f,.%20
Text:  Every foot of ground between the spot where Hook had landed his forces and the home under the trees was stealthily examined by braves wearing their mocassins with the heels in front. 
Audio: Every foot of ground between the spot where Hook had landed his forces and the home under the trees, was stealthily examined by braves wearing their moccasins with the heels in front.

#:~:text=they%20found%20o,.%20
Text:  They found only one hillock with a stream at its base, so that Hook had no choice; here he must establish himself and wait for just before the dawn. 
Audio: They found only one hillock with a stream at its base, so that Hook had no choice. Here he must establish himself and wait for just before the dawn.

#:~:text=everything%20b,.%20
Text:  Everything being thus mapped out with almost diabolical cunning, the main body of the redskins folded their blankets around them, and in the phlegmatic manner that is to them the pearl of manhood squatted above the children's home, awaiting the cold moment when they should deal pale death.
Audio: Everything being thus mapped out, with almost diabolical cunning, the main body of the redskins folded their blankets around them, and in the phlegmatic manner that is to them, the pearl of manhood squatted above the children's home, awaiting a cold moment when they should deal pale death.

#:~:text=here%20d,.%20
Text:  Here dreaming, though wide-awake, of the exquisite tortures to which they were to put him at break of day, those confiding savages were found by the treacherous Hook. 
Audio: Here, dreaming though wide awake of the exquisite tortures to which they were to put him at break of day, those confiding savages were found by the treacherous Hook.

#:~:text=from%20the%20a,.%20
Text:  From the accounts afterwards supplied by such of the scouts as escaped the carnage, he does not seem even to have paused at the rising ground, though it is certain that in that grey light he must have seen it: no thought of waiting to be attacked appears from first to last to have visited his subtle mind; he would not even hold off till the night was nearly spent; on he pounded with no policy but to fall to. 
Audio: From the accounts afterward supplied by such of the scouts as escaped the carnage, he does not seem even to have paused at the rising ground, though it is certain that in the gray light he must have seen it. No thought of waiting to be attacked appears from first to last to have visited his humble mind. He would not even hold off till the night was nearly spent. On he pounded, with no policy but to fall to.

#:~:text=what%20cou,.%20
Text:  What could the bewildered scouts do, masters as they were of every warlike artifice save this one, but trot helplessly after him, exposing themselves fatally to view, the while they gave pathetic utterance to the coyote cry.
Audio: What could the bewildered scouts do? Masters are they rare of every warlike artifice save this one, but trot helplessly after him, exposing themselves fatally to view, while they gave pathetic utterance to the coyote cry.

#:~:text=around%20the%20,.%20
Text:  Around the brave Tiger Lily were a dozen of her stoutest warriors, and they suddenly saw the perfidious pirates bearing down upon them. 
Audio: Around the brave tiger lily were a dozen of her stoutest warriors, and they suddenly saw the perfidious pirates bearing down upon them.

#:~:text=fell%20fr,.%20
Text:  Fell from their eyes then the film through which they had looked at victory. 
Audio: Fell from their eyes, then, the film through which they had looked at victory.

#:~:text=no%20more%20w,.%20
Text:  No more would they torture at the stake. 
Audio: No more would they torture at the stake.

#:~:text=for%20them%20th,.%20
Text:  For them the happy hunting-grounds now. 
Audio: For them the happy hunting guns was now.

#:~:text=they%20knew%20it,.%20
Text:  They knew it; but as their fathers' sons they acquitted themselves. 
Audio: They knew it, but as their father's sons they acquitted themselves.

#:~:text=even%20then,.%20
Text:  Even then they had time to gather in a phalanx that would have been hard to break had they risen quickly, but this they were forbidden to do by the traditions of their race. 
Audio: Even then they had time to gather in a phalanx that would have been far to break had they risen quickly, but this they were forbidden to do by the traditions of their race.

#:~:text=it%20is%20w,.%20
Text:  It is written that the noble savage must never express surprise in the presence of the white. 
Audio: It is written that the noble savage must never express surprise in the presence of the white.

#:~:text=thus%20te,.%20
Text:  Thus terrible as the sudden appearance of the pirates must have been to them, they remained stationary for a moment, not a muscle moving; as if the foe had come by invitation. 
Audio: Thus, terrible as the sudden appearance of the pirates must have been to them, they remained stationary for a moment, not a muscle moving, as if the foe had come by invitation.

#:~:text=then%2C%20i,.%20
Text:  Then, indeed, the tradition gallantly upheld, they seized their weapons, and the air was torn with the warcry; but it was now too late.
Audio: Then, indeed, the tradition gallantly upheld, they seized their weapons, and the air was torn with the war cry. But it was now too late.

#:~:text=it%20is%20no%20,.%20
Text:  It is no part of ours to describe what was a massacre rather than a fight. 
Audio: It is no part of ours to describe what was a massacre rather than a fight.

#:~:text=thus%20p,.%20
Text:  Thus perished many of the flower of the Piccaninny tribe. 
Audio: Thus perished many of the flower of the Pickaninny tribe.

#:~:text=not%20all%20u,.%20
Text:  Not all unavenged did they die, for with Lean Wolf fell Alf Mason, to disturb the Spanish Main no more; and among others who bit the dust were Geo. 
Audio: Not all unavenged did they die, for with lean wolf fell Alf Mason, to disturb the Spanish man no more, and among others who bit the dust were George

#:~:text=scourie,.%20
Text:  Scourie, Chas. 
Audio: Scorrey, Charles

#:~:text=turley%2C,.%20
Text:  Turley, and the Alsatian Foggerty. 
Audio: Turley, and the Alsatian Fogarty.

#:~:text=turley%20,.%20
Text:  Turley fell to the tomahawk of the terrible Panther, who ultimately cut a way through the pirates with Tiger Lily and a small remnant of the tribe.
Audio: Turley fell to the tomahawk of the terrible panther, who ultimately cut away through the pirates with tiger lily and a small remnant of the tribe.

#:~:text=to%20what%20e,.%20
Text:  To what extent Hook is to blame for his tactics on this occasion is for the historian to decide. 
Audio: To what extent Hook is to blame for his tactics on this occasion, it's for the historian to decide.

#:~:text=had%20he%20w,.%20
Text:  Had he waited on the rising ground till the proper hour he and his men would probably have been butchered; and in judging him it is only fair to take this into account. 
Audio: Had he waited on the rising ground to the proper hour, he and his men would probably have been butchered, and in judging him, it is only fair to take this into account.

#:~:text=what%20he%20s,.%20
Text:  What he should perhaps have done was to acquaint his opponents that he proposed to follow a new method. 
Audio: What he should perhaps have done was to acquaint his opponents that he proposed to follow a new method. On

#:~:text=on%20the%20other%20hand%20,.%20
Text:  On the other hand this, as destroying the element of surprise, would have made his strategy of no avail, so that the whole question is beset with difficulties. 
Audio: On either hand, this, as destroying the element of surprise, would have made his strategy of no avail, so that the whole question is beset with difficulties.

#:~:text=one%20cannot%20a,.%20
Text:  One cannot at least withhold a reluctant admiration for the wit that had conceived so bold a scheme, and the fell genius with which it was carried out.
Audio: One cannot at least withhold a reluctant admiration for the wit that he conceived so bold a scheme, and the fell genius with which it was carried out.

#:~:text=what%20wer,%3F%20
Text:  What were his own feelings about himself at that triumphant moment? 
Audio: What were his own feelings about himself at that triumphant moment?

#:~:text=fain%20,.%20
Text:  Fain would his dogs have known, as breathing heavily and wiping their cutlasses, they gathered at a discreet distance from his hook, and squinted through their ferret eyes at this extraordinary man. 
Audio: Fain what his dogs have known, as breathing heavily and wiping their cutlasses, they gathered at a discreet distance from his hook, and squinted through their ferret eyes at this extraordinary man.

#:~:text=elation%20m,.%20
Text:  Elation must have been in his heart, but his face did not reflect it: ever a dark and solitary enigma, he stood aloof from his followers in spirit as in substance.
Audio: Elation must have been in his heart, but his face did not reflect it. Ever a dark and solitary enigma, he stood aloof from his followers, in spirit as in substance.

#:~:text=the%20night',.%20
Text:  The night's work was not yet over, for it was not the redskins he had come out to destroy; they were but the bees to be smoked, so that he should get at the honey. 
Audio: The night's work was not yet over, for it was not the redskins he had come out to destroy. They were but the bees to be smoked, so that he should get at the honey.

#:~:text=it%20was%20pan,.%20
Text:  It was Pan he wanted, Pan and Wendy and their band, but chiefly Pan.
Audio: It was Pan he wanted, Pan and Wendy, in their band, but chiefly Pan.

#:~:text=peter%20was%20s,.%20
Text:  Peter was such a small boy that one tends to wonder at the man's hatred of him. 
Audio: Peter was such a small boy that one tends to wonder at the man's hatred of him.

#:~:text=true%20h,.%20
Text:  True he had flung Hook's arm to the crocodile; but even this and the increased insecurity of life to which it led, owing to the crocodile's pertinacity, hardly account for a vindictiveness so relentless and malignant. 
Audio: True, he had flung Hook's arm to the crocodile, but even this and the increased insecurity of life to which it led, owing to the crocodile's pertinacity, hardly account for a vindictiveness so relentless and malignant. The

#:~:text=the%20truth%20i,.%20
Text:  The truth is that there was a something about Peter which goaded the pirate captain to frenzy. 
Audio: The truth is that there was something about Peter which goaded the pirate captain to frenzy.

#:~:text=it%20was%20not%20his%20c,.%20
Text:  It was not his courage, it was not his engaging appearance, it was not—. 
Audio: It was not his courage. It was not his engaging appearance. It was not—there

#:~:text=there%20is%20no%20b,.%20
Text:  There is no beating about the bush, for we know quite well what it was, and have got to tell. 
Audio: was no beating about the bush, for we know quite well what it was and had got to tell.

#:~:text=it%20was%20peter',.%20
Text:  It was Peter's cockiness.
Audio: It was Peter's cockiness.

#:~:text=this%20had,.%20
Text:  This had got on Hook's nerves; it made his iron claw twitch, and at night it disturbed him like an insect. 
Audio: This had got on Hook's nerves. It made his iron claw twitch, and at night it disturbed him like an insect.

#:~:text=while%20p,.%20
Text:  While Peter lived, the tortured man felt that he was a lion in a cage into which a sparrow had come.
Audio: While Peter lived, the tortured man felt that he was a lion in a cage into which a sparrow had come.

#:~:text=the%20question%20n,%3F%20
Text:  The question now was how to get down the trees, or how to get his dogs down? 
Audio: The question now was how to get down the trees, or how to get his dogs down.

#:~:text=he%20ran,.%20
Text:  He ran his greedy eyes over them, searching for the thinnest ones. 
Audio: He ran his greedy eyes over them, searching for the thinnest ones.

#:~:text=they%20wr,.%20
Text:  They wriggled uncomfortably, for they knew he would not scruple to ram them down with poles.
Audio: They riddled uncomfortably, for they knew he would not scruple to ram them down with poles.

#:~:text=in%20the%20meantime%2C,%3F%20
Text:  In the meantime, what of the boys? 
Audio: In the meantime, what of the boys?

#:~:text=we%20have%20s,.%20
Text:  We have seen them at the first clang of weapons, turned as it were into stone figures, open-mouthed, all appealing with outstretched arms to Peter; and we return to them as their mouths close, and their arms fall to their sides. 
Audio: We have seen them at the first clang of the weapons, turned as it were into stone figures, open-mouthed, all appealing with outstretched arms to Peter, and we return to them as their mouths close and their arms fall to their sides.

#:~:text=the%20pan,.%20
Text:  The pandemonium above has ceased almost as suddenly as it arose, passed like a fierce gust of wind; but they know that in the passing it has determined their fate.
Audio: The pandemonium above has ceased almost as suddenly as it arose, passed like a fierce gust of wind, but they know that in the passing it has determined their fate.

#:~:text=which%20si,%3F%20
Text:  Which side had won?
Audio: Which side had won?

#:~:text=the%20pirates%2C%20l,.%20
Text:  The pirates, listening avidly at the mouths of the trees, heard the question put by every boy, and alas, they also heard Peter's answer.
Audio: The pirates, listening avidly at the mouths of the trees, heard the question put by every boy, and alas, they also heard Peter's answer.

#:~:text='if%20t,.
Text:  'If the redskins have won,' he said, 'they will beat the tom-tom; it is always their sign of victory.
Audio: 

#:~:text=ry.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: the Redskins have won, he said, they'll beat the Tom-Tom. It is always their sign of victory.

#:~:text=now%20sm,.%20
Text:  Now Smee had found the tom-tom, and was at that moment sitting on it. 
Audio: Now Smee had found the Tom-Tom, and was at that moment sitting on it.

#:~:text='you%20will%20n,.%20
Text:  'You will never hear the tom-tom again,' he muttered, but inaudibly of course, for strict silence had been enjoined. 
Audio: You will never hear the Tom-Tom again, he muttered, but inaudibly, of course, for strict silence had been enjoined.

#:~:text=to%20his%20a,.%20
Text:  To his amazement Hook signed to him to beat the tom-tom; and slowly there came to Smee an understanding of the dreadful wickedness of the order. 
Audio: To his amazement, Hook signed him to beat the Tom-Tom. And slowly there came to Smee an understanding of the dreadful wickedness of the order.

#:~:text=never%2C,.%20
Text:  Never, probably, had this simple man admired Hook so much.
Audio: Never, probably, had this simple man admired Hook so much.

#:~:text=twice%20s,.%20
Text:  Twice Smee beat upon the instrument, and then stopped to listen gleefully.
Audio: Twice Smee beat upon the instrument, and then stopped to listen gleefully.

#:~:text='the%20to,!
Text:  'The tom-tom,' the miscreants heard Peter cry; 'an Indian victory!
Audio: The Tom-Tom, Miss Grants heard Peter cry. An Indian victory!

#:~:text=ry!-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: An Indian victory!

#:~:text=the%20doom,.%20
Text:  The doomed children answered with a cheer that was music to the black hearts above, and almost immediately they repeated their goodbyes to Peter. 
Audio: The doomed children answered with a cheer that was music to the black hearts above, and almost immediately they repeated their goodbyes to Peter.

#:~:text=this%20pu,.%20
Text:  This puzzled the pirates, but all their other feelings were swallowed by a base delight that the enemy were about to come up the trees. 
Audio: This puzzled the pirates, but all their other feelings were swallowed by a base delight that the enemy were about to come up the trees.

#:~:text=they%20sm,.%20
Text:  They smirked at each other and rubbed their hands. 
Audio: They smirked at each other and rubbed their hands.

#:~:text=rapidly%20a,.%20
Text:  Rapidly and silently Hook gave his orders: one man to each tree, and the others to arrange themselves in a line two yards apart.
Audio: Rapidly and silently, Hook gave his orders, one man to each tree, and the others to arrange themselves in a line two yards apart. End of chapter 12

#:~:text=chapter%20xiii
Text:  CHAPTER XIII
Audio: CHAPTER XIII.

#:~:text=do%20you%20believe%20,%3F%20
Text:  DO YOU BELIEVE IN FAIRIES?
Audio: Do you believe in fairies?

#:~:text=the%20more%20q,.%20
Text:  The more quickly this horror is disposed of the better. 
Audio: The more quickly this horror is disposed of the better.

#:~:text=the%20first%20to%20e,.%20
Text:  The first to emerge from his tree was Curly. 
Audio: The first to emerge from his tree was Curly.

#:~:text=he%20rose%20o,.%20
Text:  He rose out of it into the arms of Cecco, who flung him to Smee, who flung him to Starkey, who flung him to Bill Jukes, who flung him to Noodler, and so he was tossed from one to another till he fell at the feet of the black pirate. 
Audio: He rose out of it into the arms of Sekko, who flung him to Smee, who flung him to Starkey, who flung him to Bill Jukes, who flung him to Noodler, and so he was tossed from one to another till he fell at the feet of the black pirate.

#:~:text=all%20the%20boys%20w,.%20
Text:  All the boys were plucked from their trees in this ruthless manner; and several of them were in the air at a time, like bales of goods flung from hand to hand.
Audio: All the boys were plucked from their trees in this ruthless manner, and several of them were in the air at a time, like bales of goods flung from hand to hand.

#:~:text=a%20diffe,.%20
Text:  A different treatment was accorded to Wendy, who came last. 
Audio: A different treatment was accorded to Wendy, who came last.

#:~:text=with%20ir,.%20
Text:  With ironical politeness Hook raised his hat to her, and, offering her his arm, escorted her to the spot where the others were being gagged. 
Audio: With ironical politeness Hook raised his hat to her, and, offering her his arm, escorted her to the spot where the others were being gagged.

#:~:text=he%20did%20it%20w,.%20
Text:  He did it with such an air, he was so frightfully distingué, that she was too fascinated to cry out. 
Audio: He did it with such an air, he was so frightfully distant gay, that she was too fascinated to cry out.

#:~:text=she%20was%20onl,.%20
Text:  She was only a little girl.
Audio: She was only a little girl.

#:~:text=perhaps%20it%20i,.%20
Text:  Perhaps it is tell-tale to divulge that for a moment Hook entranced her, and we tell on her only because her slip led to strange results. 
Audio: Perhaps it is tell-tale to divulge that for a moment Hook entranced her, and we tell on her only because her slip led to strange results.

#:~:text=had%20sh,.%20
Text:  Had she haughtily unhanded him (and we should have loved to write it of her), she would have been hurled through the air like the others, and then Hook would probably not have been present at the tying of the children; and had he not been at the tying he would not have discovered Slightly's secret, and without the secret he could not presently have made his foul attempt on Peter's life.
Audio: But she haughtily unhanded him, and we should have loved to write it of her. She would have been hurled through the air like the others, and then Hook would probably not have been present at the tying of the children. And had he not been at the tying, he would not have discovered Slightly's secret, and without the secret he could not presently have made his foul attempt on Peter's life.

#:~:text=they%20were%20ti,.%20
Text:  They were tied to prevent their flying away, doubled up with their knees close to their ears; and for the trussing of them the black pirate had cut a rope into nine equal pieces. 
Audio: They were tied to prevent their flying away, doubled up with their knees close to their ears, and for the trussing of them the black pirate had cut a rope into nine equal pieces.

#:~:text=all%20went%20w,.%20
Text:  All went well until Slightly's turn came, when he was found to be like those irritating parcels that use up all the string in going round and leave no tags with which to tie a knot. 
Audio: All went well until Slightly's turn came, when he was found to be like those irritating parcels that use up all the string in going round, and leave no tags with which to tie a knot.

#:~:text=the%20pirates%20k,.%20
Text:  The pirates kicked him in their rage, just as you kick the parcel (though in fairness you should kick the string); and strange to say it was Hook who told them to belay their violence. 
Audio: The pirates kicked him in their rage, just as you kicked the parcel, though in fairness you should kick the string. And strange to say, it was Hook who told them to belay their violence.

#:~:text=his%20lip%20w,.%20
Text:  His lip was curled with malicious triumph. 
Audio: His lip was curled with malicious triumph.

#:~:text=while%20hi,.%20
Text:  While his dogs were merely sweating because every time they tried to pack the unhappy lad tight in one part he bulged out in another, Hook's master mind had gone far beneath Slightly's surface, probing not for effects but for causes; and his exultation showed that he had found them. 
Audio: While his dogs were merely sweating, because every time they tried to pack the unhappy lad tight in one part he bulged out in another, Hook's master-mind had gone far beneath Slightly's surface, hoping not for effects, but for causes, and his exultation showed that he had found them.

#:~:text=slightly%2C%20whi,.%20
Text:  Slightly, white to the gills, knew that Hook had surprised his secret, which was this, that no boy so blown out could use a tree wherein an average man need stick. 
Audio: Slightly, white to the gills, knew that Hook had surprised his secret. Which was this, that no boy so blown out could use a tree wherein an average man needs stick.

#:~:text=poor%20sl,.%20
Text:  Poor Slightly, most wretched of all the children now, for he was in a panic about Peter, bitterly regretted what he had done. 
Audio: Poor Slightly, most wretched of all the children now, for he was in a panic about Peter, bitterly regretted what he had done.

#:~:text=madl,.%20
Text:  Madly addicted to the drinking of water when he was hot, he had swelled in consequence to his present girth, and instead of reducing himself to fit his tree he had, unknown to the others, whittled his tree to make it fit him.
Audio: Madly addicted to the drinking of water when he was hot, he had swelled in consequence to his present girth, and instead of reducing himself to fit his tree, he had, unknown to the others, whittled his tree to make it fit him.

#:~:text=suf,.%20
Text:  Sufficient of this Hook guessed to persuade him that Peter at last lay at his mercy; but no word of the dark design that now formed in the subterranean caverns of his mind crossed his lips; he merely signed that the captives were to be conveyed to the ship, and that he would be alone.
Audio: Sufficient of this, Hook guessed to persuade him that Peter at last lay at his mercy. But no word of the dark design that now formed in the subterranean caverns of his mind crossed his lips. He merely signed that the captives were to be conveyed to the ship, and that he would be alone.

#:~:text=how%20to%20c,%3F%20
Text:  How to convey them? 
Audio: How to convey them?

#:~:text=hunc,.%20
Text:  Hunched up in their ropes they might indeed be rolled down hill like barrels, but most of the way lay through a morass. 
Audio: Hunched up in their ropes they might indeed be rolled downhill like barrels, but most of the way lay through a morass.

#:~:text=again%20h,.%20
Text:  Again Hook's genius surmounted difficulties. 
Audio: Again Hook's genius surmounted difficulties.

#:~:text=he%20indic,.%20
Text:  He indicated that the little house must be used as a conveyance. 
Audio: He indicated that the little house must be used as a conveyance.

#:~:text=the%20children%20were%20f,.%20
Text:  The children were flung into it, four stout pirates raised it on their shoulders, the others fell in behind, and singing the hateful pirate chorus the strange procession set off through the wood. 
Audio: The children were flung into it. Four stout pirates raised it on their shoulders. The others fell in behind, and, singing the hateful pirate chorus, the strange procession set off through the wood.

#:~:text=i%20don't%20know%20w,.%20
Text:  I don't know whether any of the children were crying; if so, the singing drowned the sound; but as the little house disappeared in the forest, a brave though tiny jet of smoke issued from its chimney as if defying Hook.
Audio: I don't know whether any of the children were crying. If so, the singing drowned the sound. But as the little house disappeared in the forest, a brave though tiny jet of smoke issued from its chimney, as if defying Hook.

#:~:text=hook%20sa,.%20
Text:  Hook saw it, and it did Peter a bad service. 
Audio: Hook saw it, and it did Peter a bad service.

#:~:text=it%20drie,.%20
Text:  It dried up any trickle of pity for him that may have remained in the pirate's infuriated breast.
Audio: He dried up any trickle of pity for him that may have remained in the pirate's infuriated breast.

#:~:text=the%20first%20thing%20,.%20
Text:  The first thing he did on finding himself alone in the fast falling night was to tiptoe to Slightly's tree, and make sure that it provided him with a passage. 
Audio: The first thing he did on finding himself alone in the fast-falling night, was to tip-toe to Slightly's tree, and make sure that it provided him with a passage.

#:~:text=then%20fo,.%20
Text:  Then for long he remained brooding; his hat of ill omen on the sward, so that a gentle breeze which had arisen might play refreshingly through his hair. 
Audio: Then for long he remained brooding, his hat of ill omen on the sward, so that any gentle breeze which had arisen might play refreshingly through his hair.

#:~:text=dark%20as%20w,.%20
Text:  Dark as were his thoughts his blue eyes were as soft as the periwinkle. 
Audio: Dark as were his thoughts, his blue eyes were as soft as the periwinkle.

#:~:text=intently%20h,.%20
Text:  Intently he listened for any sound from the nether world, but all was as silent below as above; the house under the ground seemed to be but one more empty tenement in the void. 
Audio: Intently he listened for any sound from the nether world. But all was as silent below as above. The house under the ground seemed to be but one more empty tenement in the void.

#:~:text=was%20that%20b,%3F%20
Text:  Was that boy asleep, or did he stand waiting at the foot of Slightly's tree, with his dagger in his hand?
Audio: Was that boy asleep? Or did he stand waiting at the foot of Slightly's tree with his dagger in his hand?

#:~:text=there%20was%20no%20w,.%20
Text:  There was no way of knowing, save by going down. 
Audio: There was no way of knowing save by going down.

#:~:text=hook%20let%20his%20c,.%20
Text:  Hook let his cloak slip softly to the ground, and then biting his lips till a lewd blood stood on them, he stepped into the tree. 
Audio: Hook let his cloak slip softly to the ground, and then, biting his lips till a lewd blood stood on them. He stepped into the tree.

#:~:text=he%20was%20a%20b,.%20
Text:  He was a brave man; but for a moment he had to stop there and wipe his brow, which was dripping like a candle. 
Audio: He was a brave man, but for a moment he had to stop there and wipe his brow, which was dripping like a candle.

#:~:text=then%20silent,.%20
Text:  Then silently he let himself go into the unknown.
Audio: Then, silently, he let himself go into the unknown.

#:~:text=he%20arr,.%20
Text:  He arrived unmolested at the foot of the shaft, and stood still again, biting at his breath, which had almost left him. 
Audio: He arrived unmolested at the foot of the shaft, and stood still again, biting at his breath which had almost left him.

#:~:text=as%20his%20ey,.%20
Text:  As his eyes became accustomed to the dim light various objects in the home under the trees took shape; but the only one on which his greedy gaze rested, long sought for and found at last, was the great bed. 
Audio: As his eyes became accustomed to the dim light, various objects in the home under the trees took shape. But the only one on which his greedy gaze rested, long sought for, and found at last, was the great bed.

#:~:text=on%20the%20bed%20l,.%20
Text:  On the bed lay Peter fast asleep.
Audio: In the bed lay Peter fast asleep.

#:~:text=unaware%20of%20t,.%20
Text:  Unaware of the tragedy being enacted above, Peter had continued, for a little time after the children left, to play gaily on his pipes: no doubt rather a forlorn attempt to prove to himself that he did not care. 
Audio: Unaware of the tragedy being enacted above, Peter had continued, for a little time after the children left, to play gaily on his pipes. No doubt rather a forlorn attempt to prove to himself that he did not care.

#:~:text=then%20he%20d,.%20
Text:  Then he decided not to take his medicine, so as to grieve Wendy. 
Audio: Then he decided not to take his medicine, so as to grieve Wendy.

#:~:text=then%20he%20l,.%20
Text:  Then he lay down on the bed outside the coverlet, to vex her still more; for she had always tucked them inside it, because you never know that you may not grow chilly at the turn of the night. 
Audio: Then he lay down on the bed outside the coverlet, to vex her still more, for she had always tucked them inside it, because you never know that you may not grow chilly at the turn of the night.

#:~:text=then%20he%20n,.%20
Text:  Then he nearly cried; but it struck him how indignant she would be if he laughed instead; so he laughed a haughty laugh and fell asleep in the middle of it.
Audio: Then he nearly cried, but it struck him how indignant she would be if he laughed instead. So he laughed a haughty laugh, and fell asleep in the middle of it.

#:~:text=sometimes%2C,.%20
Text:  Sometimes, though not often, he had dreams, and they were more painful than the dreams of other boys. 
Audio: Sometimes, though not often, he had dreams, and they were more painful than the dreams of other boys.

#:~:text=for%20hours%20,.%20
Text:  For hours he could not be separated from these dreams, though he wailed piteously in them. 
Audio: For hours he could not be separated from those dreams, though he wailed piteously in them.

#:~:text=they%20had%20to%20d,.%20
Text:  They had to do, I think, with the riddle of his existence. 
Audio: They had to do, I think, with the riddle of his existence.

#:~:text=at%20such%20times%20,.%20
Text:  At such times it had been Wendy's custom to take him out of bed and sit with him on her lap, soothing him in dear ways of her own invention, and when he grew calmer to put him back to bed before he quite woke up, so that he should not know of the indignity to which she had subjected him. 
Audio: At such times it had been Wendy's custom to take him out of bed, and sit with him on her lap, soothing him in dear ways of her own invention. And when he grew calmer, to put him back to bed before he quite woke up, so that he should not know of the indignity to which she had subjected him.

#:~:text=but%20on%20thi,.%20
Text:  But on this occasion he had fallen at once into a dreamless sleep. 
Audio: But on this occasion he had fallen at once into a dreamless sleep.

#:~:text=one%20arm,.%20
Text:  One arm dropped over the edge of the bed, one leg was arched, and the unfinished part of his laugh was stranded on his mouth, which was open, showing the little pearls.
Audio: One arm dropped over the edge of the bed. One leg was arched, and the unfinished part of his laugh was stranded on his mouth, which was open, showing the little pearls.

#:~:text=thus%20de,.%20
Text:  Thus defenceless Hook found him. 
Audio: Thus defenseless Hook found him.

#:~:text=he%20stood%20s,.%20
Text:  He stood silent at the foot of the tree looking across the chamber at his enemy. 
Audio: He stood silent at the foot of the tree, looking across the chamber at his enemy.

#:~:text=did%20no%20,%3F%20
Text:  Did no feeling of compassion disturb his sombre breast? 
Audio: Did no feeling of compassion disturb his sombre breast?

#:~:text=the%20man%20,.%20
Text:  The man was not wholly evil; he loved flowers (I have been told) and sweet music (he was himself no mean performer on the harpsichord); and, let it be frankly admitted, the idyllic nature of the scene stirred him profoundly. 
Audio: The man was not wholly evil. He loved flowers, I have been told, and sweet music. He was himself no mean performer on the harpsichord. And, let it be frankly admitted, the idyllic nature of the scene stirred him profoundly.

#:~:text=mastered%20b,.%20
Text:  Mastered by his better self he would have returned reluctantly up the tree, but for one thing.
Audio: And by his better self he would have returned reluctantly up the tree, but for one thing.

#:~:text=what%20st,.%20
Text:  What stayed him was Peter's impertinent appearance as he slept. 
Audio: What stayed him was Peter's impertinent appearance as he slept.

#:~:text=the%20ope,.%20
Text:  The open mouth, the drooping arm, the arched knee: they were such a personification of cockiness as, taken together, will never again one may hope be presented to eyes so sensitive to their offensiveness. 
Audio: The open mouth, the drooping arm, the arched knee, they were such a personification of cockiness as, taken together, will never again, one may hope, be presented to eyes so sensitive to their offensiveness.

#:~:text=they%20ste,.%20
Text:  They steeled Hook's heart. 
Audio: They steeled Hook's heart.

#:~:text=if%20hi,.%20
Text:  If his rage had broken him into a hundred pieces every one of them would have disregarded the incident, and leapt at the sleeper.
Audio: If his rage had broken him into a hundred pieces, every one of them would have disregarded the incident and leaped at the sleeper.

#:~:text=though%20a%20l,.%20
Text:  Though a light from the one lamp shone dimly on the bed Hook stood in darkness himself, and at the first stealthy step forward he discovered an obstacle, the door of Slightly's tree. 
Audio: Though a light from the one lamp shone dimly on the bed, Hook stood in darkness himself. And at the first stealthy step forward he discovered an obstacle. The door of Slightly's tree.

#:~:text=it%20did%20n,.%20
Text:  It did not entirely fill the aperture, and he had been looking over it. 
Audio: It did not entirely fill the aperture, and he had been looking over it.

#:~:text=feeling%20for%20t,.%20
Text:  Feeling for the catch, he found to his fury that it was low down, beyond his reach. 
Audio: Feeling for the catch, he found to his fury that it was low down, beyond his reach.

#:~:text=to%20his%20d,.%20
Text:  To his disordered brain it seemed then that the irritating quality in Peter's face and figure visibly increased, and he rattled the door and flung himself against it. 
Audio: To his disordered brain it seemed then that the irritating quality in Peter's face and figure visibly increased, and he rattled the door and flung himself against it.

#:~:text=was%20his%20e,.%20
Text:  Was his enemy to escape him after all.
Audio: Was his enemy to escape him after all?

#:~:text=but%20what%20w,%3F%20
Text:  But what was that? 
Audio: But what was that?

#:~:text=the%20red%20,.%20
Text:  The red in his eye had caught sight of Peter's medicine standing on a ledge within easy reach. 
Audio: The red in his eye had caught sight of Peter's medicine, standing on a ledge within easy reach.

#:~:text=he%20fath,.%20
Text:  He fathomed what it was straightway, and immediately he knew that the sleeper was in his power.
Audio: He fathomed what it was straight away, and immediately knew that the sleeper was in his power.

#:~:text=lest%20he%20should%20b,.%20
Text:  Lest he should be taken alive, Hook always carried about his person a dreadful drug, blended by himself of all the death-dealing rings that had come into his possession. 
Audio: Lest he should be taken alive, Hook always carried about his person a dreadful drug, blended by himself of all the death-dealing rings that had come into his possession.

#:~:text=these%20h,.%20
Text:  These he had boiled down into a yellow liquid quite unknown to science, which was probably the most virulent poison in existence.
Audio: These he had boiled down into a yellow liquid quite unknown to science, which was probably the most virulent poison in existence.

#:~:text=five%20d,.%20
Text:  Five drops of this he now added to Peter's cup. 
Audio: Five drops of this he now added to Peter's cup.

#:~:text=his%20hand%20s,.%20
Text:  His hand shook, but it was in exultation rather than in shame. 
Audio: His hand shook, but it was in exultation rather than in shame.

#:~:text=as%20he%20d,.%20
Text:  As he did it he avoided glancing at the sleeper, but not lest pity should unnerve him; merely to avoid spilling. 
Audio: As he did it he avoided glancing at the sleeper. But not lest pity should unnerve him, merely to avoid spilling.

#:~:text=then%20o,.%20
Text:  Then one long gloating look he cast upon his victim, and turning, wormed his way with difficulty up the tree. 
Audio: In one long gloating look he cast upon his victim, and turning, wormed his way with difficulty up the tree.

#:~:text=as%20he%20e,.%20
Text:  As he emerged at the top he looked the very spirit of evil breaking from its hole. 
Audio: As he emerged at the top he looked the very spirit of evil breaking from its hole.

#:~:text=donn,.%20
Text:  Donning his hat at its most rakish angle, he wound his cloak around him, holding one end in front as if to conceal his person from the night, of which it was the blackest part, and muttering strangely to himself stole away through the trees.
Audio: Donning his hat at its most rakish angle, he wound his cloak around him, holding one end in front as if to conceal his person from the night, of which it was the blackest part, and, wondering strangely to himself, stole away through the trees.

#:~:text=peter%20sl,.%20
Text:  Peter slept on. 
Audio: Peter slept on.

#:~:text=the%20light%20g,.%20
Text:  The light guttered and went out, leaving the tenement in darkness; but still he slept. 
Audio: The light guttered, and went out, leaving the tenement in darkness. But still he slept.

#:~:text=it%20must%20have%20been%20n,.%20
Text:  It must have been not less than ten o'clock by the crocodile, when he suddenly sat up in his bed, wakened by he knew not what. 
Audio: It must have been not less than ten o'clock by the Crocodile, when he suddenly sat up in his bed, wakened by he knew not what.

#:~:text=it%20was%20a%20so,.%20
Text:  It was a soft cautious tapping on the door of his tree.
Audio: It was a soft, cautious tapping on the door of his tree.

#:~:text=soft%20an,.%20
Text:  Soft and cautious, but in that stillness it was sinister. 
Audio: Soft and cautious, but in that stillness it was sinister.

#:~:text=peter%20felt%20f,.%20
Text:  Peter felt for his dagger till his hand gripped it. 
Audio: Peter felt for his dagger till his hand gripped it.

#:~:text=then%20he%20s,%20
Text:  Then he spoke.
Audio: Then he spoke.

#:~:text='who%20i,%3F
Text:  'Who is that?
Audio: Who was that?

#:~:text=hat%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=for%20long%20t,.%20
Text:  For long there was no answer: then again the knock.
Audio: For long there was no answer. Then again the knock.

#:~:text=k.%20-,'who%20are%20you%3F
Text:  'Who are you?
Audio: Who are you?

#:~:text=ou%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=no%20answer.
Text:  No answer.
Audio: No answer.

#:~:text=he%20was%20thr,.%20
Text:  He was thrilled, and he loved being thrilled. 
Audio: He was thrilled, and he loved being thrilled.

#:~:text=in%20tw,.%20
Text:  In two strides he reached his door. 
Audio: In two strides he reached the door.

#:~:text=unlike%20s,.%20
Text:  Unlike Slightly's door it filled the aperture, so that he could not see beyond it, nor could the one knocking see him.
Audio: Unlike Slightly's door, it filled the aperture, so that he could not see beyond it, nor could the one knocking see him.

#:~:text='i%20won,.%20
Text:  'I won't open unless you speak,' Peter cried.
Audio: I won't open unless you speak, Peter cried.

#:~:text=then%20at%20last%20the%20,.%20
Text:  Then at last the visitor spoke, in a lovely bell-like voice.
Audio: Then at last the visitor spoke, in a lovely bell-like voice.

#:~:text='let%20m,.
Text:  'Let me in, Peter.
Audio: Let me in, Peter.

#:~:text=ter.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=it%20was%20tin,.%20
Text:  It was Tink, and quickly he unbarred to her. 
Audio: It was Tink, and quickly he unbarred to her.

#:~:text=she%20flew%20,.%20
Text:  She flew in excitedly, her face flushed and her dress stained with mud.
Audio: She flew in excitedly, her face flushed, and her dress stained with mud.

#:~:text=ud.%20-,'what%20is%20it%3F
Text:  'What is it?
Audio: What is it?

#:~:text=it%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='oh%2C%20y,.%20
Text:  'Oh, you could never guess,' she cried, and offered him three guesses. 
Audio: Oh, you could never guess, she cried, and offered him three guesses.

#:~:text='out,!
Text:  'Out with it!
Audio: Out with it,

#:~:text='%20he%20shouted%3B,.%20
Text:  ' he shouted; and in one ungrammatical sentence, as long as the ribbons conjurers pull from their mouths, she told of the capture of Wendy and the boys.
Audio: he shouted, and in one ungrammatical sentence. As long as the ribbons the conjurers pulled from their mouths, she told of the capture of Wendy and the boys.

#:~:text=peter's%20h,.%20
Text:  Peter's heart bobbed up and down as he listened. 
Audio: Peter's heart bobbed up and down as he listened.

#:~:text=wendy%20bo,!%20
Text:  Wendy bound, and on the pirate ship; she who loved everything to be just so!
Audio: Wendy bound, and on the pirate ship, she who loved everything to be just so.

#:~:text='i'll%20r,.%20
Text:  'I'll rescue her,' he cried, leaping at his weapons. 
Audio: I'll rescue her, he cried, leaping at his weapons.

#:~:text=as%20he%20le,.%20
Text:  As he leapt he thought of something he could do to please her. 
Audio: As he leaped, he thought of something he could do to please her.

#:~:text=he%20could%20ta,.%20
Text:  He could take his medicine.
Audio: He could take his medicine.

