#:~:text=her%20wings%20,.%20
Text:  Her wings would scarcely carry her now, but in reply she alighted on his shoulder and gave his chin a loving bite. 
Audio: Her wings would scarcely carry her now, but in reply she alighted on his shoulder and gave his nose a loving bite.

#:~:text=she%20whi,.%20
Text:  She whispered in his ear 'You silly ass'; and then, tottering to her chamber, lay down on the bed.
Audio: She whispered in his ear, You silly ass! Then, tottering to her chamber, lay down on the bed.

#:~:text=his%20head%20a,.%20
Text:  His head almost filled the fourth wall of her little room as he knelt near her in distress. 
Audio: His head almost filled the fourth wall of her little room as he knelt near her in distress.

#:~:text=every%20mom,.%20
Text:  Every moment her light was growing fainter; and he knew that if it went out she would be no more. 
Audio: Every moment her light was growing fainter, and he knew that if it went out she would be no more.

#:~:text=she%20lik,.%20
Text:  She liked his tears so much that she put out her beautiful finger and let them run over it.
Audio: She liked his tears so much that she put out her beautiful finger and let them run over it.

#:~:text=her%20voice%20w,.%20
Text:  Her voice was so low that at first he could not make out what she said. 
Audio: Her voice was so low that at first he could not make out what she said.

#:~:text=then%20he%20m,.%20
Text:  Then he made it out. 
Audio: Then he made it out.

#:~:text=she%20was%20s,.%20
Text:  She was saying that she thought she could get well again if children believed in fairies.
Audio: She was saying that she thought she could get well again if children believed in fairies.

#:~:text=peter%20fl,.%20
Text:  Peter flung out his arms. 
Audio: Peter flung out his arms.

#:~:text=there%20were%20n,.%20
Text:  There were no children there, and it was night-time; but he addressed all who might be dreaming of the Neverland, and who were therefore nearer to him than you think: boys and girls in their nighties, and naked papooses in their baskets hung from trees.
Audio: There were no children there, and it was night-time, but he addressed all who might be dreaming of the Neverland, and who were therefore nearer to him than you think. Boys and girls in their nighties, and naked papooses in their baskets hung from trees.

#:~:text='do%20you%20b,%3F
Text:  'Do you believe?
Audio: Do you believe?

#:~:text=%3F-,'%20he%20cried.%20
Text:  ' he cried.
Audio: He cried.

#:~:text=tink%20s,.%20
Text:  Tink sat up in bed almost briskly to listen to her fate.
Audio: Tink sat up in bed almost briskly to listen to her fate.

#:~:text=she%20fa,.%20
Text:  She fancied she heard answers in the affirmative, and then again she wasn't sure.
Audio: She fancied she heard answers in the affirmative. And then again she wasn't sure.

#:~:text='what%20do%20you%20think%3F
Text:  'What do you think?
Audio: What do you think?

#:~:text='%20she%20asked%20,%20
Text:  ' she asked Peter.
Audio: She asked Peter.

#:~:text='if%20you%20b,.
Text:  'If you believe,' he shouted to them, 'clap your hands; don't let Tink die.
Audio: If you believe, he shouted to them, clap your hands! Don't let Tink die!

#:~:text=die.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=many%20cl,%20
Text:  Many clapped.
Audio: She clapped.

#:~:text=some%20di,%20
Text:  Some didn't.
Audio: Some didn't.

#:~:text=a%20few%20l,.%20
Text:  A few little beasts hissed.
Audio: A few beasts hissed.

#:~:text=the%20clap,.%20
Text:  The clapping stopped suddenly; as if countless mothers had rushed to their nurseries to see what on earth was happening; but already Tink was saved. 
Audio: The clapping stopped suddenly, as if countless mothers had rushed to their nurseries to see what on earth was happening. But already Tink was saved.

#:~:text=first%20her,.%20
Text:  First her voice grew strong; then she popped out of bed; then she was flashing through the room more merry and impudent than ever. 
Audio: First, her voice grew strong. Then she popped out of bed. Then she was flashing through the room, more merry and impudent than ever.

#:~:text=she%20never%20t,.%20
Text:  She never thought of thanking those who believed, but she would have liked to get at the ones who had hissed.
Audio: She never thought of thanking those who believed, but she would have liked to get at the ones who had hissed.

#:~:text='and%20now%20t,.
Text:  'And now to rescue Wendy.
Audio: And now to rescue Wendy!

#:~:text=dy.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=the%20moon%20,.%20
Text:  The moon was riding in a cloudy heaven when Peter rose from his tree, begirt with weapons and wearing little else, to set out upon his perilous quest. 
Audio: The moon was riding in a cloudy heaven when Peter rose from his tree, begirt with weapons and wearing little else, to set out upon his perilous quest.

#:~:text=it%20was%20not%20s,.%20
Text:  It was not such a night as he would have chosen. 
Audio: It was not such a night as he would have chosen.

#:~:text=he%20had%20ho,.%20
Text:  He had hoped to fly, keeping not far from the ground so that nothing unwonted should escape his eyes; but in that fitful light to have flown low would have meant trailing his shadow through the trees, thus disturbing the birds and acquainting a watchful foe that he was astir.
Audio: He had hoped to fly, keeping not far from the ground so that nothing unwanted should escape his eyes. But in that fitful light, to have flown low would have meant trailing his shadow through the trees, thus disturbing birds and acquainting a watchful foe that he was astir.

#:~:text=he%20reg,.%20
Text:  He regretted now that he had given the birds of the island such strange names that they are very wild and difficult of approach.
Audio: He regretted now that he had given the birds of the island such strange names that they are very wild and difficult of approach.

#:~:text=there%20was%20no%20o,.%20
Text:  There was no other course but to press forward in redskin fashion, at which happily he was an adept. 
Audio: There was no other course but to press forward in redskin fashion, at which, happily, he was an adept.

#:~:text=but%20in%20w,%3F%20
Text:  But in what direction, for he could not be sure that the children had been taken to the ship? 
Audio: But in what direction? For he could not be sure that the children had been taken to the ship.

#:~:text=a%20sl,.%20
Text:  A slight fall of snow had obliterated all footmarks; and a deathly silence pervaded the island, as if for a space Nature stood still in horror of the recent carnage. 
Audio: A light fall of snow had obliterated all footmarks, and a deathly silence pervaded the island, as if for a space nature stood still in horror of the recent carnage.

#:~:text=he%20had%20ta,.%20
Text:  He had taught the children something of the forest lore that he had himself learned from Tiger Lily and Tinker Bell, and knew that in their dire hour they were not likely to forget it. 
Audio: He had taught the children something of the forest lore that he had himself learned from Tiger Lily and Tinker Bell, and knew that in their dire hour they were not likely to forget it.

#:~:text=slightly%2C%20i,.%20
Text:  Slightly, if he had an opportunity, would blaze the trees, for instance, Curly would drop seeds, and Wendy would leave her handkerchief at some important place. 
Audio: Only, if he had an opportunity, would blaze the trees, for instance. Curly would drop seeds, and Wendy would leave her handkerchief at some important place.

#:~:text=but%20mor,.%20
Text:  But morning was needed to search for such guidance, and he could not wait. 
Audio: The morning was needed to search for such guidance, and he could not wait.

#:~:text=the%20up,.%20
Text:  The upper world had called him, but would give no help.
Audio: The upper world had called him, but would give no help.

#:~:text=the%20crocodile%20passe,.%20
Text:  The crocodile passed him, but not another living thing, not a sound, not a movement; and yet he knew well that sudden death might be at the next tree, or stalking him from behind.
Audio: The crocodile passed him, but not another living thing, not a sound, not a movement, and yet he knew well that sudden death might be at the next tree, or stalking him from behind.

#:~:text=he%20swo,.
Text:  He swore this terrible oath: 'Hook or me this time.
Audio: He swore this terrible oath, Hook or me this time!

#:~:text=ime.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=now%20he%20,.%20
Text:  Now he crawled forward like a snake; and again, erect, he darted across a space on which the moonlight played: one finger on his lip and his dagger at the ready. 
Audio: Now he crawled forward like a snake, and again erect, he darted across the space on which the moonlight played, one finger on his lip and his dagger at the ready.

#:~:text=he%20was%20fr,.%20
Text:  He was frightfully happy.
Audio: He was frightfully happy.

