#:~:text=v%20-,the%20pirate%20ship%20
Text:  THE PIRATE SHIP
Audio: The Pirate Ship.

#:~:text=one%20gr,.%20
Text:  One green light squinting over Kidd's Creek, which is near the mouth of the pirate river, marked where the brig, the Jolly Roger, lay, low in the water; a rakish-looking craft foul to the hull, every beam in her detestable like ground strewn with mangled feathers. 
Audio: One green light squinting over Kidd's Creek, which is near the mouth of the Pirate River, marked where the brig, the Jolly Roger, lay low in the water. A rakish-looking craft, foul to the hull, every beam in her detestable, like ground, strewn with mental feathers.

#:~:text=she%20was%20the%20c,.%20
Text:  She was the cannibal of the seas, and scarce needed that watchful eye, for she floated immune in the horror of her name.
Audio: She was the cannibal of the seas, and scarce needed that watchful eye, for she floated immune in the horror of her name.

#:~:text=she%20was%20w,.%20
Text:  She was wrapped in the blanket of night, through which no sound from her could have reached the shore. 
Audio: She was wrapped in a blanket of night, through which no sound from her could have reached the shore.

#:~:text=there%20was%20l,.%20
Text:  There was little sound, and none agreeable save the whir of the ship's sewing machine at which Smee sat, ever industrious and obliging, the essence of the commonplace, pathetic Smee. 
Audio: There was little sound, and none agreeable save the whirr of the ship's sewing-machine, at which Smee sat, ever industrious and obliging, the essence of the commonplace, pathetic Smee. I

#:~:text=i%20know%20,.%20
Text:  I know not why he was so infinitely pathetic, unless it were because he was so pathetically unaware of it; but even strong men had to turn hastily from looking at him, and more than once on summer evenings he had touched the fount of Hook's tears and made it flow. 
Audio: I know not why he was so infinitely pathetic, unless it were because he was so pathetically unaware of it. But even strong men had to turn hastily from looking at him, and more than once on summer evenings he had touched the fount of folks' tears and made it flow.

#:~:text=of%20this%2C%20a,.%20
Text:  Of this, as of almost everything else, Smee was quite unconscious.
Audio: Of this, as of almost everything else, Smee was quite unconscious.

#:~:text=a%20few%20o,.%20
Text:  A few of the pirates leant over the bulwarks drinking in the miasma of the night; others sprawled by barrels over games of dice and cards; and the exhausted four who had carried the little house lay prone on the deck, where even in their sleep they rolled skilfully to this side or that out of Hook's reach, lest he should claw them mechanically in passing.
Audio: A few of the pirates leant over the bulwarks, drinking in the miasma of the night. Others sprawled by barrels over games of dice and cards, and the exhausted four who had carried little house lay prone on the deck, for even in their sleep they rolled skillfully to this side or that out of Hook's reach, lest he should claw them mechanically in passing.

#:~:text=hook%20tro,.%20
Text:  Hook trod the deck in thought. 
Audio: Hook trod the deck in thought.

#:~:text=o%20man%20,%20
Text:  O man unfathomable. 
Audio: O man unfathomable!

#:~:text=it%20was%20his%20h,.%20
Text:  It was his hour of triumph. 
Audio: It was his hour of triumph.

#:~:text=peter%20had%20b,.%20
Text:  Peter had been removed for ever from his path, and all the other boys were on the brig, about to walk the plank. 
Audio: Peter had been removed forever from his path, and all the other boys were in the brig, about to walk the plank.

#:~:text=it%20was%20his%20g,%3F%20
Text:  It was his grimmest deed since the days when he had brought Barbecue to heel; and knowing as we do how vain a tabernacle is man, could we be surprised had he now paced the deck unsteadily, bellied out by the winds of his success?
Audio: It was his grimmest deed since the days when he had brought barbecue to heel. And knowing as we do how vain a tabernacle is man, could we be surprised had he now paced the deck unsettling, bellied out by the wind with its success?

#:~:text=but%20there%20was%20no%20e,.%20
Text:  But there was no elation in his gait, which kept pace with the action of his sombre mind. 
Audio: But there was no relation in his gate, which kept pace with the action of his somber mind.

#:~:text=hook%20was%20p,.%20
Text:  Hook was profoundly dejected.
Audio: Hook was profoundly dejected.

#:~:text=he%20was%20often%20t,.%20
Text:  He was often thus when communing with himself on board ship in the quietude of the night. 
Audio: He was often thus, when communing with himself on board ship in the quietude of the night.

#:~:text=it%20was%20bec,.%20
Text:  It was because he was so terribly alone. 
Audio: It was because he was so terribly alone.

#:~:text=this%20ins,.%20
Text:  This inscrutable man never felt more alone than when surrounded by his dogs. 
Audio: This inscrutable man never felt more alone than when surrounded by his dogs.

#:~:text=they%20were%20so,.%20
Text:  They were socially so inferior to him.
Audio: They were socially inferior to him.

#:~:text=hook%20was%20n,.%20
Text:  Hook was not his true name. 
Audio: Hook was not his true name.

#:~:text=to%20rev,.%20
Text:  To reveal who he really was would even at this date set the country in a blaze; but as those who read between the lines must already have guessed, he had been at a famous public school; and its traditions still clung to him like garments, with which indeed they are largely concerned. 
Audio: To reveal who he really was would, even at this date, set the country in a blaze. But as those who read between the lines must already have guessed, he had been at a famous public school, and its traditions still clung to him like garments, with which, indeed, they are largely concerned.

#:~:text=thus%20i,.%20
Text:  Thus it was offensive to him even now to board a ship in the same dress in which he grappled her; and he still adhered in his walk to the school's distinguished slouch. 
Audio: Thus, it was offensive to him, even now, to board a ship in the same dress in which he grappled her, and he still adhered to his walk to the school's distinguished slouch.

#:~:text=but%20abov,.%20
Text:  But above all he retained the passion for good form.
Audio: But above all, he retained the passion for good form.

#:~:text=good%20form!
Text:  Good form! 
Audio: Good form!

#:~:text=however%20m,.%20
Text:  However much he may have degenerated, he still knew that this is all that really matters.
Audio: However much he may have degenerated, he still knew that this is all that really matters.

#:~:text=from%20fa,.%20
Text:  From far within him he heard a creaking as of rusty portals, and through them came a stern tap-tap-tap, like hammering in the night when one cannot sleep. 
Audio: From far within him he heard a creaking as of rusty portals, and through them came a stern tap-tap-tap, like hammering in the night when one cannot sleep.

#:~:text='have%20you%20b,%3F
Text:  'Have you been good form to-day?
Audio: Have you been good form today?

#:~:text='%20wa,.%20
Text:  ' was their eternal question.
Audio: was their eternal question.

#:~:text='fam,.%20
Text:  'Fame, fame, that glittering bauble, it is mine,' he cried.
Audio: Fame, fame, that glittering bauble, it is mine, he cried.

#:~:text='is%20i,%3F
Text:  'Is it quite good form to be distinguished at anything?
Audio: Is it quite good form to be distinguished at anything?

#:~:text='%20the%20t,.%20
Text:  ' the tap-tap from his school replied.
Audio: The tap-tap from his school replied.

#:~:text='i%20am%20t,.
Text:  'I am the only man whom Barbecue feared,' he urged; 'and Flint himself feared Barbecue.
Audio: I am the only man whom barbecue feared, he urged, and Flint feared barbecue.

#:~:text=cue.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='bar,%3F
Text:  'Barbecue, Flint—what house?
Audio: Barbecue, Flint, what else?

#:~:text='%20came%20the%20c,.%20
Text:  ' came the cutting retort.
Audio: came the cutting retort.

#:~:text=most%20dis,%3F%20
Text:  Most disquieting reflection of all, was it not bad form to think about good form?
Audio: Most disquieting reflection of all, was it not bad form to think about good form?

#:~:text=his%20vit,.%20
Text:  His vitals were tortured by this problem. 
Audio: His vitals were tortured by this problem.

#:~:text=it%20was%20a%20c,.%20
Text:  It was a claw within him sharper than the iron one; and as it tore him, the perspiration dripped down his tallow countenance and streaked his doublet. 
Audio: It was a claw within him sharper than the iron one. And as it tore him, the perspiration drifted down his tallow countenance and streaked his doublet.

#:~:text=oftt,.%20
Text:  Ofttimes he drew his sleeve across his face, but there was no damming that trickle.
Audio: Oft times he drew his sleeve across his face, but there was no damning that trickle.

#:~:text=ah%2C%20e,.%20
Text:  Ah, envy not Hook.
Audio: Ah, envy not, Hook.

#:~:text=there%20came%20to%20h,.%20
Text:  There came to him a presentiment of his early dissolution. 
Audio: There came to him a presentiment of his early dissolution.

#:~:text=it%20was%20as%20if%20p,.%20
Text:  It was as if Peter's terrible oath had boarded the ship. 
Audio: It was as if Peter's terrible oath had boarded the ship.

#:~:text=hook%20felt,.%20
Text:  Hook felt a gloomy desire to make his dying speech, lest presently there should be no time for it.
Audio: Hook felt a gloomy desire to make his dying speech, lest presently there should be no time for it.

#:~:text='better%20f,.
Text:  'Better for Hook,' he cried, 'if he had had less ambition.
Audio: Better for Hook, he cried, if he had had less ambition.

#:~:text='%20it%20w,.%20
Text:  ' It was in his darkest hours only that he referred to himself in the third person.
Audio: It was in his darkest hours only that he referred to himself in the third person.

#:~:text='no%20l,.
Text:  'No little children love me.
Audio: No little children to love me.

#:~:text=me.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=strange%20th,.%20
Text:  Strange that he should think of this, which had never troubled him before; perhaps the sewing machine brought it to his mind. 
Audio: Strange that he should think of this, which had never troubled him before. Perhaps the sewing machine brought it to his mind.

#:~:text=for%20long%20he%20m,.%20
Text:  For long he muttered to himself, staring at Smee, who was hemming placidly, under the conviction that all children feared him.
Audio: For long, he muttered to himself, staring at Smee, who was hemming placidly under the conviction that all children feared him.

#:~:text=feared%20him!
Text:  Feared him! 
Audio: Feared him?

#:~:text=feared%20s,%20
Text:  Feared Smee! 
Audio: Feared Smee?

#:~:text=there%20was%20not%20a%20c,.%20
Text:  There was not a child on board the brig that night who did not already love him. 
Audio: There was not a child on board the brig that night who did not already love him.

#:~:text=he%20had%20said%20h,.%20
Text:  He had said horrid things to them and hit them with the palm of his hand, because he could not hit with his fist; but they had only clung to him the more. 
Audio: He had said horrid things to them and hit them with the palm of his hand, because he could not hit with his fist. But they had only clung to him the more.

#:~:text=michael%20had%20tr,.%20
Text:  Michael had tried on his spectacles.
Audio: Michael had tried on his spectacles.

#:~:text=to%20tell%20p,!%20
Text:  To tell poor Smee that they thought him lovable! 
Audio: To tell poor Smee that they thought him lovable

#:~:text=hook%20it,.%20
Text:  Hook itched to do it, but it seemed too brutal. 
Audio: took Itch to do it. But it seemed too brutal.

#:~:text=instead%2C,%3F%20
Text:  Instead, he revolved this mystery in his mind: why do they find Smee lovable? 
Audio: Instead, he revolved this mystery in his mind. Why did they find Smee lovable?

#:~:text=he%20purs,.%20
Text:  He pursued the problem like the sleuth-hound that he was. 
Audio: He pursued the problem like the sleuth-hound that he was.

#:~:text=if%20sm,%3F%20
Text:  If Smee was lovable, what was it that made him so? 
Audio: If Smee was lovable, what was it that made him so?

#:~:text=a%20te,%3F
Text:  A terrible answer suddenly presented itself: 'Good form?
Audio: A terrible answer suddenly presented itself. Good form?

#:~:text=rm%3F-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=had%20the%20,%3F%20
Text:  Had the bo'sun good form without knowing it, which is the best form of all?
Audio: Had the boatswain good form without knowing it, which is, the best form of all? He

#:~:text=he%20remembered%20that%20y,.%20
Text:  He remembered that you have to prove you don't know you have it before you are eligible for Pop.
Audio: remembered that you have to prove you don't know you have it before you were eligible for pop.

#:~:text=with%20a%20cr,.%20
Text:  With a cry of rage he raised his iron hand over Smee's head; but he did not tear. 
Audio: With a cry of rage, he raised his iron hand over Smee's head, but he did not take tear.

#:~:text=what%20arr,%3A%20
Text:  What arrested him was this reflection:
Audio: What arrested him was this reflection.

#:~:text='to%20c,%3F
Text:  'To claw a man because he is good form, what would that be?
Audio: 

