#:~:text='tie,.%20
Text:  'Tie her up,' he shouted.
Audio: Tie her up, he shouted.

#:~:text=it%20was%20sm,.%20
Text:  It was Smee who tied her to the mast. 
Audio: It was Smee who tied her to the mast.

#:~:text='see%20,.
Text:  'See here, honey,' he whispered, 'I'll save you if you promise to be my mother.
Audio: See here, honey, he whispered. I'll save you if you promise to be my mother.

#:~:text=y%20mother.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=but%20not%20e,.%20
Text:  But not even for Smee would she make such a promise. 
Audio: But not even for Smee would she make such a promise.

#:~:text='i%20wou,.%20
Text:  'I would almost rather have no children at all,' she said disdainfully.
Audio: I would almost rather have no children at all, he said disdainfully.

#:~:text=it%20is%20sad,.%20
Text:  It is sad to know that not a boy was looking at her as Smee tied her to the mast; the eyes of all were on the plank: that last little walk they were about to take. 
Audio: It is sad to know that not a boy was looking at her as Smee tied her to the mast. The eyes of all were on the plank, that last little walk they were about to take.

#:~:text=they%20were%20no%20,.%20
Text:  They were no longer able to hope that they would walk it manfully, for the capacity to think had gone from them; they could stare and shiver only.
Audio: They were no longer able to hope that they would walk it manfully, for the capacity to think had gone from them. They could stare and shiver only.

#:~:text=hook%20sm,.%20
Text:  Hook smiled on them with his teeth closed, and took a step toward Wendy. 
Audio: Hook smiled on them with his teeth closed and took a step toward Wendy.

#:~:text=his%20inte,.%20
Text:  His intention was to turn her face so that she should see the boys walking the plank one by one. 
Audio: His intention was to turn her face so that she should see the boys walking the plank one by one.

#:~:text=but%20he%20n,.%20
Text:  But he never reached her, he never heard the cry of anguish he hoped to wring from her. 
Audio: But he never reached her. He never heard the cry of anguish he hoped to wring from her.

#:~:text=he%20heard%20s,.%20
Text:  He heard something else instead.
Audio: He heard something else instead.

#:~:text=it%20was%20the%20te,.%20
Text:  It was the terrible tick-tick of the crocodile.
Audio: It was the terrible kick-kick of the crocodile.

#:~:text=they%20all%20h,.%20
Text:  They all heard it—pirates, boys, Wendy; and immediately every head was blown in one direction; not to the water whence the sound proceeded, but toward Hook. 
Audio: They all heard it. Pirates. Boys. Wendy. And immediately every head was blown in one direction. Not to the water whence the sound proceeded, but toward Hook.

#:~:text=all%20knew%20t,.%20
Text:  All knew that what was about to happen concerned him alone, and that from being actors they were suddenly become spectators.
Audio: All knew that what was about to happen concerned him alone, and that, from being actors, they were suddenly becoming spectators.

#:~:text=very%20fr,.%20
Text:  Very frightful was it to see the change that came over him. 
Audio: Very frightful was it to see the change that came over him.

#:~:text=it%20was%20as%20if%20h,.%20
Text:  It was as if he had been clipped at every joint. 
Audio: It was as if he had been clipped at every joint.

#:~:text=he%20fell%20i,.%20
Text:  He fell in a little heap.
Audio: He fell in a little heap.

#:~:text=the%20sound%20c,.
Text:  The sound came steadily nearer; and in advance of it came this ghastly thought, 'The crocodile is about to board the ship.
Audio: 

#:~:text=hip.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: sound came steadily nearer, and in advance of it came this ghastly thought. The crocodile is about to board the ship.

#:~:text=even%20the%20i,.%20
Text:  Even the iron claw hung inactive; as if knowing that it was no intrinsic part of what the attacking force wanted. 
Audio: Even the iron claw hung inactive, as if knowing that it was no intrinsic part of the attacking force wanted.

#:~:text=left%20s,.%20
Text:  Left so fearfully alone, any other man would have lain with his eyes shut where he fell: but the gigantic brain of Hook was still working, and under its guidance he crawled on his knees along the deck as far from the sound as he could go. 
Audio: But left so fearfully alone, any other man would have lain with his eyes shut where he fell. But the gigantic brain of Hook was still working, and under its guidance, he crawled on the knees along the deck, as far from the sound as he could go.

#:~:text=the%20pirates%20r,.%20
Text:  The pirates respectfully cleared a passage for him, and it was only when he brought up against the bulwarks that he spoke.
Audio: The pirates respectfully cleared a passage for him, and it was only when he brought up against the bulwarks that he spoke.

#:~:text='hi,.%20
Text:  'Hide me,' he cried hoarsely.
Audio: Hide me, he cried hoarsely.

#:~:text=they%20gathered%20r,.%20
Text:  They gathered round him; all eyes averted from the thing that was coming aboard. 
Audio: They gathered round him, all eyes birded from the thing that was coming aboard.

#:~:text=they%20had%20no%20,.%20
Text:  They had no thought of fighting it. 
Audio: They had no thought of fighting it.

#:~:text=it%20was%20fa,%20
Text:  It was Fate.
Audio: It was fate.

#:~:text=only%20when%20ho,.%20
Text:  Only when Hook was hidden from them did curiosity loosen the limbs of the boys so that they could rush to the ship's side to see the crocodile climbing it. 
Audio: Only when Hook was hidden from them, did Curiosity loosen the limbs of the boys, so that they could rush to this ship's side to see the crocodile climbing it.

#:~:text=then%20they%20g,.%20
Text:  Then they got the strangest surprise of this Night of Nights; for it was no crocodile that was coming to their aid. 
Audio: Then they got the strange surprise of the night of nights. For it was no crocodile that was coming to their aid.

#:~:text=it%20was%20peter.
Text:  It was Peter.
Audio: It was Peter.

#:~:text=he%20signed%20to%20t,.%20
Text:  He signed to them not to give vent to any cry of admiration that might rouse suspicion. 
Audio: He signed them not to give vent to any cry of admiration of my aroused suspicion.

#:~:text=then%20he%20w,.%20
Text:  Then he went on ticking.
Audio: Then he went on ticking. Thank you.

#:~:text=chapter%20xv
Text:  CHAPTER XV
Audio: This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain. For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org. Peter Pan by J. M. Barry. Chapter 15.

#:~:text='hook%20or%20me%20this%20time'
Text:  'HOOK OR ME THIS TIME'
Audio: Hook or me this time.

#:~:text=odd%20things,.%20
Text:  Odd things happen to all of us on our way through life without our noticing for a time that they have happened. 
Audio: Odd things happen to all of us on our way through life without our noticing for a time that they have happened.

#:~:text=thus%2C,.%20
Text:  Thus, to take an instance, we suddenly discover that we have been deaf in one ear for we don't know how long, but, say, half an hour. 
Audio: Thus, to take an instance, we suddenly discover that we have been deaf in one year, for we don't know how long, but say half an hour.

#:~:text=now%20su,.%20
Text:  Now such an experience had come that night to Peter. 
Audio: Now such an experience had come that night to Peter.

#:~:text=when%20l,.%20
Text:  When last we saw him he was stealing across the island with one finger to his lips and his dagger at the ready. 
Audio: When last we saw him, he was stealing across the island with one finger to his lips and his dagger at the ready.

#:~:text=he%20had%20seen%20,.%20
Text:  He had seen the crocodile pass by without noticing anything peculiar about it, but by and by he remembered that it had not been ticking. 
Audio: He had seen the crocodile pass by without noticing anything peculiar about it, but by and by he remembered that it had not been ticking.

#:~:text=at%20first%20he%20thought%20thi,.%20
Text:  At first he thought this eerie, but soon he concluded rightly that the clock had run down.
Audio: At first, he thought this eerie, but soon concluded rightly that the clock had run down.

#:~:text=without%20g,.%20
Text:  Without giving a thought to what might be the feelings of a fellow-creature thus abruptly deprived of its closest companion, Peter at once considered how he could turn the catastrophe to his own use; and he decided to tick, so that wild beasts should believe he was the crocodile and let him pass unmolested. 
Audio: Without giving a thought to what might be the feelings of a fellow creature, thus abruptly deprived of its closest companion, Peter began to consider how he could turn the catastrophe to his own use, and he decided to tick, so that, while beasts should believe he was the crocodile and let him pass unmolested.

#:~:text=he%20ticke,.%20
Text:  He ticked superbly, but with one unforeseen result. 
Audio: He ticked superbly, but with one unforeseen result.

#:~:text=the%20crocodile%20was%20a,.%20
Text:  The crocodile was among those who heard the sound, and it followed him, though whether with the purpose of regaining what it had lost, or merely as a friend under the belief that it was again ticking itself, will never be certainly known, for, like all slaves to a fixed idea, it was a stupid beast.
Audio: The crocodile was among those who heard the sound, and it followed him, though whether with the purpose of regaining what it had lost, or merely as a friend under the belief that it was again ticking itself, will never be certainly known.

#:~:text=peter%20reached%20the%20s,.%20
Text:  Peter reached the shore without mishap, and went straight on; his legs encountering the water as if quite unaware that they had entered a new element. 
Audio: Peter reached the shore without mishap and went straight on, his legs encountering the water as if quite unaware that they had entered a new element.

#:~:text=thus%20man,.%20
Text:  Thus many animals pass from land to water, but no other human of whom I know. 
Audio: Peter asked, Thus, many animals pass from land to water, but no other human of whom I know.

#:~:text=as%20he%20sw,.
Text:  As he swam he had but one thought: 'Hook or me this time.
Audio: As he swam, he had but one thought, hook or me this time.

#:~:text='%20he%20h,.%20
Text:  ' He had ticked so long that he now went on ticking without knowing that he was doing it. 
Audio: He had ticked so long that he now went on ticking without knowing that he was doing it.

#:~:text=had%20he%20k,.%20
Text:  Had he known he would have stopped, for to board the brig by the help of the tick, though an ingenious idea, had not occurred to him.
Audio: Had he known, he would have stopped, for, to board the brick by help of the tick, though an ingenious idea, had not occurred to him.

#:~:text=on%20the%20contrary%2C%20h,.%20
Text:  On the contrary, he thought he had scaled her side as noiseless as a mouse; and he was amazed to see the pirates cowering from him, with Hook in their midst as abject as if he had heard the crocodile.
Audio: On the contrary, he thought he had scaled her side as noiseless as a mouse, and he was amazed to see the pirates covering from him, with hook in their midst, as abject as if he had heard the crocodile.

#:~:text=the%20crocodile!
Text:  The crocodile! 
Audio: The crocodile!

#:~:text=no%20soo,.%20
Text:  No sooner did Peter remember it than he heard the ticking. 
Audio: No sooner did Peter remember it than he heard the ticking.

#:~:text=at%20first%20he%20thought%20the,.%20
Text:  At first he thought the sound did come from the crocodile, and he looked behind him swiftly. 
Audio: At first, he thought the sound did come from the crocodile, and he looked behind him swiftly.

#:~:text=then%20he%20r,.%20
Text:  Then he realised that he was doing it himself, and in a flash he understood the situation. 
Audio: Then, he realized that he was doing it himself, and in a flash, he understood the situation.

#:~:text='how%20,.%20
Text:  'How clever of me,' he thought at once, and signed to the boys not to burst into applause.
Audio: How clever of me! He thought at once, and signed to the boys not to burst into applause.

#:~:text=it%20was%20at%20this%20moment%20that%20e,.%20
Text:  It was at this moment that Ed Teynte the quartermaster emerged from the forecastle and came along the deck. 
Audio: It was at this moment that Ed Daint, the quartermaster, emerged from the four-castle and came along the deck.

#:~:text=now%2C%20r,.%20
