#:~:text='%20came%20the%20t,.%20
Text:  ' came the terrible answer; and as he spoke Peter flung off his cloak. 
Audio: came the terrible answer, and as he spoke, Peter flung off his cloak.

#:~:text=then%20they,.%20
Text:  Then they all knew who 'twas that had been undoing them in the cabin, and twice Hook essayed to speak and twice he failed. 
Audio: Then they all knew who it was that had been undoing them in the cabin, and twice Hook essayed to speak, and twice he failed.

#:~:text=in%20that%20f,.%20
Text:  In that frightful moment I think his fierce heart broke.
Audio: In that frightful moment, I think his fierce heart broke.

#:~:text=at%20last%20he%20c,.%20
Text:  At last he cried, 'Cleave him to the brisket,' but without conviction.
Audio: At last he cried, Cleave him to the brisket, but without conviction.

#:~:text='dow,.%20
Text:  'Down, boys, and at them,' Peter's voice rang out; and in another moment the clash of arms was resounding through the ship. 
Audio: Down, boys, and at them. Peter's voice rang out, and in another moment, the clash of arms was resounding through the ship.

#:~:text=had%20the%20p,.%20
Text:  Had the pirates kept together it is certain that they would have won; but the onset came when they were all unstrung, and they ran hither and thither, striking wildly, each thinking himself the last survivor of the crew. 
Audio: Had the pirates kept together, it is certain that they would have won. But the onset came when they were still unstrung, and they ran hither and thither, striking wildly, each thinking himself the last survivor of the crew.

#:~:text=man%20to,.%20
Text:  Man to man they were the stronger; but they fought on the defensive only, which enabled the boys to hunt in pairs and choose their quarry. 
Audio: Man to man, they were the stronger. But they fought on the defensive only, which enabled the boys to hunt in pairs and choose their quarry.

#:~:text=some%20of%20the%20,.%20
Text:  Some of the miscreants leapt into the sea; others hid in dark recesses, where they were found by Slightly, who did not fight, but ran about with a lantern which he flashed in their faces, so that they were half blinded and fell an easy prey to the reeking swords of the other boys. 
Audio: Some of the miscreants leapt into the sea, others hidden dark recesses, where they were found by Slightly, who did not fight, but ran about with a lantern which he flashed in their faces, so that they were half blinded and fell as an easy prey to the reeking swords of the other boys. There

#:~:text=there%20was%20l,.%20
Text:  There was little sound to be heard but the clang of weapons, an occasional screech or splash, and Slightly monotonously counting—five—six—seven—eight—nine—ten—eleven.
Audio: was little sound to be heard but the clang of weapons, an occasional screech or splash, and slightly monotonously counting five, six, seven, eight, nine, ten, eleven.

#:~:text=i%20think%20a,.%20
Text:  I think all were gone when a group of savage boys surrounded Hook, who seemed to have a charmed life, as he kept them at bay in that circle of fire. 
Audio: I think all were gone when a group of savage boys surrounded Hook, who seemed to have a charmed life, as he kept them at bay in that circle of fire.

#:~:text=they%20had%20d,.%20
Text:  They had done for his dogs, but this man alone seemed to be a match for them all. 
Audio: They had done for his dogs, but this man alone seemed to be a match for them all.

#:~:text=again%20and%20again%20t,.%20
Text:  Again and again they closed upon him, and again and again he hewed a clear space. 
Audio: Again and again they closed upon him, and again and again he hewed a clear space.

#:~:text=he%20had%20li,.%20
Text:  He had lifted up one boy with his hook, and was using him as a buckler, when another, who had just passed his sword through Mullins, sprang into the fray.
Audio: He had lifted up one boy with his hook and was using him as a buckler shield, when another, who had just passed his sword through Mullins, sprang into the fray.

#:~:text='pu,.
Text:  'Put up your swords, boys,' cried the newcomer, 'this man is mine.
Audio: Put up your swords boys, cried the newcomer, this man is mine.

#:~:text=ne.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=thus%20s,.%20
Text:  Thus suddenly Hook found himself face to face with Peter. 
Audio: Thus suddenly Hook found himself face to face with Peter.

#:~:text=the%20others%20d,.%20
Text:  The others drew back and formed a ring round them.
Audio: The others drew back and formed a ring around them.

#:~:text=for%20lon,.%20
Text:  For long the two enemies looked at one another; Hook shuddering slightly, and Peter with the strange smile upon his face.
Audio: For long the two enemies looked at one another, Hook shuddering slightly and Peter with a strange smile upon his face.

#:~:text='so%2C,.
Text:  'So, Pan,' said Hook at last, 'this is all your doing.
Audio: So, pan, said Hook at last, this is all you are doing.

#:~:text=ing.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='ay%2C%20j,.
Text:  'Ay, James Hook,' came the stern answer, 'it is all my doing.
Audio: Aye, James Hook, came the stern answer. It is all my doing.

#:~:text=ing.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='pro,.
Text:  'Proud and insolent youth,' said Hook, 'prepare to meet thy doom.
Audio: Proud and insolent youth, said Hook, prepare to meet thy doom.

#:~:text=om.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='dar,.
Text:  'Dark and sinister man,' Peter answered, 'have at thee.
Audio: Dark and sinister man, Peter answered, have a thee.

#:~:text=thee.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=without%20m,.%20
Text:  Without more words they fell to, and for a space there was no advantage to either blade. 
Audio: Without more words they fell too, and for a space there was no advantage to either blade.

#:~:text=peter%20was%20a%20,.%20
Text:  Peter was a superb swordsman, and parried with dazzling rapidity; ever and anon he followed up a feint with a lunge that got past his foe's defence, but his shorter reach stood him in ill stead, and he could not drive the steel home. 
Audio: Peter was a superb swordsman and parried with dazzling rapidity. Ever and anon he followed up a feint with a lunge that caught past his forced defence, but his shorter reach stood him in ill stead, and he could not drive the steel home.

#:~:text=hook%2C%20s,.%20
Text:  Hook, scarcely his inferior in brilliancy, but not quite so nimble in wrist play, forced him back by the weight of his onset, hoping suddenly to end all with a favourite thrust, taught him long ago by Barbecue at Rio; but to his astonishment he found this thrust turned aside again and again. 
Audio: Hook, scarcely his inferior in brilliancy, but not quite so nimble in wrist play, forced him back by the weight of his onset, hoping suddenly to end all with a favourite thrust. Truth. He did. Taught him long ago by barbecue at Rio. But to his astonishment he found his thrust turned aside again and again.

#:~:text=then%20he%20s,.%20
Text:  Then he sought to close and give the quietus with his iron hook, which all this time had been pawing the air; but Peter doubled under it and, lunging fiercely, pierced him in the ribs. 
Audio: Then he sought to close and give the quietus with his iron hook, which all this time had been pawing the air, but Peter doubled under it and, lunging fiercely, pierced him in the ribs.

#:~:text=at%20sig,.%20
Text:  At sight of his own blood, whose peculiar colour, you remember, was offensive to him, the sword fell from Hook's hand, and he was at Peter's mercy.
Audio: At the sight of his own blood, whose peculiar colour, you remember, was offensive to him, the sword fell from Hook's hand, and he was at Peter's mercy.

#:~:text='now!
Text:  'Now!
Audio: Now!

#:~:text='%20cried%20a,.%20
Text:  ' cried all the boys; but with a magnificent gesture Peter invited his opponent to pick up his sword. 
Audio: Now! cried all the boys, but with a magnificent gesture, Peter invited his opponent to pick up his sword.

#:~:text=hook%20d,.%20
Text:  Hook did so instantly, but with a tragic feeling that Peter was showing good form.
Audio: Hook did so instantly, but with a tragic feeling that Peter was showing good form.

#:~:text=hitherto%20h,.%20
Text:  Hitherto he had thought it was some fiend fighting him, but darker suspicions assailed him now.
Audio: Hit her too. He had thought it was some fiend fighting him, but darker suspicions assailed him now.

#:~:text='pa,%3F
Text:  'Pan, who and what art thou?
Audio: "'Pan! Who and what art thou?'

#:~:text='%20he%20cried%20h,%20
Text:  ' he cried huskily.
Audio: he cried huskily.

#:~:text='i'm%20y,.
Text:  'I'm youth, I'm joy,' Peter answered at a venture, 'I'm a little bird that has broken out of the egg.
Audio: "'I am youth! I am joy!' Peter answered at a venture. I am a little bird that has broken out of the egg.

#:~:text=gg.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=this%2C%20o,.%20
Text:  This, of course, was nonsense; but it was proof to the unhappy Hook that Peter did not know in the least who or what he was, which is the very pinnacle of good form.
Audio: This, of course, was nonsense, but it was proof to the unhappy Hook that Peter did not know in the least who or what he was, which is the very pinnacle of good form.

#:~:text='to%20',.%20
Text:  'To 't again,' he cried despairingly.
Audio: "'Tot again!' he cried despairingly.

#:~:text=he%20foug,.%20
Text:  He fought now like a human flail, and every sweep of that terrible sword would have severed in twain any man or boy who obstructed it; but Peter fluttered round him as if the very wind it made blew him out of the danger zone. 
Audio: He fought now like a human flail, and every sweep of that terrible sword would have severed in twain any man or boy who obstructed it. But Peter fluttered round him as if the very wind it made blew him out of the danger zone,

#:~:text=and%20again%20and%20again%20he%20d,.%20
Text:  And again and again he darted in and pricked.
Audio: and again and again he darted in and pricked.

#:~:text=hook%20was%20f,.%20
Text:  Hook was fighting now without hope. 
Audio: Hook was fighting now without hope.

#:~:text=that%20pa,.%20
Text:  That passionate breast no longer asked for life; but for one boon it craved: to see Peter bad form before it was cold for ever.
Audio: That passionate breast no longer asked for life, but for one boon it craved. To see Peter show bad form before it was cold forever.

#:~:text=aban,.%20
Text:  Abandoning the fight he rushed into the powder magazine and fired it.
Audio: Abandoning the fight, he rushed into the powder magazine and fired it.

#:~:text='in,.
Text:  'In two minutes,' he cried, 'the ship will be blown to pieces.
Audio: "'In two minutes!' he cried. "'The ship will be blown to pieces!'

#:~:text=ces.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=now%2C%20n,.%20
Text:  Now, now, he thought, true form will show.
Audio: Now, now!' he thought. True form will show.

#:~:text=but%20peter%20i,.%20
Text:  But Peter issued from the powder magazine with the shell in his hands, and calmly flung it overboard.
Audio: But Peter issued from the powder magazine with a shell in his hands and calmly flung it overboard.

#:~:text=what%20so,%3F%20
Text:  What sort of form was Hook himself showing? 
Audio: What sort of form was Hook himself showing?

#:~:text=misg,.%20
Text:  Misguided man though he was, we may be glad, without sympathising with him, that in the end he was true to the traditions of his race. 
Audio: Misguided man though he was, we may be glad, without sympathizing with him, that in the end he was true to the traditions of his race.

#:~:text=the%20other%20boys%20,.%20
Text:  The other boys were flying around him now, flouting, scornful; and as he staggered about the deck striking up at them impotently, his mind was no longer with them; it was slouching in the playing fields of long ago, or being sent up for good, or watching the wall-game from a famous wall. 
Audio: The other boys were flying round him now, flouting scornful. And he staggered about the deck, striking up at them impotently, his mind was no longer with them. It was slouching in the playing fields of long ago, or being sent up to the headmaster for good, or watching the wall game from a famous wall.

#:~:text=and%20his%20sh,.%20
Text:  And his shoes were right, and his waistcoat was right, and his tie was right, and his socks were right.
Audio: And his shoes were right, and his waistcoat was right, and his tie was right, and his socks were right.

#:~:text=james%20hook%2C%20,.%20
Text:  James Hook, thou not wholly unheroic figure, farewell.
Audio: James Hook, thou not wholly unheroic figure? Farewell,

#:~:text=for%20we%20h,.%20
Text:  For we have come to his last moment.
Audio: for we have come to his last moment.

#:~:text=seeing%20p,.%20
Text:  Seeing Peter slowly advancing upon him through the air with dagger poised, he sprang upon the bulwarks to cast himself into the sea. 
Audio: Seeing Peter slowly advancing upon him through the air with dagger poised, he sprang upon the bulwarks to cast himself into the sea.

#:~:text=he%20did%20not%20know%20tha,.%20
Text:  He did not know that the crocodile was waiting for him; for we purposely stopped the clock that this knowledge might be spared him: a little mark of respect from us at the end.
Audio: He did not know that the crocodile was waiting for him, for we purposely stopped the clock that this knowledge might be spared him. A little mark of respect from us at the end.

#:~:text=he%20had%20one%20l,.%20
Text:  He had one last triumph, which I think we need not grudge him. 
Audio: He had one last triumph, which I think we need not grudge him.

#:~:text=as%20he%20sto,.%20
Text:  As he stood on the bulwark looking over his shoulder at Peter gliding through the air, he invited him with a gesture to use his foot. 
Audio: As he stood on the bulwark, looking over his shoulder at Peter gliding through the air, he invited him with a gesture to use his foot.

#:~:text=it%20made%20p,.%20
Text:  It made Peter kick instead of stab.
Audio: It made Peter kick instead of stab.

#:~:text=at%20last%20ho,.%20
Text:  At last Hook had got the boon for which he craved.
Audio: At last, Hook had got the boon for which he craved.

#:~:text='ba,.%20
Text:  'Bad form,' he cried jeeringly, and went content to the crocodile.
Audio: Bad form! he cried jeeringly, and went content to the crocodile.

#:~:text=thus%20p,.%20
Text:  Thus perished James Hook.
Audio: Thus perished James Hook.

#:~:text='se,.%20
Text:  'Seventeen,' Slightly sang out; but he was not quite correct in his figures. 
Audio: Seventeen, slightly sangled. But he was not quite correct in his figures.

#:~:text=fif,.%20
Text:  Fifteen paid the penalty for their crimes that night; but two reached the shore: Starkey to be captured by the redskins, who made him nurse for all their papooses, a melancholy come-down for a pirate; and Smee, who henceforth wandered about the world in his spectacles, making a precarious living by saying he was the only man that Jas. 
Audio: Fifteen paid the penalty for their crimes that night, but two reached the shore. Starkey, to be captured by the redskins, who made him nurse for all their papooses, a melancholy come down for a pirate. And Smee, who henceforth wandered about the world in his spectacles, making a precarious living by saying he was the only man that James

#:~:text=hook%20had%20f,%20
Text:  Hook had feared.
Audio: Hook had feared.

#:~:text=wendy%2C%20o,.%20
Text:  Wendy, of course, had stood by taking no part in the fight, though watching Peter with glistening eyes; but now that all was over she became prominent again. 
Audio: Wendy, of course, had stood by taking no part in the fight, though watching Peter with glistening eyes. But now that all was over, she became prominent again.

#:~:text=she%20p,.%20
Text:  She praised them equally, and shuddered delightfully when Michael showed her the place where he had killed one; and then she took them into Hook's cabin and pointed to his watch which was hanging on a nail. 
Audio: She praised them equally and shuddered delightfully when Michael showed her the place where he had killed one. And then she took them into Hook's cabin and pointed to his watch, which was hanging on a nail.

#:~:text=it%20sa,!%20
Text:  It said 'half-past one'!
Audio: It said half past one.

#:~:text=the%20lat,.%20
Text:  The lateness of the hour was almost the biggest thing of all. 
Audio: The lateness of the hour was almost the biggest thing of all.

#:~:text=she%20got%20t,.%20
Text:  She got them to bed in the pirates' bunks pretty quickly, you may be sure; all but Peter, who strutted up and down on deck, until at last he fell asleep by the side of Long Tom. 
Audio: She got them to bed in the pirates' bunks pretty quickly, you may be sure. All but Peter, who strutted up and down on the deck until at last he fell asleep by the side of Long Tom.

#:~:text=he%20had%20one%20o,.%20
Text:  He had one of his dreams that night, and cried in his sleep for a long time, and Wendy held him tight.
Audio: He had one of his dreams that night and cried in his sleep for a long time, and Wendy held him tightly. End of chapter 15 Recording by Kritika

