#:~:text=by%20tw,.%20
Text:  By two bells that morning they were all stirring their stumps; for there was a big sea running; and Tootles, the bo'sun, was among them, with a rope's end in his hand and chewing tobacco. 
Audio: By three bells that morning they were all stirring their stumps, for there was a big sea running, and Tootles the bosom was among them, with a rope's end in his hand and chewing tobacco.

#:~:text=they%20all%20d,.%20
Text:  They all donned pirate clothes cut off at the knee, shaved smartly, and tumbled up, with the true nautical roll and hitching their trousers.
Audio: They all donned pirate clothes, cut off at the knee, shaved smartly, and tumbled up with the true nautical roll in hitching their trousers.

#:~:text=it%20ne,.%20
Text:  It need not be said who was the captain. 
Audio: It need not be said who was the captain.

#:~:text=nibs%20and%20j,.%20
Text:  Nibs and John were first and second mate. 
Audio: Nibs and John were first and second mate.

#:~:text=there%20was%20a%20w,.%20
Text:  There was a woman aboard. 
Audio: There was a woman aboard.

#:~:text=the%20res,.%20
Text:  The rest were tars before the mast, and lived in the fo'c'sle. 
Audio: The rest were tars before the mast, and lived in the forecastle. Peter

#:~:text=peter%20had%20a,.%20
Text:  Peter had already lashed himself to the wheel; but he piped all hands and delivered a short address to them; said he hoped they would do their duty like gallant hearties, but that he knew they were the scum of Rio and the Gold Coast, and if they snapped at him he would tear them. 
Audio: had already lashed himself to the wheel, but he piped all hands and delivered a short address to them, said he hoped they would do their duty like gallant hardies, but that he knew they were the scum of Rio and the Gold Coast, and if they snapped at him he would tear them. The

#:~:text=his%20bl,.%20
Text:  His bluff strident words struck the note sailors understand, and they cheered him lustily. 
Audio: bluff's strident words struck the note sailors understood, and they cheered him lustily. Then

#:~:text=then%20a%20,.%20
Text:  Then a few sharp orders were given, and they turned the ship round, and nosed her for the mainland.
Audio: a few sharp orders were given, and they returned the ship round, and nosed her for the mainland.

#:~:text=captain%20p,.%20
Text:  Captain Pan calculated, after consulting the ship's chart, that if this weather lasted they should strike the Azores about the 21st of June, after which it would save time to fly.
Audio: Captain Pan calculated, after consulting the ship's chart, that if this weather lasted, they should strike the Azores about the twenty-first of June, after which it would save time to fly.

#:~:text=some%20of%20them%20wa,.%20
Text:  Some of them wanted it to be an honest ship and others were in favour of keeping it a pirate; but the captain treated them as dogs, and they dared not express their wishes to him even in a round robin. 
Audio: Some of them wanted it to be an honest ship, and others were in favor of keeping it a pirate, but the captain treated them as dogs, and they dared not express their wishes to him, even in a round robin,

#:~:text=instant%20,.%20
Text:  Instant obedience was the only safe thing. 
Audio: one person after another, as they had to Captain Hook. Instant obedience was the only safe thing.

#:~:text=slightly%20g,.%20
Text:  Slightly got a dozen for looking perplexed when told to take soundings. 
Audio: Slightly got a dozen for looking perplexed when told to take soundings.

#:~:text=the%20ge,.%20
Text:  The general feeling was that Peter was honest just now to lull Wendy's suspicions, but that there might be a change when the new suit was ready, which, against her will, she was making for him out of some of Hook's wickedest garments. 
Audio: The general feeling was that Peter was honest just now to lull Wendy's suspicions, but that there might be a change when the new suit was ready, which, against her will, she was making for him out of some of Hook's wickedest garments.

#:~:text=it%20was%20af,.%20
Text:  It was afterwards whispered among them that on the first night he wore this suit he sat long in the cabin with Hook's cigar-holder in his mouth and one hand clenched, all but the forefinger, which he bent and held threateningly aloft like a hook.
Audio: It was afterwards whispered among them, that on the first night he wore this suit, he sat long in the cabin with Hook's cigar holder in his mouth, and one hand clenched, all but for the forefinger, which he bent and held threateningly aloft like a hook.

#:~:text=instead%20of%20w,.%20
Text:  Instead of watching the ship, however, we must now return to that desolate home from which three of our characters had taken heartless flight so long ago. 
Audio: Instead of watching the ship, however, we must now return to that desolate home from which three of our characters had taken heartless flight so long ago.

#:~:text=it%20seems,.%20
Text:  It seems a shame to have neglected No. 
Audio: It seems a shame to have neglected number

#:~:text=14,us.%20
Text:  14 all this time; and yet we may be sure that Mrs. Darling does not blame us. 
Audio: fourteen all this time, and yet we may be sure that Mrs. Darling does not blame us.

#:~:text=if%20we%20had%20r,%3F%20
Text:  If we had returned sooner to look with sorrowful sympathy at her, she would probably have cried, 'Don't be silly; what do I matter? 
Audio: If we had returned sooner to look with sorrowful sympathy at her, she would probably have cried, Don't be silly. What do I matter?

#:~:text=do%20g,.
Text:  Do go back and keep an eye on the children.
Audio: Do go back and keep an eye on the children.

#:~:text='%20so%20l,.%20
Text:  ' So long as mothers are like this their children will take advantage of them; and they may lay to that.
Audio: So long as mothers are like this, their children will take advantage of them, and they may lay to bed on that.

#:~:text=even%20n,g.%20
Text:  Even now we venture into that familiar nursery only because its lawful occupants are on their way home; we are merely hurrying on in advance of them to see that their beds are properly aired and that Mr. and Mrs. Darling do not go out for the evening. 
Audio: Even now we venture into that familiar nursery only because its lawful occupants are on their way home. We are merely hurrying on in advance of them to see that their beds are properly aired, and that Mr. and Mrs. Darling do not go out for the evening.

#:~:text=we%20are%20n,.%20
Text:  We are no more than servants. 
Audio: We are no more than servants.

#:~:text=why%20o,%3F%20
Text:  Why on earth should their beds be properly aired, seeing that they left them in such a thankless hurry? 
Audio: Why on earth should their beds be properly aired, seeing that they left them in such a thankless hurry?

#:~:text=would%20i,%3F%20
Text:  Would it not serve them jolly well right if they came back and found that their parents were spending the week-end in the country? 
Audio: Would it not serve them jolly well right if they came back and found that their parents were spending the week-end in the country?

#:~:text=it%20would%20b,us.%20
Text:  It would be the moral lesson they have been in need of ever since we met them; but if we contrived things in this way Mrs. Darling would never forgive us.
Audio: It would be the moral lesson that they have been in need of ever since we met them. But if we contrived things in this way, Mrs. Darling would never forgive us.

#:~:text=one%20thing%20i,.%20
Text:  One thing I should like to do immensely, and that is to tell her, in the way authors have, that the children are coming back, that indeed they will be here on Thursday week. 
Audio: One thing I should like to do immensely, and that is to tell her, in the way authors have, that the children are coming back, that indeed they will be here on Thursday week.

#:~:text=this%20would%20s,.%20
Text:  This would spoil so completely the surprise to which Wendy and John and Michael are looking forward. 
Audio: This would spoil so completely the surprise to which Wendy and John and Michael are looking forward.

#:~:text=they%20have%20been%20p,.%20
Text:  They have been planning it out on the ship: mother's rapture, father's shout of joy, Nana's leap through the air to embrace them first, when what they ought to be preparing for is a good hiding. 
Audio: They have been planning it out on the ship. Mother's rapture, father's shout of joy, Nana's leap through the air to embrace them first, when what they ought to be prepared for is a good hiding.

#:~:text=how%20d,n.
Text:  How delicious to spoil it all by breaking the news in advance; so that when they enter grandly Mrs. Darling may not even offer Wendy her mouth, and Mr. Darling may exclaim pettishly, 'Dash it all, here are those boys again.
Audio: How delicious to spoil it all by breaking the news in advance, so that when they enter grandly, Mrs. Darling may not even offer Wendy her mouth, and Mr. Darling may exclaim pittishly, dash it all, hear those boys again.

#:~:text='%20howe,.%20
Text:  ' However, we should get no thanks even for this. 
Audio: However, we should get no thanks even for this.

#:~:text=we%20are%20b,e.%20
Text:  We are beginning to know Mrs. Darling by this time, and may be sure that she would upbraid us for depriving the children of their little pleasure.
Audio: We are beginning to know Mrs. Darling by this time, and may be sure that she would upbraid us for depriving the children of their little pleasure.

#:~:text='but%2C%20m,.
Text:  'But, my dear madam, it is ten days till Thursday week; so that by telling you what's what, we can save you ten days of unhappiness.
Audio: But, my dear madam, it is ten days till Thursday week, so that by telling you what's what, we can save you ten days of unhappiness.

#:~:text=ness.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text='yes%2C%20b,!%20
Text:  'Yes, but at what a cost! 
