Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=you%20see%2C%20t,.%20
Text:  You see, the woman had no proper spirit. 
Audio: You see, the woman had no proper spirit.

#:~:text=i%20had%20m,.%20
Text:  I had meant to say extraordinarily nice things about her; but I despise her, and not one of them will I say now. 
Audio: I had meant to say extraordinarily nice things about her, but I despise her, and not one of them will I say now.

#:~:text=she%20does%20n,.%20
Text:  She does not really need to be told to have things ready, for they are ready. 
Audio: She does not really need to be told to have things ready, for they are ready.

#:~:text=all%20the%20beds%20a,.%20
Text:  All the beds are aired, and she never leaves the house, and observe, the window is open. 
Audio: All the beds are aired, and she never leaves the house, and observe the window is open.

#:~:text=for%20all%20the%20,.%20
Text:  For all the use we are to her, we might go back to the ship. 
Audio: For all the use we are to her, we might well go back to the ship.

#:~:text=however%2C%20a,.%20
Text:  However, as we are here we may as well stay and look on. 
Audio: However, as we are here, we may as well stay and look on.

#:~:text=that%20is%20al,.%20
Text:  That is all we are, lookers-on. 
Audio: That is, all we are, lookers-on.

#:~:text=nobo,.%20
Text:  Nobody really wants us. 
Audio: Nobody really wants us.

#:~:text=so%20le,.%20
Text:  So let us watch and say jaggy things, in the hope that some of them will hurt.
Audio: So let us watch and say jaggy things in the hope that some of them will hurt.

#:~:text=the%20only%20c,.%20
Text:  The only change to be seen in the night-nursery is that between nine and six the kennel is no longer there. 
Audio: The only change to be seen in the night nursery is that between nine and six the kennel is no longer there.

#:~:text=when%20the%20c,e.%20
Text:  When the children flew away, Mr. Darling felt in his bones that all the blame was his for having chained Nana up, and that from first to last she had been wiser than he. 
Audio: When the children flew away, Mr. Darling felt in his bones that all the blame was his for having chained Nana up, and that from first to last she had been wiser than he.

#:~:text=of%20course%2C%20a,.%20
Text:  Of course, as we have seen, he was quite a simple man; indeed he might have passed for a boy again if he had been able to take his baldness off; but he had also a noble sense of justice and a lion courage to do what seemed right to him; and having thought the matter out with anxious care after the flight of the children, he went down on all fours and crawled into the kennel. 
Audio: Of course, as we have seen, he was quite a simple man. Indeed he might have passed for a boy again if he had been able to take his baldness off, but he had also a noble sense of justice, and a lion's courage to do what seemed right to him, and having thought the matter out with anxious care after the flight of the children, he went down on all fours and crawled into the kennel.

#:~:text=to%20al,%3A%20
Text:  To all Mrs. Darling's dear invitations to him to come out he replied sadly but firmly:
Audio: To all Mrs. Darling's dear invitations to him to come out, he replied sadly but firmly,

#:~:text='no%2C%20m,.
Text:  'No, my own one, this is the place for me.
