Audio: my own one, this is the place for me.

#:~:text=in%20the%20bi,.%20
Text:  In the bitterness of his remorse he swore that he would never leave the kennel until his children came back. 
Audio: In the bitterness of his remorse he swore that he would never leave the kennel until his children came back. Of

#:~:text=of%20course%20thi,t.%20
Text:  Of course this was a pity; but whatever Mr. Darling did he had to do in excess; otherwise he soon gave up doing it. 
Audio: Of course this was a pity, but whatever Mr. Darling did he had to do it in excess, otherwise he soon gave up doing it.

#:~:text=and%20there%20n,.%20
Text:  And there never was a more humble man than the once proud George Darling, as he sat in the kennel of an evening talking with his wife of their children and all their pretty ways.
Audio: And there never was a more humble man than the once proud George Darling, as he sat in the kennel of an evening talking with his wife of their children, and all their pretty ways. Very

#:~:text=very%20t,.%20
Text:  Very touching was his deference to Nana. 
Audio: Very touching was his deference to Nana.

#:~:text=he%20would%20not%20let%20h,.%20
Text:  He would not let her come into the kennel, but on all other matters he followed her wishes implicitly.
Audio: He would not let her come into the kennel, but on all other matters he followed her wishes implicitly.

#:~:text=every%20mor,x.%20
Text:  Every morning the kennel was carried with Mr. Darling in it to a cab, which conveyed him to his office, and he returned home in the same way at six. 
Audio: Every morning the kennel was carried with Mr. Darling in it to a cab, which conveyed him to his office, and he returned home in the same way at six.

#:~:text=something%20o,.%20
Text:  Something of the strength of character of the man will be seen if we remember how sensitive he was to the opinion of neighbours: this man whose every movement now attracted surprised attention. 
Audio: Something of the strength of character of the man will be seen if we remember how sensitive he was to the opinion of neighbors, this man whose every movement now attracted surprised attention.

#:~:text=inwardl,.%20
Text:  Inwardly he must have suffered torture; but he preserved a calm exterior even when the young criticised his little home, and he always lifted his hat courteously to any lady who looked inside.
Audio: Inwardly he must have suffered torture, but he preserved a calm exterior even when the young criticized his little home, and he always lifted his hat courteously to any lady who looked inside.

#:~:text=it%20may,.%20
Text:  It may have been quixotic, but it was magnificent. 
Audio: It may have been quesotic, but it was magnificent.

#:~:text=soon%20the%20,.%20
Text:  Soon the inward meaning of it leaked out, and the great heart of the public was touched. 
Audio: Soon the inward meaning of it leaked out, and the great heart of the public was touched.

#:~:text=crowds,.
Text:  Crowds followed the cab, cheering it lustily; charming girls scaled it to get his autograph; interviews appeared in the better class of papers, and society invited him to dinner and added, 'Do come in the kennel.
Audio: Crowds followed the cab, cheering it lustily. Charming girls scaled it to get his autograph. Interviews appeared in the better class of papers, and society invited him to dinner and added, Do come in the kennel.

#:~:text=nel.-,'%20
Text:  '
Audio: 

#:~:text=on%20tha,n.%20
Text:  On that eventful Thursday week Mrs. Darling was in the night-nursery awaiting George's return home: a very sad-eyed woman. 
Audio: On that eventful Thursday week, Mrs. Darling was in the night nursery awaiting George's return home, a very sad-eyed woman.

#:~:text=now%20that%20w,.%20
Text:  Now that we look at her closely and remember the gaiety of her in the old days, all gone now just because she has lost her babes, I find I won't be able to say nasty things about her after all. 
Audio: Now that we look at her closely, and remember the gaiety of her in the old days, all gone now just because she has lost her babes, I find I won't be able to say nasty things about her after all.

#:~:text=if%20she%20wa,.%20
Text:  If she was too fond of her rubbishy children she couldn't help it. 
Audio: If she was too fond of her rubbishy children, she couldn't help it.

#:~:text=look%20at%20her%20i,.%20
Text:  Look at her in her chair, where she has fallen asleep. 
Audio: Look at her in her chair where she has fallen asleep.

#:~:text=the%20corner%20,.%20
Text:  The corner of her mouth, where one looks first, is almost withered up. 
Audio: The corner of her mouth where one looks first is almost withered up.

#:~:text=her%20hand%20m,.%20
Text:  Her hand moves restlessly on her breast as if she had a pain there. 
Audio: Her hand moves restlessly on her breast, as if she had had a pain there.

#:~:text=some%20like%20p,.%20
Text:  Some like Peter best and some like Wendy best, but I like her best. 
Audio: Some like Peter best, and some like Wendy best, but I like her best.

#:~:text=suppose%2C,.%20
Text:  Suppose, to make her happy, we whisper to her in her sleep that the brats are coming back. 
Audio: Suppose to make her happy we whisper to her in her sleep that her brats are coming back. They

#:~:text=they%20are%20real,.%20
Text:  They are really within two miles of the window now, and flying strong, but all we need whisper is that they are on the way. 
Audio: They are really within two miles of the window now, and flying strong, but all we need whisper is that they are on their way.

#:~:text=let',%20
Text:  Let's.
Audio: Let's.

#:~:text=it%20is%20a%20,.%20
Text:  It is a pity we did it, for she has started up, calling their names; and there is no one in the room but Nana.
Audio: It is a pity we did it, for she has started up, calling their names, and there is no one in the room but Nana.

#:~:text='o%20n,.
Text:  'O Nana, I dreamt my dear ones had come back.
